(71, 'SOHK', 'Whale', 'Daymond John', 'Founder & Investor', 'FUBU / Shark Tank', 'Entrepreneur', 'New York, NY', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 73, NULL, 'Built FUBU from $40 into a $6B global brand. Shark Tank investor with $8B+ in deals. Author of ''The Power of Broke.'' Grew up poor in Queens — entire brand is about working with limited resources.', 'Lead with GCU''s first-generation student story and ''Power of Broke'' alignment with affordability.', 'Christian. Openly speaks about prayer and faith in his success story.', '''Power of Broke'' maps to GCU''s accessibility mission. Canyon Ventures speaker or first-gen student scholarship.', '["FUBU $6B", "Shark Tank", "Power of Broke", "First-Gen", "Christian"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, NULL, NULL, '[]'::jsonb),
(72, 'SOHK', 'Review', 'Craig Groeschel', 'Founding Pastor', 'Life.Church', 'Entrepreneur', 'Edmond, OK', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 93, NULL, 'Founding pastor of Life.Church — largest church in America with 100K+ weekly attendees across 40+ campuses. Creator of YouVersion Bible App (500M+ downloads). Author of 15+ books.', 'Lead with GCU''s Christian mission. Life.Church has Phoenix campuses — local connection.', 'One of the most influential pastors in America. Life is the mission.', 'Craig Groeschel at GCU or Life.Church x GCU chapel partnership would be extraordinary. YouVersion is already on every student''s phone.', '["Life.Church", "100K Attendees", "YouVersion 500M Downloads", "Most Influential Pastor", "Phoenix Campuses"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, NULL, NULL, '[]'::jsonb),
(73, 'SOHK', 'Review', 'Tom Ziglar', 'CEO & Speaker', 'Ziglar Inc.', 'Entrepreneur', 'Plano, TX', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 87, NULL, 'CEO of Ziglar Inc. and son of legendary Zig Ziglar. Carries his father''s faith-first, character-first motivation and business development legacy forward. Speaks at Christian businesses, universities, and conferences worldwide.', 'Lead with GCU''s Christian mission and how Zig Ziglar''s principles are embedded in GCU''s culture.', 'Deeply Christian. Carries Zig Ziglar''s faith-first legacy explicitly.', 'Ziglar brand is one of the most trusted in Christian business motivation. GCU-Ziglar curriculum partnership or endorsement would be hugely credible.', '["Zig Ziglar Legacy", "Ziglar Inc.", "Christian Motivation", "Faith-First Business", "Speaker"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, NULL, NULL, '[]'::jsonb),
(74, 'SOHK', 'Whale', 'Drew Brees', 'Former NFL QB', 'Jimmy John''s / Multiple Ventures', 'Sports', 'New Orleans, LA', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 80, NULL, 'NFL Hall of Famer. Led Saints to Super Bowl XLIV. Major investor (Jimmy John''s franchises). Post-Katrina community rebuilding work in New Orleans mirrors CityServe. Active in faith-based community service.', 'Lead with GCU''s sports programs and community rebuilding work. His foundation''s post-Katrina story mirrors CityServe.', 'Deeply Christian. Openly discusses faith throughout career.', 'Drew''s community rebuilding = the CityServe story. Student athlete mentorship or community program partnership.', '["NFL Hall of Fame", "Super Bowl Champion", "Jimmy John''s", "Community Rebuilding", "Christian"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, NULL, NULL, '[]'::jsonb),
(75, 'SOHK', 'Whale', 'Stephen Curry', 'NBA Superstar', 'Golden State Warriors / SC30', 'Sports', 'San Francisco, CA', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 82, NULL, '4x NBA Champion, 2x MVP, greatest shooter in basketball history. Davidson College graduate. Deeply Christian and outspoken about his faith. Runs SC30 — business, media, and charitable enterprise.', 'Lead with student athletes and his Davidson College story — undersized, overlooked, proved everyone wrong. Perfect GCU underdog narrative.', 'One of the most openly Christian NBA players. Points to sky after every made shot.', 'Curry''s Davidson underdog story IS the GCU student story. SC30 x GCU student athlete partnership.', '["4x NBA Champion", "2x MVP", "Davidson Underdog", "SC30", "Deeply Christian"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, NULL, NULL, '[]'::jsonb),
(76, 'SOHK', 'Whale', 'Tyler Perry', 'Founder & CEO', 'Tyler Perry Studios', 'Entertainment', 'Atlanta, GA', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 82, NULL, 'Overcame homelessness, childhood abuse, and multiple failures to build Tyler Perry Studios — first major studio owned by a Black person. $1B+ valued. Deeply Christian with a radical redemption story.', 'Lead with GCU''s media programs and CityServe community transformation. His redemption story and giving record align.', 'Born-again Christian. Credits God entirely for rescue from homelessness. Active in Christian giving.', 'Tyler''s redemption story is extraordinary. Media program partnership or named scholarship.', '["Tyler Perry Studios", "Homeless to Billionaire", "Christian", "Media Empire", "Redemption Story"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, NULL, NULL, '[]'::jsonb),
(77, 'SOHK', 'Whale', 'Matthew McConaughey', 'Actor & Author', 'j.k. livin Foundation', 'Entertainment', 'Austin, TX', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 71, NULL, 'Academy Award-winning actor, author of ''Greenlights,'' founder of j.k. livin Foundation serving underserved youth. Teaches a course at UT Austin. Known for philosophy of meaning and purpose.', 'His foundation serves underserved youth — exact CityServe demographic. UT Austin teaching shows university openness.', 'Christian. Discusses faith in ''Greenlights'' and interviews.', 'j.k. livin Foundation + CityServe = natural partnership. UT Austin engagement shows university willingness.', '["Academy Award Winner", "Greenlights", "j.k. livin Foundation", "UT Austin", "Christian"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, NULL, NULL, '[]'::jsonb),
