Would you be open to a 20-minute call with President Brian Mueller?

With great respect,
[Name] | Grand Canyon University | [Phone]', '["https://baptistnews.com/article/paxtons-pastor-joins-faith-team-for-cornyn/", "https://prestonwood.org/about/our-staff/dr-jack-graham/", "https://jackgraham.org/", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jack_Graham_(pastor)"]'::jsonb),
(1007, 'KIC', NULL, 'Ronnie Floyd', NULL, NULL, 'Baptist Denomination Leaders (Household)', 'Rogers, Arkansas', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 76, NULL, 'Dr. Ronnie Floyd was born in Perryville, Arkansas. He served as Senior Pastor of Cross Church in Northwest Arkansas for over 33 years (1986-2019), growing it into one of the largest churches in the region with multiple campuses and thousands of members. He served as President of the Southern Baptist Convention (2014-2016) — the denomination''s highest elected office — and as President and CEO of the SBC Executive Committee (2019-2021), overseeing the central administrative body of the 14-million-member denomination during one of its most turbulent periods regarding sexual abuse accountability. He founded the Great Commission Collective, a ministry focused on spiritual awakening and revival in America. He is the author of over 20 books. He received his bachelor''s degree from Ouachita Baptist University and his master''s and doctoral degrees from Southwestern Baptist Theological Seminary. He was called by both the Clinton and Bush White Houses to pray at key national occasions. He is married to Jeana Floyd and has two sons.', 'Email through Cross Church (ronnie@crosschurch.com format) or call (479) 751-4523. Floyd''s personal website ronniekfloyd.com has a contact form. His Northwest Arkansas base puts him near Walmart/Sam''s Club HQ — a GCU event at Walmart''s corporate campus (where he has relationships) would be a compelling venue. Lead with GCU''s SBC founding heritage.

