I''m reaching out from Grand Canyon University — the largest Christian university in America. Your decades of SBC leadership are deeply respected here.

Would you be open to a brief call with President Brian Mueller?

With great respect,
[Name] | Grand Canyon University | [Phone]', '["https://ronniekfloyd.com", "https://crosschurch.com"]'::jsonb),
(1008, 'KIC', NULL, 'James Merritt', 'Pastor of Cross Pointe Church', 'Cross Pointe Church', 'Baptist Denomination Leaders (Household)', 'Duluth, Georgia', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 76, NULL, 'Dr. James Merritt was born in 1952 in Palatka, Florida, the son of a Baptist minister. He attended Stetson University and earned his Ph.D. from Mid-America Baptist Theological Seminary. He has served as Senior Pastor of Cross Pointe Church in Duluth, Georgia since 2000. He previously served as President of the Southern Baptist Convention (2000-2002) — the largest Protestant denomination in America with 14 million members. He is the host of Touching Lives, a syndicated television ministry broadcast in over 200+ countries reaching tens of millions of viewers globally. He has authored over 30 books. He served on President George W. Bush''s National Prayer Committee and spoke at the White House. He is married to Teresa Merritt and has three sons: Jonathan (a prominent faith writer and author), James, and Josh. He was a member of President Trump''s evangelical advisory board.', 'Contact Touching Lives ministry: info@touchinglives.org, (770) 292-0306. Cross Pointe Church: (770) 497-9500. Merritt''s global TV reach (200+ countries) makes him a media partner as much as a donor prospect — a GCU interview on Touching Lives is the right first ask. His son Jonathan Merritt is a prominent faith writer and accessible on social media — a warm intro through Jonathan is viable.

