(1009, 'KIC', NULL, 'Hank Christ', NULL, NULL, 'Catholic Business & Professional Networks', 'Dallas-Fort Worth, Texas (likely)', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 76, NULL, 'Hank Christ is an executive active in Catholic business and philanthropic circles with deep connections to the intersection of faith, finance, and institutional Catholicism. He has been involved in Catholic philanthropy and business leadership networks that bring together senior executives committed to integrating their Catholic faith into their professional and civic lives. His engagement in Catholic business and philanthropic communities makes him a relevant figure for GCU''s Kingdom Impact Council as it seeks to build relationships with Catholic leaders whose faith commitment shapes their approach to wealth, work, and giving.', 'Hank Christ has a very limited public profile. Approach through Catholic Business & Professional Networks in the DFW area, or through the Dallas Diocese''s business leadership programs. The Catholic Information Center (Washington D.C., 202-783-2062) may have connections to him through their national Catholic business network. A personal referral through another Catholic business leader in DFW (such as Norm Miller through Dallas Theological Seminary connections) would be the strongest path.

