(1010, 'KIC', NULL, 'Cindy Owens', NULL, NULL, 'Christian Business Leaders', 'St. Louis, Missouri', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 76, NULL, 'Cindy Owens is a nonprofit executive, humanitarian, and co-founder of The Rooted Sisters — a national network of Christian women business leaders that has grown to 13 markets and an annual conference of 800+ attendees. She has an extensive career in executive leadership, including serving as CEO of the American Red Cross of Missouri & Arkansas, where she led a team of over 2,000 staff and volunteers and grew regional revenue from $6 million to over $28 million. She also held executive roles with the American Lung Association. She holds a master''s degree in public administration and has studied at Harvard University''s Kennedy School of Government and in London. She has lectured at Washington University and Saint Louis University, and serves on multiple nonprofit and corporate boards. She is a committed Christian who integrates faith into every aspect of her professional and philanthropic work.

Other board roles: The Rooted Sisters (co-founder & CEO). American Red Cross Missouri & Arkansas (former CEO). American Lung Association (former executive). Multiple nonprofit and corporate boards (ongoing).', 'Connect via LinkedIn (linkedin.com/in/cindy-owens-mpa-95bba611) or through therootedsisters.com. She is professionally accessible and entrepreneurial. The Rooted Sisters annual conference (800+ attendees) is an ideal GCU sponsorship opportunity — a GCU scholarship announcement at their conference would generate significant goodwill. Lead with women''s leadership and GCU''s female student majority.

