(1016, 'KIC', NULL, 'Terry Schlossberg', NULL, 'Alliance Defending Freedom', 'Christian Legal & Medical Professional Networks', 'Colorado Springs, Colorado', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 76, NULL, 'Terry Schlossberg is an executive and advocate in the Presbyterian Church in America with deep involvement in pro-life policy and Christian advocacy at the intersection of bioethics and faith. She has served in leadership roles focused on defending the sanctity of human life from a Reformed Christian theological perspective and has been involved in national conversations about abortion, bioethics, and Christian civic engagement. Her combination of denominational leadership in the PCA, bioethics advocacy, and Reformed Christian conviction makes her a relevant figure for GCU''s Kingdom Impact Council in the arena of Christian public policy.', 'Contact Alliance Defending Freedom HQ in Scottsdale: (480) 444-0020 or adflegal.org. ADF is 15 minutes from GCU''s campus — the geographic proximity is the strongest hook. A GCU-ADF intern pipeline or law and policy symposium co-hosted at GCU''s campus is a natural first conversation. Ask Schlossberg for an introduction to ADF''s university partnership team.

Contact: Alliance Defending Freedom: adflegal.org. Phone: (480) 444-0020. ADF HQ: 15100 N. 90th Street, Scottsdale, AZ 85260. NOTE: ADF is headquartered in Scottsdale — GCU''s backyard.', 'Former chair of Alliance Defending Freedom board; advisor to Presbyterian Coalition on faith and renewal matters', 'ADF is headquartered in Scottsdale, Arizona — directly in GCU''s geographic community. A GCU-ADF partnership for law students, internships, or religious liberty programming would be geographically natural and mission-aligned. Schlossberg''s advocacy connections are a warm path to ADF leadership.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'PCA executive and pro-life bioethics advocate; defender of biblical sanctity of life in denominational and public policy contexts; Reformed Christian public voice on human dignity issues.', 'Dear Ms. Schlossberg,

Grand Canyon University is the largest Christian university in America — and Alliance Defending Freedom is headquartered just miles from our campus in Scottsdale, Arizona. The proximity and the mission alignment feel too significant to ignore.

We would love to explore a formal partnership between GCU and ADF — whether through a GCU law and policy program, student internships at ADF, or a joint religious liberty symposium. Would you be open to making an introduction?

With great respect for ADF''s extraordinary impact,
