(1017, 'KIC', NULL, 'Joe Jimenez', NULL, 'Novartis', 'Christian Pharma & Biotech Executives (Household)', 'Atherton, California', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 76, NULL, 'Joe Jimenez is a former CEO of Novartis, one of the world''s largest pharmaceutical companies, where he led the organization from 2010 to 2018 through a period of significant strategic transformation and portfolio reshaping. He is a Christian executive who has spoken about the role of faith in his leadership and personal life. Jimenez serves on multiple corporate boards and is active in global health and business leadership circles. His combination of Fortune 500 pharmaceutical CEO experience, board-level influence, and Christian faith makes him a significant figure for GCU''s Kingdom Impact Council, particularly in connecting faith with healthcare and global business leadership.', 'Household-name pharma executive with explicit Catholic faith commitment demonstrated through board service at Catholic Charities USA.

Contact: Joe Jimenez: Reach through Novartis alumni networks or board connections. Novartis AG, Basel, Switzerland. LinkedIn: linkedin.com/in/joe-jimenez.', 'Publicly shared his Catholic faith in interviews, stating it guides his leadership and ethics, including service on the board of Catholic Charities USA.', 'No direct GCU connection documented. GCU''s pre-med and pharmaceutical sciences programs are the natural connection point — a Jimenez endowed scholarship for GCU healthcare or pre-med students would align with his life''s work in pharmaceuticals.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Former Novartis CEO (2010-2018) who oversaw major acquisitions like Alcon and drove global pharmaceutical growth.', 'Dear Mr. Jimenez,

