(1018, 'KIC', NULL, 'Eugene Scalia', NULL, NULL, 'Christian Supreme Court Clerks & Legal Influencers', 'Washington, D.C.', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 76, NULL, 'Eugene Scalia served as U.S. Secretary of Labor under President Trump from 2019 to 2021, having previously served as a partner at Gibson, Dunn & Crutcher, one of America''s most prestigious law firms. He is the son of the late Supreme Court Justice Antonin Scalia, one of the most consequential conservative Catholic jurists in American history, and shares his father''s Catholic faith and originalist legal philosophy. Scalia has been involved in religious liberty litigation and policy matters throughout his career. His combination of Cabinet-level government service, elite legal credentials, and deep Catholic heritage makes him a relevant figure for GCU''s Kingdom Impact Council in the arena of faith and public service.', 'High-level federal executive with SCOTUS clerkship, major Catholic faith profile, and policy influence

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Gibson, Dunn & Crutcher LLP: 1050 Connecticut Avenue NW, Washington, D.C. 20036 | Phone: (202) 955-8500

Gibson, Dunn & Crutcher LLP: gibsondunn.com. Washington D.C. office: 1050 Connecticut Avenue NW, Washington DC 20036. Phone: (202) 955-8500. Email format: escalia@gibsondunn.com.', 'Devout Catholic, son of prominent Catholic jurist Antonin Scalia, with public involvement in faith-based policy', 'No direct GCU connection documented. As former Secretary of Labor with regulatory expertise, Scalia would be a compelling speaker for GCU''s Colangelo College of Business or a legal/policy symposium. His Catholic faith and conservative legal values align with GCU''s mission.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '78th U.S. Secretary of Labor; former Gibson Dunn partner; son of Justice Antonin Scalia; Catholic public servant with deep roots in federal executive and legal service.', 'Dear Secretary Scalia,

