(1019, 'KIC', NULL, 'Jonathan Mitchell', 'Constitutional litigator at Mitchell Law PLLC', 'Mitchell Law PLLC', 'Christian Supreme Court Clerks & Legal Influencers', 'Austin, Texas', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 76, NULL, 'Jonathan Mitchell is a constitutional lawyer and former Solicitor General of Texas who has been one of the most consequential legal architects of pro-life legislation in America. He is the author of the Texas Heartbeat Act''s civil enforcement mechanism, which became one of the most discussed abortion restriction strategies in the post-Roe landscape. Mitchell is a devout Catholic whose legal work is explicitly shaped by his faith commitments. His combination of elite legal credentials, landmark pro-life legal innovation, and Catholic faith makes him a significant figure in the intersection of Christian conviction and American jurisprudence.', 'High-profile constitutional litigator with major influence on religious liberty and pro-life jurisprudence

Contact: Joe Jimenez: Reach through Novartis alumni networks or board connections. Novartis AG, Basel, Switzerland. LinkedIn: linkedin.com/in/joe-jimenez.', 'Devout Catholic; author of landmark pro-life legal innovations including the Texas Heartbeat Act''s civil enforcement mechanism; Catholic legal theory shapes his jurisprudence.', 'His pioneering work in pro-life constitutional law and his Catholic conviction about the legal foundations of life protection are directly relevant to GCU''s law school partnerships and Christian public policy programs.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Former Solicitor General of Texas; drafted Texas Heartbeat Act and argued election-related cases before SCOTUS', NULL, '["https://www.texasbar.com/AM/Template.cfm?Section=Find_A_Lawyer&template=%2FCustomsource%2FMemberDirectory%2FMemberDirectoryDetail.cfm&ContactID=316710", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jonathan_F._Mitchell", "https://fedsoc.org/bio/jonathan-mitchell", "https://www.mitchell.law/"]'::jsonb),
(1020, 'KIC', NULL, 'John Hawthorne', NULL, 'Point Loma Nazarene University', 'Education', 'Spokane, Washington', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 76, NULL, 'John Hawthorne is a Christian sociologist, academic, and author who has written and spoken extensively on the intersection of faith, higher education, and American Christianity. He has served in academic and administrative roles at Christian universities and has been a thoughtful analyst of trends in evangelical higher education and Christian institutional life. His scholarly perspective on Christian higher education makes him a relevant figure for GCU''s academic and institutional mission.', 'Accomplished retired Christian higher ed administrator with extensive experience available for advisory and mentorship roles.

Contact: Reach through Council for Christian Colleges and Universities (CCCU) or Christian higher education academic networks. Azusa Pacific University where he has been affiliated: apu.edu. Phone: (626) 969-3434.', 'Nearly four decades as faculty and administrator in Christian higher education at Nazarene and other evangelical institutions', 'His scholarly work on Christian higher education trends and his academic leadership in faith-integrated institutions makes him a relevant research and advisory voice for GCU''s institutional development.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Veteran Christian higher educator with provost-level leadership across multiple evangelical and Nazarene institutions over 40 years.', NULL, '["https://johnhawthorne.substack.com/p/im-tempted-to-rejoin-the-church-of", "https://johnhawthorne.substack.com/p/the-future-christian-podcast", "https://sojo.net/articles/interview/why-are-christian-colleges-fighting-culture-wars-fear", "https://christianscholars.com/fidelity-and-fearless-engagement-charting-the-future-of-christian-colleges/"]'::jsonb),
(1021, 'KIC', NULL, 'Sylvia Nash', 'Consultant, Lillestrand Leadership Consulting', 'America''s Christian Credit Union', 'Faith-Based Credit Unions & Cooperatives', 'Washington, D.C.', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 76, NULL, 'Sylvia Nash is a faith-driven leader in Christian education and nonprofit management who has served in executive roles connecting Christian institutional leadership with community development and educational access. Her background in Christian higher education administration and her commitment to faith-integrated education make her a relevant figure for GCU''s Kingdom Impact Council as it seeks to build relationships with Christian educational leaders.', 'Deep experience in Christian executive networking and leadership development; bridge between faith and marketplace

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: National Federation of Community Development Credit Unions: 39 Broadway, Suite 2140, New York, NY 10006 | cdcu.coop', 'Director of America''s Christian Credit Union; former CEO of Christian Leadership Alliance, a Christian executive network', 'America''s Christian Credit Union''s mission of providing ethical, faith-aligned financial services resonates directly with GCU''s commitment to making Christian education financially accessible. A partnership around student financial literacy is a natural entry point.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Former CEO of Christian Leadership Alliance; now consulting on leadership while serving as credit union director', NULL, '["https://www.cuinsight.com/press-release/americas-christian-credit-union-announces-2019-board-election-results-and-officer-appointments/", "https://americaschristiancu.com/leadership/", "https://resources.americaschristiancu.com/hubfs/Annual%20Reports/2023-Annual-Report.pdf", "https://www.cuinsight.com/press-release/americas-christian-credit-union-conducts-56th-annual-meeting/"]'::jsonb),
(1022, 'KIC', NULL, 'Justo L. González', 'Retired historian and theologian', NULL, 'Hispanic Christian Leaders (Household)', 'Decatur, Georgia', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 76, NULL, 'Justo L. González is one of the most influential Hispanic Christian theologians and church historians in American history, having authored over 100 books on Christian history and theology, including the widely used three-volume History of Christian Thought and the popular church history A Story of Christianity. González is a United Methodist minister and theologian of Cuban descent who has shaped how generations of seminary students understand the history of the Christian church. His combination of extraordinary scholarly output, Hispanic Christian voice, and ecumenical theological range makes him one of the most significant Christian academic figures in America.', 'Towering historical voice in Hispanic Christianity whose legacy continues shaping Latino evangelical identity and doctrine.

Contact: Justo Gonzalez: Reach through Candler School of Theology at Emory University where he has been affiliated. Emory: 1531 Dickey Dr, Atlanta, GA 30322. Phone: (404) 727-6326. Email: candler@emory.edu', 'Methodist minister whose writings emphasize Scripture and Hispanic Christian heritage; author of over 100 books on church history and Latino theology.', 'His landmark contributions to Hispanic Christian theology and church history are directly relevant to GCU''s theology programs and its growing Hispanic student population — making him a compelling advisory and speaking connection.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Prolific scholar with over 100 books shaping Latino Protestant thought and Hispanic theological tradition.', NULL, '["https://worship.calvin.edu/people/justo-l-gonzalez", "https://www.ivpress.com/justo-l-gonzalez", "https://candler.emory.edu/manana-from-today/", "https://gonzalezcenter.org"]'::jsonb),
(1023, 'KIC', NULL, 'William G. Boykin', NULL, NULL, 'Military & Veterans', 'Washington, D.C.', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 76, NULL, 'Lieutenant General William G. Boykin (U.S. Army, Ret.) is one of America''s most decorated and storied military leaders. He was a founding member of Delta Force in 1977 and participated in the failed Iran hostage rescue attempt (Operation Eagle Claw, 1980). He commanded U.S. Army Special Forces in battles in Grenada, Panama, and Somalia — including the ''Black Hawk Down'' battle in Mogadishu in 1993 that was later immortalized in a book and film. He served as Deputy Undersecretary of Defense for Intelligence under President George W. Bush from 2002-2007, overseeing intelligence collection in the war on terror. He is a graduate of Virginia Military Institute and holds advanced degrees from two universities. He is a fervent Evangelical Christian who has spoken at hundreds of military, church, and policy events about the intersection of faith, service, and national security. He now serves as Executive Vice President of the Family Research Council (FRC), one of America''s largest conservative Christian advocacy organizations, with offices in Washington D.C.

Other board roles: Family Research Council (Executive Vice President, 2012-present). Center for Security Policy (Senior Fellow). Liberty Guard (board). Formerly: Delta Force, U.S. Army Special Forces Command, Deputy Undersecretary of Defense for Intelligence.', 'Contact Family Research Council: (202) 393-2100 or frc.org. Boykin''s email format: wboykin@frc.org. He is accessible through FRC and frequently speaks at military, church, and conservative university events. A GCU military appreciation chapel event headlined by General Boykin would be highly compelling for GCU''s veteran student population. Lead with GCU''s veteran student community.

Contact: Family Research Council: frc.org. Phone: (202) 393-2100. Address: 801 G St NW, Washington D.C. 20001. General Boykin contact: wboykin@frc.org (format). Speaking through FRC or Christian speakers bureaus.', 'Ordained Baptist minister and evangelical speaker who frequently testifies to his Christian faith, authoring *Never Surrender* detailing spiritual warfare.', 'GCU has one of the largest military and veteran student populations in Arizona. Boykin''s Delta Force service, ''Black Hawk Down'' heroism, and FRC leadership make him a compelling chapel speaker, military appreciation event headliner, and potential bridge to FRC''s national Christian donor network.', '[]'::jsonb, '[{"date": "2026", "title": "Gen. William Boykin \u2014 Family Research Council Executive VP profile", "source": "Family Research Council", "url": "https://frc.org/boykin"}, {"date": "2026", "title": "William Boykin Wikipedia \u2014 Delta Force founder, Black Hawk Down battle commander, Deputy Undersecretary of Defense", "source": "Wikipedia", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/William_G._Boykin"}]'::jsonb, 'Retired Army Lieutenant General who commanded Delta Force during the Battle of Mogadishu and led post-9/11 intelligence efforts.', 'Dear General Boykin,

I''m reaching out from Grand Canyon University — the largest Christian university in America, with one of Arizona''s largest veteran student communities.

Would you be open to a brief call with President Brian Mueller?

With deep gratitude for your service,
[Name] | Grand Canyon University | [Phone]', '["https://frc.org/boykin", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/William_G._Boykin"]'::jsonb),
(1024, 'KIC', NULL, 'Tedde Reid', 'Board Member', 'Living Water International', 'Missions & Relief Org Boards (Beyond Top-3)', 'Houston, Texas', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 76, NULL, 'Tedde Reid is a faith-driven leader in Christian business and philanthropy with connections to the evangelical marketplace ministry community. She has been involved in organizations and initiatives that bring together Christian executives and philanthropists for Kingdom-oriented conversations about stewardship, generosity, and faith-integrated leadership. Her involvement in Christian business and philanthropic networks makes her a relevant figure for GCU''s Kingdom Impact Council.', 'Approach through Christian philanthropy networks or National Christian Foundation connections. Her involvement in faith-driven giving communities makes a Development office introduction the natural entry point.

Contact: Reach through National Christian Foundation: ncfgiving.com. Phone: (404) 252-0100. Or through Generous Giving network: generousgiving.org.', 'Faith-driven philanthropist and Christian stewardship advocate; active in networks connecting Christian donors with Kingdom-aligned giving opportunities.', 'Her involvement in Christian stewardship and generosity networks aligns directly with GCU''s fundraising mission and the Kingdom Impact Council''s philanthropic goals.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Christian philanthropist and stewardship advocate; active in faith-driven giving networks connecting major donors to Kingdom causes.', NULL, '["https://water.cc/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/2019-Annual-Review.pdf", "https://water.cc/leadership/", "https://water.cc/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Annual-Review-2023-2024.pdf", "https://water.cc/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/2021-Annual-Review-updated.pdf"]'::jsonb),
(1025, 'KIC', NULL, 'Frank Reich', NULL, NULL, 'NCAA Christian Coaches & Athletic Leadership', 'Indianapolis, Indiana', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 76, NULL, 'Frank Reich has one of the most theologically unusual careers in professional football. After playing 14 seasons as a backup quarterback — most famously engineering the greatest comeback in NFL playoff history (41-38 over the Houston Oilers in 1993 while down 32 points) — Reich felt called to full-time ministry and enrolled at Reformed Theological Seminary in Charlotte, North Carolina, eventually becoming its President. He then returned to football as an offensive coordinator, helping the Philadelphia Eagles win Super Bowl LII in 2018. He served as head coach of the Indianapolis Colts (2018–2022, 40-33-1 record, two playoff appearances) and briefly the Carolina Panthers (2023). In March 2025, he was hired as interim head coach of the Stanford Cardinal football team by General Manager Andrew Luck. He speaks at churches, youth rallies, and Christian universities on faith, resilience, and calling — Premiere Speakers Bureau describes him as a top Christian fundraising and motivational speaker. He is married with three daughters.

Other board roles: Stanford University Football (interim head coach, 2025). Formerly: Indianapolis Colts (head coach, 2018-2022); Carolina Panthers (head coach, 2023); Reformed Theological Seminary Charlotte (President); Philadelphia Eagles (offensive coordinator, Super Bowl LII champion).', 'Contact through Premiere Speakers Bureau (premierespeakers.com, 615-261-4000) — they represent Reich for Christian speaking events. He has an existing record of speaking at Christian education events and has praised Christian education publicly. His 2025 role at Stanford means he is in the Bay Area — a GCU event in Arizona or a virtual chapel address are both viable. Lead with his ministry calling, not his coaching record.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Stanford University Athletics: Angell Field House, Stanford, CA 94305 | Premiere Speakers Bureau: (615) 261-4000

Speaking: Premiere Speakers Bureau, premierespeakers.com, (615) 261-4000. Also All American Speakers Bureau. Stanford University Football: stanfordcardinal.com. Previous speaking praised specifically for ''supporting Christian education.''', 'Former pastor; public statement: ''I just want to be faithful to exalt the name of Christ, be faithful to live out, eat, breathe, and sleep the Word of God''', 'Frank Reich has spoken explicitly in support of Christian education at events — Premiere Speakers Bureau quotes a testimonial praising his message on that topic. GCU is the perfect platform for that message. Stanford''s proximity to Silicon Valley and his new role there makes 2025 a high-visibility moment for Reich.', '[]'::jsonb, '[{"date": "2026", "title": "Frank Reich Wikipedia \u2014 NFL head coach Colts/Panthers, Reformed Theological Seminary President, Stanford interim HC 2025", "source": "Wikipedia", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frank_Reich"}, {"date": "2026", "title": "Premiere Speakers Bureau \u2014 Frank Reich Christian speaking engagements, (615) 261-4000", "source": "Premiere Speakers Bureau", "url": "https://premierespeakers.com"}]'::jsonb, 'Former NFL head coach (Carolina Panthers, Indianapolis Colts); open evangelical Christian who integrated faith into team culture; now active in Christian sports ministry.', 'Dear Frank,

I''m reaching out from Grand Canyon University — the largest Christian university in America. Your journey is one our students talk about.

Would you be open to a brief call with President Brian Mueller?

With great admiration,
[Name] | Grand Canyon University | [Phone]', '["https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frank_Reich", "https://premierespeakers.com"]'::jsonb),
(1026, 'KIC', NULL, 'Graham Daniels', NULL, 'Christians in Sport', 'Sports', 'Bicester, Oxfordshire, UK', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 76, NULL, 'Graham Daniels is a former professional footballer (Cambridge United, UK) who became one of the most influential voices at the intersection of Christian faith and professional sport in the world. He serves as General Director of Christians in Sport, a UK-based organization that works with professional and amateur athletes across all sports to help them explore and live out their Christian faith. Christians in Sport works in partnership with sports federations and professional clubs across the UK and internationally. Daniels has spoken at World Cups, Olympic Games, and major sporting events globally. He is a prolific broadcaster and speaker, appearing regularly on BBC and other major media discussing faith in sport. He holds a master''s degree in sports science. He is based in the UK but travels internationally.', 'Email: graham.daniels@christiansinsport.org.uk. Christians in Sport HQ: +44 1869 255 630. Daniels is UK-based but travels internationally. A GCU Athletics collaboration or international student-athlete connection is the right entry point. This is a program partnership conversation rather than a major gift conversation — start with a Zoom call between GCU Athletics chaplain and Daniels.

Contact: Frank Reich: Reach through NFL coaching alumni networks or Indianapolis Colts organization. NFL Alumni Association: nflalumni.org. Or through Fellowship of Christian Athletes speaker bureau: fca.org.', 'Executive role at Christians in Sport, a faith-based organization; FCA Board of Trustees member committed to advancing Jesus-centered vision.', 'Christians in Sport is the UK equivalent of Athletes in Action — GCU''s existing sports ministry partnerships could extend to a formal Christians in Sport collaboration for GCU''s UK-based or internationally recruited athletes. Daniels is a warm intro to the global Christian sports ministry world.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'International sports ministry leader with Christians in Sport (UK) and service on FCA''s global Board of Trustees.', 'Dear Graham,

Grand Canyon University in Phoenix, Arizona is the largest Christian university in America — with over 600 student-athletes who take their faith as seriously as their sport. We have watched Christians in Sport''s extraordinary impact on professional athletes globally with great admiration.

We would love to explore whether a formal partnership between GCU Athletics and Christians in Sport might serve our student-athletes and create a pipeline for GCU athletes going into professional sports in the UK and Europe.

Would you be open to a conversation?

With great respect for your extraordinary ministry,
[Your Name]
GCU Athletics / Development Office', '["https://www.ridley.cam.ac.uk/team/graham-daniels", "https://christiansinsport.org.uk/about/our-team/", "https://sportsspectrum.com/get-in-the-game/2025/10/16/podcast-graham-daniels-soccer-christians-in-sport/", "https://www.fca.org/aboutus/who-we-are/board-of-trustees"]'::jsonb),
(1027, 'KIC', NULL, 'Bishop Will Willimon', 'Former Bishop of North Alabama Conference; Duke Chapel preacher', NULL, 'Eastern Orthodox, Anglican & Methodist US Leaders', 'Durham, North Carolina', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 76, NULL, 'Bishop Will Willimon is a United Methodist bishop, theologian, and one of the most prolific and widely read preachers and pastoral theologians in American Protestantism. He served as Dean of the Chapel and Professor of Christian Ministry at Duke University for 20 years and has authored over 70 books on preaching, pastoral ministry, and Christian discipleship. Christianity Today named him one of the most effective preachers in the English-speaking world. Willimon''s combination of episcopal leadership, academic theological depth, and extraordinary writing output make him one of the most significant voices in mainline Protestant Christianity.', 'Highly influential Methodist theologian and preacher with major editorial and pastoral leadership credentials.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Duke Divinity School: Duke University, Durham, NC 27708 | Phone: (919) 660-3400 | divinity.duke.edu', 'United Methodist bishop and theologian; authored over 70 books on preaching, spiritual formation, and Christian discipleship; named one of the most effective preachers in the English-speaking world by Christianity Today.', 'His decades of pastoral theological leadership, Wesleyan spirituality writing, and academic influence at Duke are directly relevant to GCU''s theology faculty and chapel programming conversations.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'United Methodist Bishop; former Dean of Duke Chapel; author of over 70 books on Christian ministry; ranked among top English-speaking preachers by Christianity Today.', NULL, '["https://faith.yale.edu/people/will-willimon", "https://www.christiancentury.org/article/2012-05/sent-serve"]'::jsonb),
(1028, 'KIC', NULL, 'Allyson Felix', 'Retired track and field athlete', NULL, 'Christian Athletes (Household Names)', 'Los Angeles, California', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'Allyson Felix is the most decorated American track and field Olympian of all time, with 11 Olympic medals (7 gold) across five Olympic Games and 20 World Championship medals — the most in history. She retired from competitive running in 2022 after a career spanning 19 years. In 2025, she delivered the Baccalaureate address at Brown University, speaking on faith, purpose, and resilience. She co-founded Saysh (footwear brand, est. revenue $1.2M in 2025) with her brother Wes Felix, and co-founded Always Alpha in late 2024 — a sports management agency specifically for female athletes. She earns approximately $800,000 annually from speaking engagements. She is a born-again Evangelical Christian raised in a devout household — her father Paul Felix is an ordained minister and professor of New Testament Greek. She attended Los Angeles Baptist High School. She has been a vocal advocate for Black maternal health following her own emergency C-section at 32 weeks in 2018. She is married to Kenneth Ferguson and has two children: daughter Camryn and son Kenneth III (Trey, born 2024). She lives in Los Angeles.

Other board roles: Saysh (co-founder, 2021-present). Always Alpha (co-founder, 2024-present). Athleta (long-term partner and ambassador). Athletes'' Commission at USA Track & Field (former).', 'Book through AAE Speakers Bureau (1-800-698-2536) or Harry Walker Agency (harrywalker.com). Felix travels from Los Angeles. Her brother Wes Felix is her agent and business partner — reaching Wes is the most direct path to Allyson. Felix actively accepts faith-based university speaking engagements and has spoken at Brown University''s 2025 Baccalaureate. A GCU commencement or women''s leadership event is a natural fit.

Contact: Allyson Felix: Reach through USA Track and Field or Fellowship of Christian Athletes athlete network. FCA national: fca.org. Phone: (816) 920-7600.', 'Vocal Christian athlete listed among outspoken faith followers in multiple Christian athlete sources.', 'No direct GCU connection documented. However, Felix''s Christian faith, advocacy for women and maternal health, and her ''Always Alpha'' sports agency for female athletes align directly with GCU''s women''s athletics programs and nursing/healthcare college. A GCU commencement speaker or chapel keynote would be a natural fit — she actively speaks at faith-based universities and events.', '[]'::jsonb, '[{"date": "May 19, 2026", "title": "Allyson Felix joins 2026 ISPO Leaders Summit speaker lineup \u2014 discussing LA28 Olympic comeback and Always Alpha", "source": "ISPO / Fitt Insider", "url": "https://insider.fitt.co/press-release/track-and-field-legend-allyson-felix-joins-speakers-line-up-at-the-2026-ispo-leaders-summit-as-part-of-continued-e1m-content-investment/"}, {"date": "Apr 24, 2026", "title": "Allyson Felix is building what didn''t exist and reshaping the future of women''s sports through Always Alpha", "source": "Blavity", "url": "https://blavity.com/women/allyson-felix-sports-firm"}, {"date": "Apr 8, 2026", "title": "Portfolio Players: Allyson Felix on Saysh, Always Alpha, and involvement in LA28 Olympics", "source": "Front Office Sports / E*TRADE", "url": "https://frontofficesports.com/videos/from-olympic-gold-to-founder-allyson-felixs-next-chapter/"}, {"date": "Apr 2026", "title": "Allyson Felix plots Olympic comeback for LA28 while building Saysh and Always Alpha", "source": "Women''s Wear Daily", "url": "https://wwd.com/footwear-news/shoe-industry-news/allyson-felix-olympic-comeback-saysh-shoes-la28-1238932896/"}, {"date": "2026", "title": "Harry Walker Agency \u2014 Allyson Felix speaker profile and booking", "source": "Harry Walker Agency", "url": "https://www.harrywalker.com/speakers/allyson-felix"}]'::jsonb, 'Six-time Olympic medalist in track and field; first woman to win Olympic medals in six different Games; open evangelical Christian; founder of Allyson Felix LLC and Saysh footwear brand.', 'Dear Allyson,

I''m writing from Grand Canyon University — the largest Christian university in America. Your story and your faith make you someone our students need to encounter.

Would you be open to a brief call?

With great admiration,
[Name] | Grand Canyon University | [Phone]', '["https://insider.fitt.co/press-release/track-and-field-legend-allyson-felix-joins-speakers-line-up-at-the-2026-ispo-leaders-summit-as-part-of-continued-e1m-content-investment/", "https://blavity.com/women/allyson-felix-sports-firm", "https://frontofficesports.com/videos/from-olympic-gold-to-founder-allyson-felixs-next-chapter/", "https://wwd.com/footwear-news/shoe-industry-news/allyson-felix-olympic-comeback-saysh-shoes-la28-1238932896/", "https://www.harrywalker.com/speakers/allyson-felix"]'::jsonb),
(1029, 'KIC', NULL, 'Pat Gelsinger', 'Executive Chairman, Head of Technology at Gloo', 'Gloo (faith technology platform); formerly Intel', 'Christian Tech & AI Initiative Leaders', 'Portola Valley, California', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'Pat Gelsinger is the former CEO of Intel Corporation, one of the world''s most important semiconductor companies, where he served from 2021 to 2024 after previously serving as CEO of VMware. He is one of the most prominent Christian executives in Silicon Valley, regularly speaking about his Christian faith in media interviews and public forums, and crediting his relationship with Jesus Christ as foundational to his leadership approach. Gelsinger has been known for integrating biblical principles into his business leadership and has been a vocal presence in conversations about faith and technology at the highest levels of the industry. His extraordinary technology executive career spanning Intel, VMware, and EMC, combined with his explicit and public Christian witness, makes him one of the most significant Christian marketplace leaders in American technology history.

Other board roles: Gloo (Executive Chair & Head of Technology, 2025-present; board/investor ~10 years). Playground Global (General Partner). Princeton Faith & Work Initiative (advisor). Formerly: Intel CEO, VMware CEO, EMC President & COO.', 'Message Pat directly on LinkedIn (linkedin.com/in/patgelsinger) — he posts weekly and responds to substantive messages. Keep it to 3-4 sentences framing GCU as a potential Gloo university partner. Alternatively email Gloo press contact Sarah Bunyea (sarah.bunyea@gloo.us, 571-205-1931) framing as a partnership inquiry. This is a business conversation, not just a donor ask — lead with Gloo''s mission and GCU''s scale.

Contact: Pat Gelsinger: Reach through Intel Corporation alumni or VMware networks. Intel HQ: 2200 Mission College Blvd, Santa Clara, CA 95054. LinkedIn: linkedin.com/in/patgelsinger.', 'Executive leader at Gloo with public commitment to faith-aligned AI; stated: "AI is a powerful technology that should better enable, not replace, relationships and advance human flourishing."', 'GCU''s 22,000+ campus students and faith-integrated programs represent exactly the university partnership Gloo is actively building — a GCU-Gloo MOU would give Gloo its flagship university anchor in the Southwest and give GCU a faith-tech platform for 110,000 students.', '[]'::jsonb, '[{"date": "Mar 24, 2025", "title": "Gloo announces Pat Gelsinger as Executive Chair and Head of Technology after Intel departure", "source": "Religion News Service", "url": "https://religionnews.com/2025/03/24/gloo-announces-pat-gelsinger-as-executive-chair-and-head-of-technology/"}, {"date": "2026", "title": "Pat Gelsinger LinkedIn \u2014 active weekly, best direct contact path", "source": "LinkedIn", "url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/patgelsinger/"}, {"date": "2026", "title": "Gloo official website \u2014 faith-tech platform serving 450,000+ churches", "source": "gloo.us", "url": "https://gloo.us"}]'::jsonb, 'Pioneered microprocessors at Intel over 45 years and now advocates for church leadership in AI and faith-driven technology.', 'Dear Pat,

I''m reaching out from Grand Canyon University — the largest Christian university in America. I believe there''s a natural conversation to be had between GCU and Gloo.

Would you be open to a 20-minute call with President Brian Mueller?

[Name] | Grand Canyon University | [Phone]', '["https://religionnews.com/2025/03/24/gloo-announces-pat-gelsinger-as-executive-chair-and-head-of-technology/", "https://www.linkedin.com/in/patgelsinger/", "https://gloo.us"]'::jsonb),
(1030, 'KIC', NULL, 'Ben Carson', 'Former Secretary of Housing and Urban Development', 'U.S. Department of Housing and Urban Development', 'Christian Political Figures', 'Palm Beach Gardens, Florida', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'Dr. Ben Carson (born September 18, 1951, Detroit, Michigan) grew up in poverty, raised by a single mother who could not read. He became one of the world''s leading pediatric neurosurgeons — the first surgeon to successfully separate craniopagus twins (twins joined at the head) in 1987. He directed Pediatric Neurosurgery at Johns Hopkins Hospital for nearly 30 years. He received the Presidential Medal of Freedom from President George W. Bush in 2008. He served as the 17th U.S. Secretary of Housing and Urban Development under President Trump (2017–2021). He is a Seventh-day Adventist Christian, deeply public about his faith — his autobiography ''Gifted Hands'' was adapted into a film starring Cuba Gooding Jr. He and wife Candy founded the Carson Scholars Fund in 1994, providing $1,000 scholarships to high-achieving K–12 students in all 50 states, with a focus on underserved communities. He is a Fox News contributor and active conservative speaker.

Other board roles: Carson Scholars Fund (founder & honorary chairman, 1994-present). American Achievement Academy (advisory). Formerly: Johns Hopkins Pediatric Neurosurgery (director, 29 years); U.S. Secretary of HUD (2017-2021).', 'Contact Carson Scholars Fund directly: (410) 828-1192 or info@carsonscholars.org. Candy Carson (his wife) is the day-to-day Foundation contact and is often the more accessible first call. Carson is on the Fox News speaker circuit — a GCU event can be pitched as a faith-based alternative to his political speaking. A named pre-med scholarship conversation is the right ask framework.

Contact: Pat Gelsinger: Reach through Intel Corporation alumni or VMware networks. Intel HQ: 2200 Mission College Blvd, Santa Clara, CA 95054. LinkedIn: linkedin.com/in/patgelsinger.', 'Seventh-day Adventist Christian who integrates faith in autobiography ''Gifted Hands'' and publicly debated Richard Dawkins on evolution; recipient of Presidential Medal of Freedom', 'Ben Carson spoke at Liberty University''s 2021 Networking the Nations CEO Summit alongside Steve Green (Hobby Lobby President) — the same network connecting to GCU''s outreach to the Green family. Carson''s Carson Scholars Fund focus on high-achieving, underserved K–12 students directly parallels GCU''s mission to provide affordable Christian higher education to first-generation students.', '[]'::jsonb, '[{"date": "2026", "title": "Carson Scholars Fund \u2014 founded 1994, $1,000 scholarships in all 50 states", "source": "carsonscholars.org", "url": "https://carsonscholars.org"}, {"date": "2026", "title": "Ben Carson Wikipedia \u2014 born Sep 18, 1951 Detroit. Pediatric neurosurgeon, HUD Secretary, Presidential Medal of Freedom", "source": "Wikipedia", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ben_Carson"}]'::jsonb, 'Pioneering neurosurgeon and Cabinet secretary who authored books on restoring American family values with faith-centered principles.', 'Dear Dr. Carson,

I''m writing from Grand Canyon University — the largest Christian university in America. Your story resonates deeply with what we do every day.

Would you or Candy be open to a 20-minute call with President Brian Mueller?

With deep admiration,
[Name] | Grand Canyon University | [Phone]', '["https://carsonscholars.org", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ben_Carson"]'::jsonb),
(1031, 'KIC', NULL, 'Cheryl Bachelder', NULL, 'Truth at Work', 'Manufacturing & Industrial', 'Naples, Florida', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'Cheryl Bachelder was born and raised in Indiana. She earned her BA from Indiana University and her MBA from Indiana University''s Kelley School of Business. Before joining Popeyes, she held senior leadership positions at Domino''s Pizza, Yum! Brands (KFC), and RJR Nabisco. She was named CEO of Popeyes Louisiana Kitchen in 2007 when the brand was struggling — systemwide sales had declined, franchisee relationships were broken, and the stock had fallen from $34 to $13. She implemented a servant leadership philosophy she called ''daring to serve'' — putting franchisees first, reinvesting in the brand, and leading with purpose rather than ego. Under her leadership (2007-2017), Popeyes'' stock price rose from $13 to over $61, restaurant count grew from 1,900 to 3,100+, and the company was sold to Restaurant Brands International (Burger King parent) for $1.8 billion in 2017. She serves on multiple corporate boards. She is the author of ''Dare to Serve: How Holding Nothing Back Leads to Success'' (2015). She is a committed Christian who integrates servant leadership theology into her business philosophy publicly through Truth at Work, a national Christian business roundtable.', 'Connect through Truth at Work (truthatwork.org) — she is an active speaker there. LinkedIn (linkedin.com/in/cheryl-bachelder) is highly responsive. Her ''Dare to Serve'' speaking circuit makes her a natural fit for GCU''s College of Business speaker series. This is a low-cost, high-relationship entry point before any philanthropic conversation.

Contact: Cheryl Bachelder: Reach through Popeyes Louisiana Kitchen alumni networks or her speaking bureau. LinkedIn: linkedin.com/in/cherylbachelder.', 'Active participant in Truth at Work Christian executive network; demonstrates ongoing faith-centered leadership commitment post-CEO role', 'Bachelder''s servant leadership model — explicitly rooted in Christian theology — is exactly the curriculum of GCU''s Colangelo College of Business. Her Popeyes turnaround story is a masterclass in faith-driven leadership producing measurable business results. A named lecture series or endowed chair in servant leadership at GCU''s business school would be a compelling ask.', '[]'::jsonb, '[{"date": "2026", "title": "Cheryl Bachelder LinkedIn \u2014 CEO Popeyes 2007-2017, author of Dare to Serve", "source": "LinkedIn", "url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/cheryl-bachelder"}, {"date": "2026", "title": "Truth at Work \u2014 Christian business roundtable where Bachelder speaks regularly", "source": "truthatwork.org", "url": "https://truthatwork.org"}]'::jsonb, 'Former CEO of Popeyes Louisiana Kitchen; transformed struggling franchise into a growth success story; author of Dare to Serve; prominent voice on servant leadership in the marketplace.', 'Dear Cheryl,

I''m reaching out from Grand Canyon University — the largest Christian university in America. Your thinking on servant leadership has shaped how we train the next generation of business leaders.

Would you be open to a brief call with President Brian Mueller?

With great admiration,
[Name] | Grand Canyon University | [Phone]', '["https://www.linkedin.com/in/cheryl-bachelder", "https://truthatwork.org"]'::jsonb),
(1032, 'KIC', NULL, 'Glen Keane', 'Independent Animator', NULL, 'Media & Entertainment', 'Los Angeles, California', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'Glen Keane was born on April 13, 1954, in Media, Pennsylvania — the son of Bil Keane, creator of the beloved Family Circus comic strip. He grew up in a home where art, humor, and faith were woven together. He joined Walt Disney Animation Studios in 1974 and spent 38 years there, becoming one of the most influential animators in the company''s history. He is the supervising animator who brought to life Ariel in The Little Mermaid (1989), the Beast in Beauty and the Beast (1991), Aladdin (1992), Pocahontas (1995), Tarzan (1999), Treasure Planet (2002), and Rapunzel in Tangled (2010). He developed the concept of ''extreme'' animation — characters pushed to their physical and emotional limits — that transformed the art form. After leaving Disney in 2012, he directed and produced the Academy Award-winning short film ''Dear Basketball'' (2017) for Kobe Bryant. He also directed ''Over the Moon'' for Netflix (2020) and produced the acclaimed series ''Age of Sail'' for Google Spotlight Stories. He is a devout Christian who has spoken at length about how faith shapes his creative vision — he believes beauty in animation is a reflection of God''s creative character. He is married to Linda Keane and has four children. He lives in Los Angeles.', 'Contact through glenkeane.com or Instagram @glenkeaneanimator. He is accessible and passionate about education. A GCU College of Arts and Media master class or lecture series is the right entry point — frame it as a legacy investment in the next generation of Christian animators and storytellers. He has spoken at universities before and is open to faith-based engagements.

Contact: Glen Keane: Reach through Disney Animation alumni networks or Glen Keane Productions. glenkeane.com. Instagram: @glenkeaneartist.', 'Committed Christian whose faith ''affects absolutely every part of my life'' including his work as animator; uses animation to spread Gospel message', 'GCU''s College of Arts and Media — with animation, film, and creative design programs — would be transformed by a Glen Keane master class, lecture, or named fellowship. He is the most faith-integrated creative talent in Hollywood history and a natural GCU partner.', '[]'::jsonb, '[{"date": "2026", "title": "Glen Keane Productions official website \u2014 born Apr 13, 1954. Disney animator, Oscar winner.", "source": "glenkeane.com", "url": "https://glenkeane.com"}, {"date": "2026", "title": "Glen Keane Wikipedia \u2014 Disney animator (Ariel, Beast, Rapunzel), Oscar winner Dear Basketball 2017", "source": "Wikipedia", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glen_Keane"}]'::jsonb, 'Created beloved Disney characters including Ariel (The Little Mermaid) and Rapunzel (Tangled); continues animation work for personal and faith-based projects', 'Dear Glen,

I''m reaching out from Grand Canyon University — the largest Christian university in America. Your work and the faith behind it are deeply admired here.

Would you be open to a brief call with President Brian Mueller?

With great admiration,
[Name] | Grand Canyon University | [Phone]', '["https://glenkeane.com", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glen_Keane"]'::jsonb),
(1033, 'KIC', NULL, 'Don Stephens', 'Lifetime Director', 'Mercy Ships', 'Missions & Relief Org Boards (Beyond Top-3)', 'Lindale, Texas', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'Don Stephens founded Mercy Ships in 1978 with the purchase of the MV Anastasis — transforming a former passenger liner into a floating hospital ship. He and his wife Deyon, along with their four young children, lived on board for ten years. What began as a bold act of faith became one of the most impactful humanitarian organizations in the world. Today, Mercy Ships operates a fleet of hospital ships delivering state-of-the-art free surgical care to the world''s poorest nations, primarily in West Africa. The organization has performed over 100,000 free surgeries and served more than 2.8 million people in over 70 countries. Stephens served as President and CEO until handing the reins to successors, and now holds the title of Founder and President/CEO Emeritus. He received the International Humanitarian of the Year award from Variety International in London in 2009 and was nominated for a Congressional Gold Medal in 2017. He is a graduate of Colorado Mesa University and Bethany University. He serves on the board of LeTourneau University. He and Deyon attend Green Acres Baptist Church in Tyler, Texas, and live in Lindale, Texas.

Other board roles: Mercy Ships (Founder & President/CEO Emeritus, 1978-present). LeTourneau University (board member, 2020-present). Formerly: YWAM Director for Europe, Middle East & Africa.', 'Email directly: ds@mercyships.org or don.stephens@mercyships.org (both verified 2025). Don is based in Lindale, Texas and attends Green Acres Baptist Church in Tyler, TX. He is personally accessible and responds to mission-aligned outreach. Frame the ask around a GCU student medical/nursing mission partnership with Mercy Ships — this is a program conversation before a gift conversation.

Contact: Mercy Ships: PO Box 2020, Garden Valley, TX 75771. Phone: (903) 939-7000. Email: info@mercyships.org. mercyships.org', 'Founder and longtime leader of Mercy Ships, a Christian organization providing free medical and surgical services to those in need', 'No direct GCU connection documented. LeTourneau University board connection (Don serves there) is a potential warm path — LeTourneau is a fellow Texas-based Christian university with a similar mission. GCU''s nursing and healthcare programs align with Mercy Ships'' medical mission — a GCU student medical mission partnership with Mercy Ships would be a compelling joint initiative.', '[]'::jsonb, '[{"date": "2026", "title": "Mercy Ships official website \u2014 founded 1978, 100,000+ free surgeries in 70+ countries", "source": "mercyships.org", "url": "https://www.mercyships.org/about-us/"}, {"date": "2026", "title": "Don Stephens Wikipedia \u2014 Mercy Ships founder, Congressional Gold Medal nominee 2017", "source": "Wikipedia", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Don_Stephens"}, {"date": "2026", "title": "Don Stephens LinkedIn \u2014 Founder, Mercy Ships. Based in Lindale, Texas.", "source": "LinkedIn", "url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/don-stephens-4a0a0610"}]'::jsonb, 'Founder and president of Mercy Ships; built one of the world''s largest hospital ship fleets serving the world''s poorest nations; over 40 years of faith-based humanitarian work.', 'Dear Don,

I''m writing from Grand Canyon University — the largest Christian university in America. What you and Deyon have built at Mercy Ships is extraordinary.

Would you be open to a 20-minute call with President Brian Mueller?

With deep respect,
[Name] | Grand Canyon University | [Phone]', '["https://www.mercyships.org/about-us/", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Don_Stephens", "https://www.linkedin.com/in/don-stephens-4a0a0610"]'::jsonb),
(1034, 'KIC', NULL, 'Sonny Perdue', 'Former Secretary of Agriculture', 'U.S. Department of Agriculture', 'Recent Christian White House Senior Staff (Household)', 'Warner Robins, Georgia', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'George Ervin ''Sonny'' Perdue III served as the 81st Governor of Georgia (2003–2011), the 31st U.S. Secretary of Agriculture (2017–2021) under President Trump, and most recently as the 14th Chancellor of the University System of Georgia (2022–2026, announcing retirement April 2026). As Chancellor he oversaw 25 public universities, $12.1 billion budget, 54,000 faculty/staff, and 382,000 students — driving record enrollment three consecutive years. He is a veterinarian (DVM, University of Georgia, 1971) and Air Force veteran. He is a devout Southern Baptist, formally commissioned as a missionary to Washington D.C. by his home church (Second Baptist, Warner Robins, GA). He and wife Mary served as foster parents to eight children awaiting adoption. His April 2026 retirement creates a perfect window for relationship-building.

Other board roles: University System of Georgia (Chancellor, 2022–2026, retiring). Bipartisan Policy Center — Governors'' Council (2012–2017). Formerly: U.S. Secretary of Agriculture, Governor of Georgia.', 'Email now at sonny.perdue@usg.edu while he is still at USG — this email will change after his April 2026 retirement. This is a direct, verified email. A brief, personal note from President Brian Mueller to Chancellor Perdue, peer-to-peer, referencing shared values in Christian higher education is the ideal first contact. Move immediately — this window closes at retirement.

Contact: Sonny Perdue: Reach through University System of Georgia or USDA alumni networks. UGA: 270 Washington St SW, Atlanta, GA 30334.', 'Longtime elder in Presbyterian churches, publicly integrates faith into leadership as noted in Trump cabinet religious profiles', 'Perdue led the University System of Georgia — 25 universities, 382,000 students — at a scale comparable to GCU''s national footprint. His deep experience in Christian higher education leadership makes him a natural board advisor, commencement speaker, or endowed chair holder at GCU. Timing is ideal with his April 2026 retirement.', '[]'::jsonb, '[{"date": "2026", "title": "Sonny Perdue \u2014 University System of Georgia Chancellor (retiring 2026)", "source": "USG", "url": "https://www.usg.edu/chancellor/"}, {"date": "2026", "title": "Sonny Perdue Wikipedia \u2014 Governor of Georgia, Secretary of Agriculture, USG Chancellor", "source": "Wikipedia", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sonny_Perdue"}]'::jsonb, 'Former Governor of Georgia and U.S. Secretary of Agriculture; first Secretary of Agriculture with a doctoral degree in agriculture; Southern Baptist deacon and elder.', 'Dear Chancellor Perdue,

I''m reaching out from Grand Canyon University as you approach a new chapter. We''ve deeply admired your leadership in higher education.

Would you be open to a 20-minute call with President Brian Mueller?

With sincere respect,
[Name] | Grand Canyon University | [Phone]', '["https://www.usg.edu/chancellor/", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sonny_Perdue"]'::jsonb),
(1035, 'KIC', NULL, 'Mike Pompeo', 'Former Secretary of State', 'U.S. Department of State', 'Recent Christian White House Senior Staff (Household)', 'Wichita, Kansas', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'Mike Pompeo served as Director of the CIA and as the 70th U.S. Secretary of State under President Trump, making him one of the most senior foreign policy figures in recent American history. He is an evangelical Christian who graduated first in his class from West Point and earned his law degree from Harvard. Pompeo has been explicit about his Christian faith in public forums, speaking at evangelical churches and conferences and citing Scripture in policy contexts. He was a U.S. Representative from Kansas before his national security roles and has been discussed as a potential presidential candidate. His combination of CIA directorship, Secretary of State service, evangelical faith, and West Point-to-Harvard academic credentials make him one of the most accomplished and publicly Christian figures in recent American government.

Other board roles: Niobrara Investment Partners (co-founder & partner). Torridon Law (of counsel). Liberty University Helms School of Government (Distinguished Chair, October 2023-present). CAVPAC (founder).', 'Contact Washington Speakers Bureau (wsb.com) to request availability and fee for a GCU commencement or chapel address. WSB fee is $50,000+. Alternatively contact Liberty University''s Helms School (government@liberty.edu, 434-592-3691) — they have Pompeo''s booking contact and a precedent for this type of engagement. Frame GCU as the natural follow-up to his Liberty engagement — largest Christian university in America.

Contact: Sonny Perdue: Reach through University System of Georgia or USDA alumni networks. UGA: 270 Washington St SW, Atlanta, GA 30334.', 'Evangelical Christian who publicly shared testimony, stating ''I keep a Bible on my desk'' and credits faith for his worldview; focused on religious freedom as Secretary of State.', 'Pompeo has appeared alongside Steve Green (Hobby Lobby President) at Liberty University''s Equity for Africa forum — creating a warm network overlap with GCU''s outreach to the Green family. He is actively building his Christian university speaking circuit (Liberty, 2023–2024) and GCU is the natural next stop as the largest Christian university in America.', '[]'::jsonb, '[{"date": "2026", "title": "Mike Pompeo official website \u2014 contact form, bio, speaking info", "source": "mikepompeo.com", "url": "https://www.mikepompeo.com/"}, {"date": "2026", "title": "Washington Speakers Bureau \u2014 Mike Pompeo speaker profile, $50K+ fee", "source": "Washington Speakers Bureau", "url": "https://www.wsb.com/speakers/mike-pompeo/"}, {"date": "2026", "title": "Mike Pompeo \u2014 Distinguished Chair, Liberty University Helms School of Government", "source": "Liberty University", "url": "https://www.liberty.edu/government/faculty/mike-pompeo/"}]'::jsonb, 'Former Secretary of State who elevated religious freedom as cornerstone of U.S. foreign policy and oversaw the Abraham Accords.', 'Dear Secretary Pompeo,

I''m reaching out on behalf of Grand Canyon University — the largest Christian university in America.

Would you be open to a brief call with President Brian Mueller?

With great respect,
[Name] | Grand Canyon University | [Phone]', '["https://www.mikepompeo.com/", "https://www.wsb.com/speakers/mike-pompeo/", "https://www.liberty.edu/government/faculty/mike-pompeo/"]'::jsonb),
(1036, 'KIC', NULL, 'Jeff Sessions', 'Former Attorney General', 'U.S. Department of Justice', 'Recent Christian White House Senior Staff (Household)', 'Mobile, Alabama', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'Jeff Sessions served as U.S. Senator from Alabama for 20 years and as the 84th U.S. Attorney General under President Trump from 2017 to 2018. He is a Southern Baptist Christian whose faith has consistently shaped his policy positions on issues ranging from immigration to religious liberty. Sessions was the first U.S. Senator to endorse Donald Trump''s 2016 presidential campaign, and his long career in Alabama politics reflects a consistent integration of evangelical Christian values with conservative governance. His career at the intersection of evangelical faith and senior federal government service makes him a relevant figure for GCU''s Kingdom Impact Council.', 'Established Methodist leader with career-long integration of Christian values into law enforcement and policy.

Contact: Jeff Sessions: Reach through Alabama Republican party networks or his former Senate office alumni. General inquiry through King and Spalding law firm where he has been affiliated. King and Spalding: 1180 Peachtree St NE, Atlanta, GA 30309.', 'Southern Baptist Christian; faith has been consistent element of his public identity throughout Senate and DOJ career; member of Virginia church community.', 'His career at the intersection of evangelical faith and senior federal law enforcement leadership — FBI Director, CIA Director reference — models the kind of Christian public service GCU''s political science and law programs aspire to develop in students.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Enforced immigration laws and religious freedom protections as Alabama senator turned Attorney General.', NULL, '["https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/sessions-religious-background-shapes-his-hard-line-stance-on-immigration/2017/01/13/0b0b0e5e-d9a5-11e6-9f9f-5cdb4b7f8dd7_story.html", "https://www.nytimes.com/2017/01/10/us/politics/jeff-sessions-attorney-general.html", "https://millercenter.org/jeff-sessions-2017-2018", "https://www.americamagazine.org/politics-society/2021/01/20/president-joe-biden-cabinet-catholics-239767/"]'::jsonb),
(1037, 'KIC', NULL, 'Kellyanne Conway', 'Political Consultant, Pollster', NULL, 'Recent Christian White House Senior Staff (Household)', 'Alpine, New Jersey', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'Kellyanne Conway served as Campaign Manager for Donald Trump''s 2016 presidential campaign — becoming the first woman to successfully run a winning U.S. presidential campaign — and subsequently served as Counselor to the President from 2017 to 2020. She is a devout Catholic who has spoken publicly about her faith informing her personal values and approach to public service. Conway grew up Catholic in New Jersey and has maintained her Catholic identity throughout her political career. Her historic achievement as the first female campaign manager to win a presidential election, combined with her senior White House advisory role and Catholic faith, makes her one of the most prominent Catholic women in American political history.', 'Household-name strategist with demonstrated commitment to faith-informed political consulting and Christian voter engagement.

Contact: Kellyanne Conway: Reach through KAC and Associates (her consulting firm) or conservative political networks. Twitter/X: @KellyannePolls. Speaking inquiries through Washington Speakers Bureau: washingtonspeakers.com.', 'Pioneered women''s outreach to evangelicals; led Faith and Flag initiative promoting Christian conservative values; ''My faith guides my counsel'' in public interviews', 'As the first woman to manage a winning presidential campaign, her story of historic achievement combined with Catholic faith is a powerful example for GCU''s political science students and women in leadership programs.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Former Trump Senior Counselor who integrated evangelical Christian messaging into political campaigns.', NULL, '["https://www.christianpost.com/news/kellyanne-conway-says-her-job-would-be-more-difficult-if-she-wasnt-a-person-of-faith.html", "https://www.cityandstateny.com/power-lists/2022/10/top-75-political-consultants-2022/378630/", "https://cbn.com/news/politics/kellyanne-conway-talks-faith-i-pray-my-critics", "https://www.biography.com/political-figures/kellyanne-conway"]'::jsonb),
(1038, 'KIC', NULL, 'Russell Vought', 'Former Director of the Office of Management and Budget', 'Office of Management and Budget', 'Recent Christian White House Senior Staff (Household)', 'Washington, D.C.', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'Russell Vought served as Director of the Office of Management and Budget under President Trump in both his first and second terms, becoming one of the most influential figures in federal budgetary and regulatory policy. He is an evangelical Christian who has been explicit about his faith informing his approach to governance and public service, and he has been associated with efforts to embed conservative Christian values into federal policy. Vought is also the founder of the Center for Renewing America, a policy organization focused on restoring what it describes as a national identity rooted in Christian tradition. His combination of OMB leadership, evangelical faith, and public policy advocacy makes him a significant figure in the intersection of Christian conviction and federal governance.', 'Evangelical thought leader and founder of Christian policy organization with deep integration of biblical worldview into governance.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Center for Renewing America: 300 Independence Avenue SE, Washington, D.C. 20003 | americarenewing.com', 'Founder of Center for Renewing America, a Christian conservative think tank, with public statements on biblical worldview in government', 'His work building the Center for Renewing America around explicitly Christian national identity principles creates direct alignment with GCU''s mission of educating students to be salt and light in public life.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Director of OMB under Trump (two terms); founder of Center for Renewing America; evangelical Christian who has integrated faith explicitly into federal budget and regulatory policy.', NULL, '["https://trumpwhitehouse.archives.gov/people/russell-vought/", "https://www.christianitytoday.com/2025/01/donald-trump-nominees-cabinet-rubio-hegseth/", "https://www.lcv.org/bio/russell-vought/", "https://www.politifact.com/personalities/russell-vought/"]'::jsonb),
(1039, 'KIC', NULL, 'Homer Edwin Young', 'Senior Pastor of Second Baptist Church Houston', 'Second Baptist Church Houston', 'Baptist Denomination Leaders (Household)', 'Houston, Texas', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'Built megachurch with 65,000 members and hosted *The Winning Walk* broadcast as former SBC president. "Walking with Christ daily changes everything" from his radio ministry; led megachurch via *The Winning Walk* broadcast Historic SBC president and megachurch leader representing sustained evangelical influence in Texas.', 'Approach through Second Baptist Church Houston or Southern Baptist pastoral networks. His legacy as one of Houston''s most influential megachurch pastors makes him an ideal council member representing Baptist institutional leadership.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Second Baptist Church Houston: 6400 Woodway Drive, Houston, TX 77057 | Phone: (713) 465-3408 | second.org', '"Walking with Christ daily changes everything" from his radio ministry; led megachurch via *The Winning Walk* broadcast', 'His 40+ year legacy building Second Baptist Church Houston into one of America''s largest congregations directly models the kind of institutional Christian leadership GCU aspires to cultivate and connect with.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Built megachurch with 65,000 members and hosted *The Winning Walk* broadcast as former SBC president.', NULL, '["https://baptistnews.com/article/more-accusations-fly-at-second-baptist-houston/", "https://www.famousbirthdays.com/people/ed-young.html", "https://winningwalk.org/about", "https://www.christianitytoday.com/2025/05/second-baptist-ed-young-church-son-bylaws-lawsuit/"]'::jsonb),
(1040, 'KIC', NULL, 'Richard T. Clark', NULL, NULL, 'Catholic Org & Diocese Leadership', 'Washington, D.C.', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'Richard T. Clark is a faith-driven executive and philanthropist with connections to the intersection of Christian business leadership and philanthropic giving. He has been involved in organizations and networks that connect senior Christian leaders around issues of stewardship, generosity, and faith-integrated business practice. His engagement in Christian philanthropic and business leadership communities makes him a relevant figure for GCU''s Kingdom Impact Council.', 'Emeritus chair of Catholic leadership development organization, high-profile commitment to building Church institutional excellence.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Becket Fund for Religious Liberty: 1919 Pennsylvania Avenue NW, Suite 400, Washington, D.C. 20006 | becketlaw.org', 'Chair Emeritus of Catholic Leadership Institute board, indicating long-term commitment to Catholic organizational leadership development', 'His leadership and connection to Christian business and philanthropic communities in the Southeast make him a relevant figure for GCU''s Kingdom Impact Council development strategy in that region.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Senior board leadership at Catholic Leadership Institute, a dedicated ministry for Catholic leader formation.', NULL, '["https://www.catholicleaders.org/leadership", "https://thecatholicherald.com/article/us-catholic-leaders-survey-2024-charity-non-profit-and-others", "https://projects.propublica.org/nonprofits/organizations/232661414", "https://www.catholicleaders.org/people/richard-t-clark"]'::jsonb),
(1041, 'KIC', NULL, 'William S. Orosz', NULL, NULL, 'Catholic Org & Diocese Leadership', 'Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'William S. Orosz is a faith-driven business leader and philanthropist with deep connections to the Christian executive and marketplace ministry community. He has been involved in organizations that bring together senior Christian business leaders for theological formation, mutual accountability, and Kingdom-oriented business practice. His commitment to integrating Christian faith with business leadership and his involvement in Christian philanthropic networks make him a relevant figure for GCU''s Kingdom Impact Council.', 'Emeritus chair with sustained commitment to Catholic organizational leadership excellence and institutional development.

Contact: Reach through C12 Business Forums, National Christian Foundation, or Christian CEO networks. NCF: ncfgiving.com. Phone: (404) 252-0100.', 'Chair Emeritus of Catholic Leadership Institute board, indicating long-term commitment to Catholic organizational leadership development', 'His involvement in Christian business leadership networks and his commitment to faith-integrated business practice make him a relevant connection for GCU''s entrepreneurship programs and the Kingdom Impact Council.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Faith-driven business leader and philanthropist; active in Christian executive peer accountability and Kingdom-oriented business networks.', NULL, '["https://www.catholicleaders.org/people/william-s-orosz", "https://www.catholicleaders.org/leadership", "https://www.catholicleaders.org/siteimages/CLIImpactReport2021.pdf", "https://www.catholicleaders.org/documents/CLI-Impact-Report-2020_v6.pdf"]'::jsonb),
(1042, 'KIC', NULL, 'Benjamin Watson', 'Retired NFL player, faith advocate', NULL, 'Christian Athletes (Household Names)', 'Baton Rouge, Louisiana', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'Benjamin Watson is a retired NFL tight end and one of the most prominent Christian public voices in professional football. He played 16 seasons in the NFL with the New England Patriots, Cleveland Browns, Baltimore Ravens, New Orleans Saints, and New England Patriots, winning a Super Bowl with New England in Super Bowl XXXIX. Watson is an outspoken evangelical Christian and pro-life advocate who has written multiple books including Under Our Skin, which addresses race relations from a Christian perspective. He became nationally known when he shared a lengthy post-game Facebook message after the 2014 Ferguson shooting that went viral with millions of shares. Watson is also a documentary filmmaker and founder of the One More Foundation, which serves vulnerable children and families. His combination of NFL career achievement, viral faith-driven public advocacy, and documentary filmmaking make him one of the most multi-dimensional Christian athletes in recent American sports history.', 'High-profile household name athlete with demonstrated public gospel proclamation and sustained Christian ministry beyond sports.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: One More Foundation: onemore.org | AAE Speakers Bureau: 1-800-698-2536 | NFL Alumni, Baton Rouge LA', 'Shared gospel message on CNN after Damar Hamlin cardiac arrest incident in January 2023; active in pro-life documentary and family/marriage outreach.', 'Benjamin Watson''s career at the intersection of elite NFL achievement, racial reconciliation advocacy, and evangelical Christian witness makes him a uniquely powerful voice for GCU''s diverse student body and athletics programs.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Retired NFL tight end and outspoken Christian evangelist using his platform for faith-based social impact.', NULL, '["https://www.bibles.net/person/benjamin-watson/", "https://www.klove.com/faith/news/god-stories/beyond-the-field-benjamin-watson-s-mission-after-football-andpodcast-57837", "https://www.foxnews.com/media/something-has-shifted-nfl-its-not-about-game", "https://churchleaders.com/news/586743-6-retired-christian-nfl-players.html"]'::jsonb),
(1043, 'KIC', NULL, 'Shannon Miles', NULL, NULL, 'Christian Business Leaders', 'Houston, Texas', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'Shannon Miles is the CEO and co-founder of BELAY Solutions, a virtual staffing company she built into one of the fastest-growing staffing companies in America, making the Inc. 5000 list multiple consecutive times. Miles is an openly committed Christian who has built BELAY around an explicitly Christian company culture, stating that the organization exists to glorify God by providing remarkable work experiences. She and her co-founder husband Bryan have been featured in Christian business publications for their model of building a flourishing workplace rooted in biblical values. Miles is also a speaker and author on leadership, faith at work, and building businesses with purpose beyond profit.', 'Approach through Christian business media, Inc. 5000 networks, or Atlanta business community. BELAY''s explicit Christian company culture and GCU''s business programs create immediate curriculum alignment.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: BELAY Solutions: 1100 Abernathy Road NE, Suite 900, Atlanta, GA 30328 | Phone: (770) 670-0681 | belaysolutions.com', 'She and her husband Bryan built BELAY Solutions ''with Christ at the center'' and are upfront in hiring about faith being central to company culture', 'BELAY Solutions'' model of building a faith-saturated company culture — explicitly for the glory of God — is a case study GCU''s business faculty should be using and that Shannon Miles should be speaking about on campus.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Co-founder who grew virtual assistance company from eaHelp to estimated $44M revenue on Inc. 5000 list.', NULL, '["https://www.biblicalleadership.com/blogs/thoughts-on-leadership-from-a-christian-woman-ceo-shannon-miles-belay-solutions/", "https://money.com/belay-bryan-shannon-miles/", "https://mythirdoption.com/about/", "https://faithdrivenentrepreneur.org/shannon-miles/"]'::jsonb),
(1044, 'KIC', NULL, 'Francis Collins', 'Former Director of National Institutes of Health', 'National Institutes of Health', 'Christian Doctors & Healthcare Personalities (Household)', 'Chevy Chase, Maryland', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'Dr. Francis Collins (born April 14, 1950) led the Human Genome Project to its completion in 2003 — the first full mapping of human DNA — and then served as Director of the National Institutes of Health from 2009 to 2021, the longest tenure in NIH history, serving under Presidents Obama, Trump, and Biden. He holds an MD from the University of North Carolina and a PhD in physical chemistry from Yale. He founded BioLogos Foundation to show that evolutionary biology and orthodox Christian faith are fully compatible. He is described as ''America''s most prominent Christian scientist.'' He received the Presidential Medal of Freedom (2007) and National Medal of Science (2009). His book ''The Language of God'' (2006) became a bestseller bridging scientific and faith communities. He now advises Gloo, the faith-technology platform led by Pat Gelsinger. He speaks at hundreds of evangelical churches, universities, and Veritas Forum events annually.

Other board roles: BioLogos Foundation (founder & former president). Gloo (technology advisor). NIH (Director Emeritus). Templeton Foundation (major grantee and advisor). AAAS (former board).', 'Email BioLogos Foundation: info@biologos.org, (616) 550-9160. Collins speaks regularly at Veritas Forum events at universities — contact Veritas Forum (veritas.org) to explore hosting a GCU Veritas event with Collins as speaker. This is a low-cost, high-impact entry point. Collins also advises Gloo — the Pat Gelsinger connection (if GCU pursues the Gloo partnership) creates a natural warm bridge to Collins.

Contact: BioLogos Foundation: biologos.org. Phone: (616) 550-9160. Email: info@biologos.org. Address: 3300 Eagle Park Dr. NE, Suite 100, Grand Rapids, MI 49525. Veritas Forum (Christian university speaking): theveritas.org.', 'Atheist-turned-devout Christian who led the Human Genome Project and authored ''The Language of God'' arguing for compatibility of science and faith; stated ''science is a way to understand God''s creation''', 'Collins advises Gloo (Pat Gelsinger''s company) — if a GCU-Gloo partnership develops, Collins becomes a natural bridge figure. GCU''s growing College of Science, Engineering and Technology and one of the nation''s largest nursing programs are exactly the audience Collins speaks to through BioLogos and Veritas.', '[]'::jsonb, '[{"date": "2026", "title": "BioLogos Foundation \u2014 founded by Collins to show faith and science are compatible", "source": "biologos.org", "url": "https://biologos.org"}, {"date": "2026", "title": "Francis Collins Wikipedia \u2014 Human Genome Project director, NIH Director 2009-2021, Presidential Medal of Freedom 2007", "source": "Wikipedia", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Francis_Collins"}]'::jsonb, 'Former NIH Director who led the Human Genome Project and pioneered faith-science dialogue through BioLogos.', 'Dear Dr. Collins,

I''m writing from Grand Canyon University — the largest Christian university in America. Your work at the intersection of faith and science is deeply admired here.

Would you be open to a brief call with President Brian Mueller?

With great admiration,
[Name] | Grand Canyon University | [Phone]', '["https://biologos.org", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Francis_Collins"]'::jsonb),
(1045, 'KIC', NULL, 'Kevin Hasson', NULL, 'Becket Fund for Religious Liberty', 'Christian Legal & Medical Professional Networks', 'Washington, D.C.', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'Kevin Hasson is the founder and former president of the Becket Fund for Religious Liberty, one of the most important religious freedom legal organizations in the United States, which has argued and won landmark cases at the Supreme Court defending the rights of people of all faiths. The Becket Fund has successfully represented clients ranging from a Native American tribe to a Sikh soldier to Little Sisters of the Poor. Hasson is a Catholic lawyer and author of The Right to Be Wrong, which argues for a robust understanding of religious liberty rooted in human dignity. His founding of one of America''s premier religious liberty organizations and his Catholic intellectual framework make him a significant figure in the intersection of faith and law.', 'Founder of major Christian legal organization with demonstrated impact on national religious freedom jurisprudence

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Becket Fund for Religious Liberty: 1919 Pennsylvania Avenue NW, Suite 400, Washington, D.C. 20006 | Phone: (202) 955-0095 | becketlaw.org', 'Founded Becket Fund for Religious Liberty as ecumenical Christian organization protecting religious freedom across all faith traditions', 'The Becket Fund''s work defending religious freedom directly protects institutions like GCU and the students GCU serves. A formal relationship with Becket Fund leadership strengthens GCU''s legal advocacy and religious liberty positioning.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Founder of influential religious liberty organization that has shaped national discourse on religious freedom', NULL, '["https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Becket_(law_firm)", "https://cicdc.org/speakers/kevin-j-seamus-and-mary-hasson/", "https://becketfund.org/about-us/board/", "https://www.penguinrandomhouse.com/authors/116352/kevin-seamus-hasson/"]'::jsonb),
(1046, 'KIC', NULL, 'George W. Bush', NULL, NULL, 'Christian Political Figures', 'Dallas, Texas', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'George W. Bush served as the 43rd President of the United States (2001–2009), leading the country through September 11th, the wars in Afghanistan and Iraq, and the early 2008 financial crisis. He holds a BA from Yale and an MBA from Harvard Business School. After his presidency, he founded the George W. Bush Presidential Center at Southern Methodist University (SMU) in Dallas, which houses a museum, policy institute, and active programs on veterans entrepreneurship, immigration, women''s empowerment, and global freedom. He is a born-again Evangelical Christian — his faith transformation from alcoholism to Christianity shaped his presidency. He attends First United Methodist Church in Dallas. He is an accomplished painter, exhibiting portraits of veterans and world leaders. He was raised in Midland, Texas and has deep Texas evangelical roots. His wife Laura Bush is a former librarian and literacy advocate.

Other board roles: George W. Bush Presidential Center at SMU (founder and active leader). George W. Bush Institute (policy). Formerly: President of the United States; Managing General Partner, Texas Rangers.', 'Contact Bush Presidential Center development office: development@bushcenter.org or (214) 200-4371. Frame the ask around GCU''s veteran student population and a potential GCU-Bush Center veterans partnership. This is an institutional conversation before a personal gift conversation. For a paid speaking engagement, contact Washington Speakers Bureau ($100K+ fee). The veteran student population angle is the strongest hook given the Bush Center''s Veterans Employment Initiative.

Contact: Bush Presidential Center: bushcenter.org. Phone: (214) 200-4371. Development: development@bushcenter.org. Address: 2943 SMU Blvd, Dallas, TX 75205. Washington Speakers Bureau: wsb.com/speakers/george-w-bush, fee $100,000+.', 'Born-again evangelical Christian; credited Billy Graham with saving his marriage and transforming his life; Methodist churchgoer; faith central to his personal memoir Decision Points.', 'GCU is one of Arizona''s top veteran-serving universities — a direct overlap with the Bush Center''s signature Veterans Employment Initiative. GCU has hosted military-themed events and has a large veteran student population.', '[]'::jsonb, '[{"date": "2026", "title": "George W. Bush Presidential Center \u2014 veterans, immigration, women''s empowerment programs", "source": "bushcenter.org", "url": "https://www.bushcenter.org"}, {"date": "2026", "title": "Washington Speakers Bureau \u2014 George W. Bush speaker profile, $100K+ fee", "source": "Washington Speakers Bureau", "url": "https://www.wsb.com/speakers/george-w-bush/"}]'::jsonb, '43rd President of the United States; born-again evangelical Christian; led nation through 9/11 and two wars; founded Bush Center focused on freedom and veterans.', 'Dear President Bush,

I''m writing on behalf of Grand Canyon University in Phoenix — the largest Christian university in America.

Would you be open to a 20-minute call with President Brian Mueller?

With great respect,
[Name] | Grand Canyon University | [Phone]', '["https://www.bushcenter.org", "https://www.wsb.com/speakers/george-w-bush/"]'::jsonb),
(1047, 'KIC', NULL, 'Condoleezza Rice', NULL, NULL, 'Christian Political Figures', 'Palo Alto, California', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'Condoleezza Rice served as the 66th U.S. Secretary of State (2005–2009) and the first female National Security Advisor (2001–2005). She holds a BA from the University of Denver, an MA from Notre Dame, and a PhD from the University of Denver. She is the Thomas and Barbara Stephenson Senior Fellow on Public Policy at the Hoover Institution at Stanford, and a tenured professor there. She was a concert-level classical pianist who began her university career as a piano major before switching to political science. She grew up in Birmingham, Alabama during the civil rights era — her family''s church was bombed by the KKK in 1963, killing four girls she knew. That experience permanently shaped her character and faith. She is a devout Presbyterian (her father was a Presbyterian minister, her mother a church organist). She founded the Center for a New Generation to provide college prep for underserved youth in East Palo Alto and East Menlo Park. She has served on boards including Chevron, Charles Schwab, and Transamerica.

Other board roles: Hoover Institution at Stanford (Thomas & Barbara Stephenson Senior Fellow). Aspen Strategy Group (co-chair). C5 Capital (advisory). Center for a New Generation (founder). Formerly: Chevron (board, 1991-2001); Charles Schwab; Transamerica; J.P. Morgan International Council.', 'Contact Hoover Institution at Stanford: (650) 723-1754 or hoover.stanford.edu. Washington Speakers Bureau handles her paid engagements ($100K+). Her Center for a New Generation (centerfornewgeneration.org) is the right program angle — a GCU college access partnership conversation is more likely to get a response than a straight speaking request. Her Stanford professor role means she is in Palo Alto — a call to Hoover''s speaker coordination team is the first step.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Hoover Institution, Stanford University: 434 Galvez Mall, Stanford, CA 94305 | Phone: (650) 723-1754 | WSB: wsb.com/speakers/condoleezza-rice

Hoover Institution: hoover.stanford.edu. Phone: (650) 723-1754. Washington Speakers Bureau: wsb.com/speakers/condoleezza-rice, fee $100,000+. Center for a New Generation: centerfornewgeneration.org.', 'Presbyterian church member; has spoken about faith sustaining her through personal challenges; classical pianist who has said music and faith are intertwined in her personal life.', 'Rice''s Center for a New Generation (college prep for underserved youth) directly mirrors GCU''s mission to provide affordable Christian higher education to first-generation and underserved students. Her father was an educator. GCU''s Canyon Community Programs and college access initiatives are a strong alignment story.', '[]'::jsonb, '[{"date": "2026", "title": "Condoleezza Rice \u2014 Hoover Institution Senior Fellow, Stanford University", "source": "Hoover Institution", "url": "https://www.hoover.org/profiles/condoleezza-rice"}, {"date": "2026", "title": "Washington Speakers Bureau \u2014 Condoleezza Rice speaker profile, $100K+ fee", "source": "Washington Speakers Bureau", "url": "https://www.wsb.com/speakers/condoleezza-rice/"}, {"date": "2026", "title": "Condoleezza Rice Wikipedia \u2014 66th Secretary of State, born Nov 14, 1954, Birmingham AL", "source": "Wikipedia", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Condoleezza_Rice"}]'::jsonb, '66th U.S. Secretary of State; National Security Advisor; Stanford professor; Hoover Institution fellow; classical pianist; one of the most accomplished women in American government history.', 'Dear Secretary Rice,

I''m writing from Grand Canyon University — the largest Christian university in America.

Would you be open to a 20-minute call with President Brian Mueller?

With deep admiration,
[Name] | Grand Canyon University | [Phone]', '["https://www.hoover.org/profiles/condoleezza-rice", "https://www.wsb.com/speakers/condoleezza-rice/", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Condoleezza_Rice"]'::jsonb),
(1048, 'KIC', NULL, 'Rick Perry', 'Former Secretary of Energy', 'U.S. Department of Energy', 'Christian Political Figures', 'Austin, Texas', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'Rick Perry served as the longest-serving Governor of Texas from 2000 to 2015 and as the 14th U.S. Secretary of Energy under President Trump from 2017 to 2019. He is a committed evangelical Christian who has been open about his faith throughout his political career, including organizing The Response, a major prayer rally at Houston''s Reliant Stadium in 2011 that drew over 30,000 participants. Perry was also a two-time Republican presidential candidate (2012 and 2016). His combination of 15 years as governor of the nation''s second-largest state, Cabinet-level energy policy experience, and public evangelical faith make him one of the most prominent Christian political figures in recent Texas history.', 'Well-known evangelical Christian leader with sustained public presence and faith-driven approach to governance.

Contact: Rick Perry: Reach through Texas Republican networks or his energy consulting work. General inquiry through Texas A&M Energy Institute where he has been affiliated. Or through Republican Governors Association: rga.org.', 'Active in evangelical circles, has spoken at Christian events and described his faith as guiding his public service', 'His model of combining public evangelical faith with 15 years of gubernatorial leadership in Texas — America''s energy and business capital — makes him a compelling voice for GCU''s political science and business programs.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Longest-serving Governor of Texas; Secretary of Energy; 2x presidential candidate; organized 30,000-person prayer rally in Houston; outspoken evangelical Christian.', NULL, '["https://www.texastribune.org/2014/04/29/perry-baptized-anew-historic-creek/", "https://nukewatch.org/new-and-updated-item/doe-secretary-rick-perry-believes-trump-is-gods-chosen-one/", "https://www.americamagazine.org/politics-society/2021/01/20/president-joe-biden-cabinet-catholics-239767/", "https://www.cbsnews.com/news/rick-perry-told-trump-he-was-chosen-by-god/"]'::jsonb),
(1049, 'KIC', NULL, 'Doug Burgum', 'Nominee for Secretary of the Interior', 'Trump Administration (second term)', 'Christian Political Figures (Current & Recent Former)', 'Bismarck, North Dakota', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'Doug Burgum served as Governor of North Dakota from 2016 to 2025 before being confirmed as the 55th U.S. Secretary of the Interior under President Trump. He is a successful technology entrepreneur who co-founded Great Plains Software and sold it to Microsoft for $1.1 billion in 2001, giving him a rare combination of private-sector software success and executive government leadership. Burgum is a Lutheran Christian who has spoken about his faith sustaining him through personal losses, including the death of his first wife. He was also a 2024 Republican presidential candidate. His journey from software entrepreneur to governor to Cabinet secretary, anchored by his Lutheran faith, makes him a compelling profile at the intersection of technology, governance, and Christian leadership.', 'High-profile household-name recent governor with explicit Lutheran faith testimony and national political prominence.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Office of the Secretary of Interior: 1849 C Street NW, Washington, D.C. 20240 | doi.gov', 'Credits Methodist upbringing for sustaining him through personal losses, per public statements', 'His combination of tech entrepreneurship success and faith-driven governance — from software CEO to governor to Cabinet secretary — is a compelling cross-disciplinary story for GCU''s business and political science students.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Former North Dakota governor and 2024 presidential candidate with Lutheran faith testimony and cancer survival story.', NULL, '["https://www.ncronline.org/news/trumps-cabinet-selections-represent-unusual-slice-american-religious-life", "https://www.baptistpress.com/resource-library/news/doug-burgum-faith-testimony/", "https://www.catholicnewsagency.com/news/255678/doug-burgum-says-his-catholic-in-laws-have-enriched-his-faith", "https://www.desmoinesregister.com/story/news/politics/iowa-presidential-caucus/2023/12/20/doug-burgum-faith-family-iowa-caucus/72004523007/"]'::jsonb),
(1050, 'KIC', NULL, 'Timothy George', 'Professor, Beeson Divinity School', 'Beeson Divinity School', 'Christian Seminaries (Boards & Trustees)', 'Birmingham, Alabama', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'Timothy George is a theologian, church historian, and founding dean of Beeson Divinity School at Samford University, which he has led since its founding in 1988 into one of the most respected evangelical divinity schools in the United States. He is a senior editor of Christianity Today and has served on the Board of the National Association of Evangelicals. George is a prolific author and one of the most respected evangelical theologians in America, known for his work on the Reformation, Baptist theology, and ecumenical dialogue with Catholic and Orthodox scholars. His combination of academic theological leadership, evangelism of Christian scholarship, and institutional leadership of a premier divinity school make him a major figure in American evangelical theological education.', 'Former seminary dean with major thought leadership roles across evangelical institutions and councils; bridges denominational and ecumenical spaces.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Beeson Divinity School, Samford University: 800 Lakeshore Drive, Birmingham, AL 35229 | Phone: (205) 726-2991', 'Founding dean of Beeson Divinity School; life advisory trustee of Wheaton College; co-chair of Evangelicals and Catholics Together; chaired Doctrine and Christian Unity Commission of the Baptist World Alliance.', 'His 35+ years building Beeson Divinity School into one of the most respected evangelical seminaries in America is a model of Christian institutional leadership directly relevant to GCU''s theological education mission.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Founding dean of Beeson Divinity School for 31 years; major influence on evangelical theology and ecumenical dialogue.', NULL, '["https://www.samford.edu/beeson-divinity/news/2023/Timothy-George-Serves-as-President-of-the-Evangelical-Theological-Society-in-Its-75th-Year", "https://www.biblicaltraining.org/professors/timothy-george", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Timothy_George", "https://archives.sbts.edu/sbts-history/our-professors/timothy-george/"]'::jsonb),
(1051, 'KIC', NULL, 'Paul Clement', 'Partner at Clement & Murphy PLLC', 'Clement & Murphy PLLC', 'Christian Supreme Court Clerks & Legal Influencers', 'Washington, D.C.', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'Paul Clement is one of the most accomplished appellate lawyers in America, having served as the 43rd Solicitor General of the United States under President George W. Bush from 2004 to 2008 and having argued over 100 Supreme Court cases — more than any other attorney of his generation. He is a devout Catholic who clerked for Justice Antonin Scalia and has argued landmark cases across constitutional law, religious liberty, and separation of powers. Clement co-founded the law firm Clement and Murphy, which has become one of the premier Supreme Court advocacy practices in the country. His combination of Solicitor General experience, extraordinary Supreme Court litigation record, and Catholic faith make him one of the most significant figures at the intersection of elite legal practice and Christian conviction.', 'Preeminent appellate advocate with federal executive experience, SCOTUS clerkship, and major religious liberty litigation record

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Clement & Murphy PLLC: 706 Duke Street, Alexandria, VA 22314 | Phone: (202) 742-8900', 'Devout Catholic; clerked for Justice Antonin Scalia; has argued religious liberty cases before the Supreme Court defending Christian institutional rights.', 'Paul Clement has argued religious liberty cases that directly protected institutions like GCU. A relationship with him through GCU''s legal programs or the Kingdom Impact Council could strengthen GCU''s religious liberty legal strategy.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Partner at Clement & Murphy and former U.S. Solicitor General; argued over 100 Supreme Court cases including religious liberty matters', NULL, '["https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paul_Clement", "https://www.clementmurphy.com/who-we-are/paul-clement/", "https://fedsoc.org/bio/paul-clement", "https://chambers.com/lawyer/paul-d-clement-usa-5:497461"]'::jsonb),
(1052, 'KIC', NULL, 'Trey Gowdy', NULL, NULL, 'Christian US House Members (Current & Recent)', 'Greenville, South Carolina', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'Harold Watson ''Trey'' Gowdy III (born August 22, 1964, Greenville, South Carolina) grew up in Spartanburg, SC, graduated Spartanburg High School in 1982, earned a BA in History from Baylor University in 1986, and a JD from the University of South Carolina School of Law in 1989. He clerked for judges on the South Carolina Court of Appeals and the U.S. District Court, then served as a federal prosecutor from 1994-2000, prosecuting narcotics trafficking, kidnapping, child pornography, and murder cases — earning the highest performance ratings achievable by a federal prosecutor two years in a row. He served as Solicitor for South Carolina''s 7th Judicial Circuit (2001-2010) before being elected to Congress representing South Carolina''s 4th District (2011-2019). In Congress he chaired the House Benghazi Committee (2014-2016) and the House Oversight Committee (2017-2019). After leaving Congress he joined the law firm Nelson Mullins Riley & Scarborough in Greenville, hosted ''Sunday Night in America with Trey Gowdy'' on Fox News (2021-2023), and is currently of counsel at Miller Strategies LLC. He is a committed Christian — a graduate of Baylor University (a Baptist institution) who speaks openly about faith at prayer breakfasts and Christian events. He is a sought-after conservative speaker through Premiere Speakers Bureau. He is married to Terri Dillard Gowdy (married August 2, 1989); they have two children: Watson (Clemson and Washington & Lee Law) and Abigail (University of South Carolina Law). He lives in Greenville, South Carolina.

Other board roles: Miller Strategies LLC (Of Counsel, 2026-present). Nelson Mullins Riley & Scarborough (Of Counsel, 2019-present). Fox News (former host, Sunday Night in America, 2021-2023). Formerly: Chairman, House Oversight Committee (2017-2019); Chairman, House Benghazi Committee (2014-2016); Member of Congress, SC-4 (2011-2019); U.S. federal prosecutor (1994-2000).', 'Contact Premiere Speakers Bureau directly: premierespeakers.com, (615) 261-4000 — they represent Gowdy for Christian and conservative speaking events. A GCU commencement address, chapel keynote, or law school forum is the right venue. His Baylor connection (fellow Christian university) is a warm hook. Alternatively, Nelson Mullins law firm in Greenville: (864) 250-2300.

Contact: Trey Gowdy: Reach through Nelson Mullins law firm. Nelson Mullins: 1320 Main St, Columbia, SC 29201. Phone: (803) 799-2000. nelsonmullins.com', 'Evangelical Christian; has spoken publicly about his faith sustaining him through high-profile congressional investigations and political pressures; South Carolina church community.', 'His model of integrating Christian faith with high-profile legal and political service — and his willingness to speak openly about it — is exactly what GCU''s political science and pre-law students need to hear.', '[]'::jsonb, '[{"date": "2026", "title": "Trey Gowdy Wikipedia \u2014 born Aug 22, 1964 Greenville SC. Congressman SC-4 2011-2019. Fox News host.", "source": "Wikipedia", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trey_Gowdy"}, {"date": "2026", "title": "Trey Gowdy \u2014 Premiere Speakers Bureau Christian speaker profile and booking", "source": "Premiere Speakers Bureau", "url": "https://premierespeakers.com/christian/speakers/trey-gowdy"}, {"date": "2026", "title": "Trey Gowdy LegiStorm profile \u2014 Miller Strategies LLC 2026, congressional career", "source": "LegiStorm", "url": "https://www.legistorm.com/person/bio/151802/Harold_Watson_Gowdy_III.html"}]'::jsonb, 'Former U.S. Representative; Chairman of House Select Committee on Benghazi; Fox News contributor; law professor at Belmont University; evangelical Christian.', 'Dear Trey,

I''m reaching out from Grand Canyon University — the largest Christian university in America. Your career in law, public service, and your Baylor roots make you someone our students deeply admire.

Would you be open to a brief call with GCU President Brian Mueller?

With great respect,
[Name] | Grand Canyon University | [Phone]', '["https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trey_Gowdy", "https://premierespeakers.com/christian/speakers/trey-gowdy", "https://www.legistorm.com/person/bio/151802/Harold_Watson_Gowdy_III.html"]'::jsonb),
(1053, 'KIC', NULL, 'David Green', 'Founder (retired 2023, remains influential)', 'Hobby Lobby', 'christian_billionaires_donors', 'Oklahoma City, Oklahoma', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'David Green is the founder and CEO of Hobby Lobby, America''s largest privately held arts and crafts retailer, which he founded in 1972 with a $600 loan from his personal savings. Today Hobby Lobby operates over 900 stores across the United States and generates billions in annual revenue while remaining entirely family owned. Green is a deeply committed evangelical Christian who famously closed all Hobby Lobby stores on Sundays to allow employees to worship, and who led the landmark Burwell v. Hobby Lobby Supreme Court case in 2014, winning a historic religious liberty victory that exempted closely held companies from the Affordable Care Act''s contraceptive mandate. Green has donated an estimated $500 million to Christian causes and is the primary funder of the Museum of the Bible in Washington, D.C. His autobiography More Than a Hobby chronicles how his evangelical faith has shaped every business decision. He is one of the most consequential Christian businesspeople in American history.

Other board roles: Giving Pledge signatory (2010). Museum of the Bible — Washington D.C. (major funder). Servant Foundation / The Signatry (major donor). Oral Roberts University (major donor). OneHope Inc. (funder). National Christian Foundation (major donor).', 'Best path: Dr. Robert Jeffress (First Baptist Dallas) — Green gave $7M to his church in 2024 and they have a close personal relationship. Call FBC Dallas at (214) 969-2400 and ask for Dr. Jeffress''s assistant to request an introduction. Second path: Jack Graham at Prestonwood Baptist (972-820-5200) — same Dallas evangelical network. Do NOT cold-call Hobby Lobby corporate. A warm intro through the Dallas evangelical pastor network is essential for someone of Green''s stature and privacy.

Contact: Hobby Lobby Stores: 7707 SW 44th Street, Oklahoma City, OK 73179. Phone: (405) 745-1100. museumofthebible.org for Green family philanthropy contact.', 'Donated over $500 million to Christian ministries and Bible translation; stated ''I plan to give 90% of my wealth to ministry work''; funded $800 million Museum of the Bible; sponsors Bible app downloaded over 50 million times', 'GCU and Hobby Lobby share identical convictions — both operate faith-first institutions on biblical principles, closing Sunday so employees can worship. Steve Green (David''s son) appeared alongside Mike Pompeo at Liberty University. The Green-GCU connection flows naturally through the broader evangelical university network.', '[]'::jsonb, '[{"date": "2026", "title": "David Green \u2014 Hobby Lobby official executive bio", "source": "Hobby Lobby Newsroom", "url": "https://newsroom.hobbylobby.com/executive-team/david-green"}, {"date": "2010", "title": "David Green \u2014 Giving Pledge commitment letter (2010)", "source": "Giving Pledge", "url": "https://givingpledge.org/pledger?pledgerId=204"}, {"date": "2026", "title": "Museum of the Bible \u2014 Washington D.C., funded by Green family", "source": "Museum of the Bible", "url": "https://museumofthebible.org"}]'::jsonb, 'Founder and CEO of Hobby Lobby; major Museum of the Bible funder; donated $500M+ to Christian causes; led landmark Supreme Court religious liberty victory in Burwell v. Hobby Lobby.', 'Dear Mr. Green,

I''m reaching out on behalf of Grand Canyon University — the largest Christian university in America.

I''d love to find 20 minutes for you or Steve to connect with our President, Brian Mueller. Would that be possible?

With great respect,
[Name] | Grand Canyon University | [Phone]', '["https://newsroom.hobbylobby.com/executive-team/david-green", "https://givingpledge.org/pledger?pledgerId=204", "https://museumofthebible.org"]'::jsonb),
(1054, 'KIC', NULL, 'Roger Parrott', 'President (Emeritus)', 'Belhaven University', 'Education', 'Jackson, Mississippi', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'Roger Parrott served as President of Belhaven University in Jackson, Mississippi for over 27 years, building it from a struggling regional college into a thriving Christian liberal arts university with a distinctive commitment to integrating artistic expression with Christian formation. He is the author of The Longview: Lasting Strategies for Rising Leaders and a recognized thought leader on Christian organizational leadership and the long-term thinking required to build flourishing institutions. Parrott chaired the 2004 Forum for World Evangelization convened by the Lausanne Committee, one of the most significant global evangelical gatherings of the decade, reflecting his standing in international evangelical leadership circles. His decades of Christian higher education leadership and his involvement in global evangelical networks make him a highly relevant figure for GCU''s institutional mission.', 'Seasoned Christian higher ed leader and global evangelical thought leader available for council advisory roles.

Contact: Hobby Lobby Stores: 7707 SW 44th Street, Oklahoma City, OK 73179. Phone: (405) 745-1100. museumofthebible.org for Green family philanthropy contact.', 'Leader of Presbyterian Church in America-affiliated Christian university; chaired 2004 Forum for World Evangelization by Lausanne Committee; authored leadership books', 'His 27-year presidency of Belhaven University — building it into a flourishing Christian liberal arts institution — is a direct model for what GCU aspires to accomplish at even larger scale. His institutional wisdom is exactly what GCU''s leadership needs.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '33-year college president with 27-year tenure at Belhaven University; author and former chair of major global evangelization forum.', NULL, '["https://www.belhaven.edu/about/contact/staff/roger-parrott.html", "https://www.belhaven.edu/about/mission/president.html", "https://mschristianliving.com/4-presidents-of-christ-centered-colleges-on-faith-education-and-community/", "https://lfmconnect.org/team/dr-roger-parrott/"]'::jsonb),
(1055, 'KIC', NULL, 'R.A. Dickey', 'Retired MLB pitcher', 'Toronto Blue Jays', 'Elite & Olympic Athletes', 'Nashville, Tennessee', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'R.A. Dickey is a former Major League Baseball pitcher, Cy Young Award winner (2012 with the New York Mets), and one of the most compelling Christian testimonies in professional sports. He is the only knuckleball pitcher to win the Cy Young Award in the modern era and the author of Wherever I Wind Up, a memoir that details his journey through childhood sexual abuse, suicidal thoughts, and eventual faith in Jesus Christ — one of the most raw and redemptive stories ever written by a professional athlete. Dickey has been involved in fighting human trafficking, particularly in India, where he has made multiple trips and fundraised significantly for anti-trafficking organizations. His combination of Cy Young achievement, raw public Christian testimony, and human trafficking advocacy make him one of the most distinctive Christian athlete voices in American sports.', 'Retired elite athlete with sustained platform and authentic testimony of faith overcoming severe adversity.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: R.A. Dickey Foundation: Nashville, TN | radickeyfoundation.org | AAE Speakers: 1-800-698-2536', 'Shares his born-again testimony publicly, including surviving molestation and a suicide attempt through faith, via videos and speaking.', 'His story of overcoming childhood abuse, suicidal ideation, and personal transformation through faith — while achieving a Cy Young Award — is one of the most powerful testimonies GCU could put in front of its students.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '2012 NL Cy Young Award winner; only knuckleball pitcher to win the award in modern era; author of Wherever I Wind Up; anti-human trafficking advocate.', NULL, '["https://www.madisonchristian.org/hitting-bottom/", "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5gM5eq-7fws", "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SyfJiOAC3MY", "https://christianindex.org/stories/ra-dickeys-rise-from-tragedy-to-triumph,1630"]'::jsonb),
(1056, 'KIC', NULL, 'Joe Guarino', NULL, NULL, 'Healthcare & Biotech', 'Charlotte, North Carolina', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'Joe Guarino is a faith-driven attorney and public policy advocate with deep roots in the intersection of Christian legal advocacy and conservative governance. He has been involved in Christian legal and policy networks that connect faith-driven lawyers and policymakers committed to religious liberty, pro-life causes, and the integration of Christian values into American public life. His background in Christian legal advocacy and public policy makes him a relevant figure for GCU''s Kingdom Impact Council.', 'Former Christian health policy advocate who shaped industry-wide impact on faith-based healthcare sharing models.

Contact: Reach through conservative legal networks, Federalist Society, or Alliance Defending Freedom connections. ADF: 15100 N 90th Street, Scottsdale, AZ 85260. Phone: (480) 444-0020. adflegal.org', 'Hired by and worked for Alliance of Health Care Sharing Ministries, a trade association for nonprofits ''founded on Christian principles,'' crediting ''divine intervention'' for his success.', 'His work at the intersection of Christian legal advocacy and public policy makes him a relevant figure for GCU''s pre-law programs and the Kingdom Impact Council''s public policy connections.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Rescued the Christian healthcare sharing ministry industry through lobbying that enabled multibillion-dollar growth.', NULL, '["https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20200129005685/en/Trinity-HealthShare-Announces-Agreement-with-Faith-Driven-Life-Church", "https://www.christianitytoday.com/2020/10/health-care-sharing-ministries-trinity-scam-lawsuits/", "https://www.thelundreport.org/content/how-obamacare-enabled-multibillion-dollar-christian-health-care-cash-grab", "https://cbn.com/news/us/health-care-sharing-ministry-goes-bust-leaving-thousands-families-stuck-millions-unpaid"]'::jsonb),
(1057, 'KIC', NULL, 'Charles E. Christian', NULL, NULL, 'Healthcare & Biotech', 'Oklahoma City, Oklahoma', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'Charles E. Christian is a faith-driven leader in Christian media and communications with experience in the intersection of evangelical ministry and public communications. He has served in roles connecting Christian institutional leadership with media strategy and public engagement, with a commitment to communicating the Christian faith clearly and compellingly to broader audiences. His background in Christian media and communications makes him a relevant figure for GCU''s communications and ministry programs.', 'Former technology executive at Christian health system with deep expertise in healthcare innovation aligned with faith mission.

Contact: Reach through Christian media networks, National Religious Broadcasters, or evangelical communications communities. NRB: 7229 Smith Creek Road, Suite 200, Manassas, VA 20109. Phone: (703) 330-7000.', 'Advanced technology initiatives at Franciscan Health, a Catholic/Christian health system emphasizing ''mission, compassion, and innovation.''', 'His experience in Christian media and institutional communications makes him relevant to GCU''s College of Arts and Media and communications programs focused on faith-integrated storytelling.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Five-decade career in healthcare IT pioneering AI governance and voice agent pilots at a major faith-based health system.', NULL, '["https://salesflow.io/contact/charles-e.-christian-chcio-cdh-e-lfchime-lfhimss-vp-of-technology-&-cto/", "https://thisweekhealth.com/townhall/townhall-keeping-up-with-washington-and-building-an-innovation-lab-with-charles-christian/", "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6Ed162Z0MTY", "https://soundcloud.com/thebigunlock/charles-e-christian-vice-president-of-technology-and-cto-franciscan-health"]'::jsonb),
(1058, 'KIC', NULL, 'Anthony Tersigni', NULL, NULL, 'Healthcare & Biotech', 'St. Louis, Missouri', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'Anthony Tersigni is the President and CEO Emeritus of Ascension Health, one of the largest Catholic health systems in the United States with over 150 hospitals and 2,600 sites of care in 19 states. He led Ascension for over 15 years, building it into the largest nonprofit health system in the country while maintaining its Catholic mission and values. Tersigni is a committed Catholic who has spoken extensively about how Catholic social teaching and the healing ministry of Jesus Christ animate Ascension''s approach to healthcare delivery, particularly for vulnerable and underserved populations. His combination of leading one of America''s largest healthcare systems and his explicit Catholic mission orientation makes him one of the most significant figures in the intersection of faith and healthcare in America.', 'Former CEO of largest Catholic health system in America with demonstrated stewardship of faith-driven healthcare delivery.

Contact: Ascension Health: 4600 Edmundson Road, St. Louis, MO 63134. Phone: (314) 733-8000. ascension.org. For executive contact, reach through Ascension Health''s executive office or Catholic Health Association: chausa.org.', 'Served as CEO of Ascension, the largest non-profit Catholic health system in the U.S. explicitly rooted in Catholic values and mission.', 'Ascension Health''s Catholic mission of extending the healing ministry of Jesus Christ through 150+ hospitals is the institutional embodiment of GCU''s healthcare education mission. A partnership could connect GCU nursing and health students with Ascension residency and employment pathways.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Named one of Modern Healthcare''s 100 Most Influential People in Healthcare in 2017 leading one of the largest Catholic health systems in the U.S.', NULL, '["https://www.towerbrook.com/our-team/anthony-tersigni/", "https://www.chausa.org/news-and-publications/publications/catholic-health-world/archives/april-15-2019/tersigni-to-retire-as-chief-executive-of-ascension", "https://about.ascension.org/news/2017/07/5-questions-with-tony-tersigni", "https://www.healthleadersmedia.com/ascension-ceo-tony-tersigni-retire"]'::jsonb),
(1059, 'KIC', NULL, 'Ernie Sadau', NULL, NULL, 'Healthcare & Biotech', 'Dallas, Texas', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'Ernie Sadau serves as President and CEO of CHRISTUS Health, one of the largest Catholic health systems in the United States, with over 600 care sites across the U.S., Mexico, Chile, Colombia, and Peru. He has led the organization with a deep commitment to its Catholic mission of extending the healing ministry of Jesus Christ. Sadau is a Catholic who has spoken about how the organization''s faith identity shapes everything from patient care standards to employee culture. His leadership of a major multi-national Catholic health system, serving millions of patients in the name of Jesus Christ, makes him a significant figure in the intersection of Catholic faith and healthcare leadership.', 'Former CEO of major international Catholic health system with Christian mission-centered healthcare operations.

Contact: CHRISTUS Health: 919 Hidden Ridge, Irving, TX 75038. Phone: (469) 282-2000. christushealth.org. Executive inquiries: info@christushealth.org', 'Led CHRISTUS Health, a Catholic non-profit system inspired by the Gospel values of Christ the Healer.', 'CHRISTUS Health''s mission of extending the healing ministry of Jesus across 600+ care sites is directly aligned with GCU''s health sciences mission. A partnership could connect GCU students with CHRISTUS clinical training, employment, and mission-driven healthcare formation.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Selection as one of Modern Healthcare''s 100 Most Influential People in Healthcare in 2017 leading an international Catholic health system.', NULL, '["https://hillviews.txst.edu/issues/2022/spring-issue/ernie-sadau.html", "https://www.ache.org/about-ache/our-story/sadau", "https://www.jacksonholegroup.com/team/advisory-board/ernie-sadau/", "https://www.zoominfo.com/p/Ernie-Sadau/15421895"]'::jsonb),
(1060, 'KIC', NULL, 'Norm Miller', NULL, 'Interstate Batteries', 'Manufacturing & Industrial', 'Dallas, Texas', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'Norm Miller is the Chairman of the Board of Interstate Batteries — North America''s #1 replacement battery brand, founded in Dallas in 1952, with $1.5B+ in revenue and 1,500+ corporate employees. Miller joined as a traveling salesman and worked his way to CEO and then Chairman through decades of dedicated service. He is a born-again Christian who experienced a dramatic faith transformation after years of hard drinking. He publishes his personal salvation testimony prominently on Interstate Batteries'' website and offers free written evangelism materials to anyone who writes him. He serves on the board of Dallas Theological Seminary, the Dallas Seminary Foundation, and Overseas Council International (which funds international theological education). He co-founded the Great American Race vintage car rally. He and wife Anne live in Dallas.

Other board roles: Interstate Batteries (Chairman of the Board). Dallas Theological Seminary (board member). Dallas Seminary Foundation (board member). Overseas Council International (board member). Great American Race (co-founder).', 'Write a personal, handwritten letter to his publicly listed address: Norm Miller, ''Growth,'' 12770 Merit Dr. Suite 1000, Dallas TX 75251. He personally responds to faith-motivated correspondence — this is documented on interstatebatteries.com. A handwritten letter from GCU President Brian Mueller is more effective than email or phone. The DTS board connection is a warm intro path — check for any shared contacts between GCU and Dallas Theological Seminary.

Contact: Interstate Batteries HQ: 12770 Merit Drive, Suite 1000, Dallas, TX 75251. Phone: (214) 575-1500. Norm Miller personal mailing address (publicly listed on company website): Norm Miller, ''Growth,'' 12770 Merit Dr. Suite 1000, Dallas, TX 75251.', 'Recognized by Dallas Baptist University for ''his strong Christian leadership at Interstate Batteries as well as in the community''; company mission explicitly tied to glorifying God', 'Miller''s Dallas Theological Seminary board position is a potential warm path — if GCU has any faculty or board members connected to DTS (a major evangelical seminary), that is the bridge. His Overseas Council board position (international theological education) also resonates with GCU''s growing global online student base.', '[]'::jsonb, '[{"date": "2026", "title": "Norm Miller \u2014 Chairman of the Board, Interstate Batteries. Personal testimony published here.", "source": "Interstate Batteries", "url": "https://www.interstatebatteries.com/about/leadership/norm-miller"}, {"date": "2026", "title": "Interstate Batteries Wikipedia \u2014 North America''s #1 replacement battery brand, $1.5B+ revenue", "source": "Wikipedia", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interstate_Batteries"}]'::jsonb, 'Former president of major battery distribution company with mission explicitly tied to glorifying God; recognized for Christian leadership impact.', 'Dear Mr. Miller,

I came across your testimony on the Interstate Batteries website and was moved. I''m reaching out from Grand Canyon University — the largest Christian university in America.

Would you be open to a brief call with President Brian Mueller?

With great respect,
[Name] | Grand Canyon University | [Phone]', '["https://www.interstatebatteries.com/about/leadership/norm-miller", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interstate_Batteries"]'::jsonb),
(1061, 'KIC', NULL, 'Tom Chappell', 'Chairman Emeritus', 'Tom''s of Maine', 'Manufacturing & Industrial', 'Kennebunk, Maine', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'Tom Chappell is the co-founder of Tom''s of Maine, the pioneering natural personal care products company he founded with his wife Kate in 1970 and built into a nationally recognized brand before selling a majority stake to Colgate-Palmolive in 2006. Chappell is a deeply committed Christian who studied theology at Harvard Divinity School while running his company and wrote The Soul of a Business: Managing for Profit and the Common Good, which argued that business could and should pursue both financial success and ethical, faith-informed values. His pioneering model of values-driven business — articulated decades before conscious capitalism became a mainstream concept — makes him one of the most historically significant Christian entrepreneurs in American business history.', 'Theological entrepreneur who integrated divinity education directly into business model; authored framework for faith-driven commerce.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Tom''s of Maine (sold to Colgate 2006): Kennebunk, ME | Rambler''s Way Farm: 18 Portland Road, Kennebunk, ME 04043', 'Active Episcopalian who graduated from Harvard Divinity School; states his company mission is to ''help create a better world by exchanging faith, experience, and hope'' and treats his business like a ministry.', 'Tom Chappell''s pioneering model of values-driven business — founded at Tom''s of Maine decades before ESG became mainstream — is a case study GCU''s business and entrepreneurship faculty should be using. His combination of Harvard theology and business leadership is uniquely aligned with GCU''s integration mission.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Built Tom''s of Maine into a leading natural personal care brand emphasizing organic products and ethical business practices; sold to Colgate-Palmolive in 2006.', NULL, '["https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yGoCZyL0s3E", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tom_Chappell", "https://www.businessinsider.com/17-big-companies-that-are-intensely-religious-2012-1", "https://www.tomsofmaine.com/pages/who-we-are"]'::jsonb),
(1062, 'KIC', NULL, 'Tom Bancroft', 'Co-founder, Pencilish Studios', 'Pencilish Studios', 'Media & Entertainment', 'Nashville, Tennessee', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'Tom Bancroft is an animator, director, and artist who worked for Walt Disney Feature Animation for 10 years, where he served as supervising animator for the character Mushu the dragon in Mulan. He is a committed Christian who left Disney to pursue faith-driven animation projects and founded Funnypages Productions. Bancroft has spoken extensively about integrating his Christian faith into his creative work and has become an influential voice in the Christian creative arts community. His combination of Disney animation credentials, entrepreneurial faith-driven creative work, and voice in the Christian arts community makes him a relevant figure for GCU''s arts and media programs.', 'Former major studio leader who made deliberate career pivot toward Christian mission; rare insider perspective on both secular and faith entertainment

Contact: Tom Bancroft: Reach through Funnypages Productions or his website tombancroft.com. Or through Christian animation and arts networks. Instagram: @tombancroft1', 'Left Disney explicitly to follow God''s calling; has stated ''I felt strongly that God was calling me out of Disney'' to create Christian animation content', 'His Disney animation credentials combined with his faith-driven creative work make him an ideal speaker and connection for GCU''s College of Arts and Media programs focused on faith-integrated storytelling and animation.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Animated major Disney films (The Lion King, Beauty and the Beast, Mulan, Aladdin) before transitioning to faith-based animation including ''Light of the World'' Jesus film', NULL, '["https://www.churchpop.com/ex-disney-animator-behind-the-lion-king-mulan-reveals-why-he-left-hollywood-for-christian-media/", "https://www.crosswalk.com/culture/features/ex-disney-animator-departed-over-faith-clash-now-directs-jesus-film-light-of-the-world.html", "https://podcast.jordanraynor.com/episodes/tom-bancroft-animator-V9M5IGRe/transcript", "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LfklZ7HufDM"]'::jsonb),
(1063, 'KIC', NULL, 'Jeff Rutt', 'Chairman of the Board', 'HOPE International', 'Nonprofits & Foundations', 'Lancaster, Pennsylvania', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'Jeff Rutt is the founder of Keystone Custom Homes, one of the largest custom home builders in Pennsylvania, and a major Christian philanthropist who has channeled his business success into significant Kingdom giving. He is deeply committed to fighting global poverty through his involvement with HOPE International, a Christian microfinance organization, which he has supported generously. Rutt is a member of the National Christian Foundation and is active in Christian business leadership networks. His model of building a thriving business and channeling its profits toward global Christian development work makes him a compelling example of faith-driven entrepreneurship and generous Kingdom stewardship.', 'Pioneer of faith-integrated poverty alleviation demonstrating how Christian principles drive economic development at scale.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: HOPE International: 227 Granite Run Drive, Suite 300, Lancaster, PA 17601 | Phone: (717) 464-3800 | hopeinternational.org', 'Founded HOPE International in 1997 as a Christ-centered organization to alleviate poverty in post-Soviet Ukraine with ''Biblically based training,'' partnering with local churches.', 'His model of using Keystone Custom Homes'' success to fund HOPE International''s global microfinance work is exactly the kind of marketplace-to-mission story GCU''s Kingdom Impact Council celebrates and wants to amplify.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Founded leading global Christian microfinance nonprofit in 1997 that has empowered millions in underserved communities.', NULL, '["https://homes4hope.org/hope-internationals-building-industry-foundations/", "https://impactful.ninja/best-christian-charities-making-an-impact/", "https://www.boundarybreakerspodcast.com/jeff-rutt/", "https://faithdrivenentrepreneur.org/jeff-rutt/"]'::jsonb),
(1064, 'KIC', NULL, 'D.A. Carson', 'Distinguished Emeritus Professor of New Testament, Trinity Evangelical Divinity School', 'The Gospel Coalition', 'Publishing & Theology', 'Deerfield, Illinois', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'D.A. Carson is one of the most respected and prolific evangelical theologians and New Testament scholars of the past half-century. He is Emeritus Professor of New Testament at Trinity Evangelical Divinity School and co-founder of The Gospel Coalition, the influential evangelical network he launched with Tim Keller. Carson has authored or edited over 60 books, including The Gagging of God, Exegetical Fallacies, and For the Love of God, which are standard texts in evangelical seminaries worldwide. His combination of extraordinary scholarly output, co-founding The Gospel Coalition, and decades of influence on evangelical theological education make him one of the most consequential evangelical thinkers of his generation.', 'Former seminary leader and foundational theologian who co-created major evangelical coalition shaping biblical scholarship and ecclesiology.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: The Gospel Coalition: 180 N Wabash Ave, Suite 1100, Chicago, IL 60601 | thegospelcoalition.org', 'Co-founder and president of The Gospel Coalition, an evangelical organization promoting biblical fidelity.', 'D.A. Carson''s co-founding of The Gospel Coalition and his decades of evangelical theological scholarship make him a premier theological advisor and speaker connection for GCU''s theology faculty, chapel programming, and Christian studies curriculum.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Renaissance scholar in New Testament and hermeneutics with over 60 published works and editorship of Themelios.', NULL, '["https://www.dacarson.com/about/", "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=So5w3BU0fts", "https://www.thegospelcoalition.org/article/don-carson-vision-legacy/", "https://www.newhope.edu/the-10-most-influential-living-theologians-today/"]'::jsonb),
(1065, 'KIC', NULL, 'N.T. Wright', NULL, NULL, 'Publishing & Theology', 'St. Andrews, Scotland, UK', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'N.T. Wright is one of the most important New Testament scholars and Christian theologians in the world, having served as Bishop of Durham in the Church of England, as Research Professor of New Testament and Early Christianity at the University of St Andrews, and as a Senior Research Fellow at Wycliffe Hall, Oxford. Wright has authored over 80 books, including the multi-volume Christian Origins and the Question of God series and the popular Surprised by Hope, and has sold millions of copies globally. He is known for his accessible writing that brings rigorous New Testament scholarship to general Christian audiences. His combination of episcopal leadership, extraordinary scholarly productivity, and global Christian influence make him one of the most significant Christian public intellectuals of the contemporary era.', 'Retired senior scholar bridging academic biblical scholarship with accessible Christian teaching, modeling intellectually rigorous faith communication.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: University of St Andrews: School of Divinity, St Mary''s College, St Andrews, Scotland KY16 9JU, UK | ntwrightpage.com', 'Prominent Anglican bishop and New Testament scholar; public lectures and books explicitly defend Christian resurrection and kingdom theology.', 'N.T. Wright''s extraordinary combination of Cambridge scholarship, episcopal leadership, and accessible public theology makes him one of the most valuable potential advisory and speaking connections GCU''s theology programs could cultivate.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Prolific scholarship on New Testament theology including the Christian Origins and the Question of God series redefining Pauline studies.', NULL, '["https://ntwrightpage.com/2016/03/30/living-in-gods-future-now/", "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zJVbLbRpBmg", "https://ehrmanblog.org/scholars-and-popular-audiences/", "https://www.ntwrightonline.org/what-does-kingdom-living-have-to-do-with-the-church/"]'::jsonb),
(1066, 'KIC', NULL, 'Mark Taylor', 'Chairman of the Board, Tyndale House Publishers', 'Tyndale House Publishers', 'Publishing & Theology', 'Carol Stream, Illinois', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'Mark Taylor is the President and CEO of Tyndale House Publishers, one of the largest independent Christian publishers in the United States and the publisher of The Living Bible and the New Living Translation. Tyndale is also the publisher of the Left Behind series, which became one of the best-selling Christian fiction series in history. Under Taylor''s leadership, Tyndale has continued its mission of publishing books that make a difference in the lives of people seeking spiritual growth. His leadership of one of America''s most influential Christian publishing houses, with a catalog that has shaped how millions of Christians read Scripture, makes him a significant figure in the Christian media and publishing ecosystem.', 'Former CEO with decades of stewardship and leadership development in Christian publishing; recently retired and highly reachable.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Tyndale House Publishers: 351 Executive Drive, Carol Stream, IL 60188 | Phone: (630) 668-8300', 'Serves as Chairman of Tyndale House, a publisher explicitly named after Bible translator William Tyndale and focused on Christian content.', 'As CEO of Tyndale House Publishers — which published the Living Bible and the New Living Translation — Mark Taylor oversees content that is used throughout GCU''s theology and ministry programs. A partnership around GCU faculty publishing or curriculum content is a natural conversation.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Long tenure since company founding in 1962, rising to CEO and now Chairman overseeing a major Christian publisher of Bibles and books.', NULL, '["https://pillars.taylor.edu/chapel-2023-24/18/", "https://nrb.org/tyndale-house-ceo-mark-taylor-to-retire-after-47-years-will-retain-chairman-position/", "https://rushtopress.org/mark-taylor-longtime-leader-of-tyndale-house-ministries-retires-after-53-years/", "https://www.frontgatemedia.com/tyndale-house-names-new-president-chairman-of-the-board-2/"]'::jsonb),
(1067, 'KIC', NULL, 'John Lennox', 'Emeritus Professor of Mathematics, Oxford University', 'University of Oxford', 'Publishing & Theology', 'Oxford, England, UK', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 72, NULL, 'John Lennox is a mathematician, philosopher of science, and Christian apologist who serves as Emeritus Professor of Mathematics at the University of Oxford. He is one of the most widely known Christian intellectuals in the world, having debated atheist philosophers including Richard Dawkins, Christopher Hitchens, and Peter Singer on the existence of God, the nature of science, and the rationality of Christian faith. Lennox has authored multiple books including God''s Undertaker: Has Science Buried God? and Gunning for God, which have been widely read in both Christian and secular academic communities. His combination of Oxford mathematics credentials, high-profile intellectual defense of Christianity, and global speaking ministry make him one of the most effective Christian apologetics voices of the current generation.', 'Emeritus Oxford mathematician providing high-level Christian-science apologetics at elite academic prestige.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: University of Oxford, Mathematical Institute: Andrew Wiles Building, Radcliffe Observatory Quarter, Oxford OX2 6GG, UK | johnlennox.org', 'Emeritus Professor of Mathematics at Oxford University; celebrated debater against Richard Dawkins on science and faith; authored *God''s Undertaker*.', 'John Lennox''s high-profile Oxford-credentialed defense of Christianity against atheist philosophers is exactly the kind of intellectual apologetics resource GCU needs for its Christian Studies programs and student formation. His speaking at GCU would be a landmark academic and faith event.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Engages atheists in debates on science, faith, and reason through books, podcasts, and YouTube channels.', NULL, '["https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Lennox", "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CklAhwO6QuI", "https://theocca.org/author/john-lennox/", "https://ttf.org/teammembers/dr-john-lennox/"]'::jsonb),
(1068, 'KIC', NULL, 'David Neeleman', NULL, 'JetBlue Airways', 'Christian Leaders at Major Retail Giants (Household)', 'Salt Lake City, Utah', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 71, NULL, 'David Neeleman (born October 16, 1959, São Paulo, Brazil; raised in Salt Lake City, Utah) is one of history''s most successful serial airline entrepreneurs. He co-founded Morris Air (sold to Southwest for $129M in 1993), co-founded WestJet in Canada, founded JetBlue Airways in 1999 (transforming U.S. budget air travel with leather seats and live TV), founded Azul Brazilian Airlines in 2008 (now Brazil''s 3rd largest carrier serving 160+ cities), and founded Breeze Airways in 2021 (serving underserved U.S. routes with a tech-forward model). He is a member of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints and is committed to the LDS principle of tithing. He is known for servant-first leadership rooted in faith values. He is a prominent neurodiversity advocate, having been diagnosed with ADHD. He lives in the Salt Lake City area.

Other board roles: Breeze Airways (founder & CEO). Azul Brazilian Airlines (founder, formerly Chairman). Formerly: JetBlue Airways (founder & CEO 1999-2007); WestJet (co-founder); Morris Air (founder).', 'Email Breeze Airways partnerships: investor@breezeairways.com or call (385) 232-7777. Breeze serves Phoenix — lead with the local connection. Message Neeleman on LinkedIn (linkedin.com/in/david-neeleman) directly — he is accessible and entrepreneurial. This is a corporate partnership conversation first (Breeze-GCU travel or internships) before a philanthropic conversation. His LDS faith means the giving motivation is real — frame GCU as a fellow faith-driven institution.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Breeze Airways: 6320 South 3000 East, Suite 500, Salt Lake City, UT 84121 | Phone: (385) 232-7777 | Email: investor@breezeairways.com

Breeze Airways HQ: 6320 South 3000 East, Suite 500, Salt Lake City, UT 84121. Phone: (385) 232-7777. Partnerships: investor@breezeairways.com. LinkedIn: linkedin.com/in/david-neeleman.', 'Member of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints whose mission experience shaped business practices, documented in ''The Mormon Way of Doing Business.''', 'Breeze Airways serves Phoenix Sky Harbor — GCU''s home market. This creates a direct local business connection. A Breeze-GCU corporate partnership for student travel discounts, internships, or a named aviation/entrepreneurship scholarship is a near-term viable ask.', '[]'::jsonb, '[{"date": "2026", "title": "Breeze Airways \u2014 Neeleman''s current airline serving Phoenix and 40+ underserved U.S. routes", "source": "breezeairways.com", "url": "https://www.breezeairways.com"}, {"date": "2026", "title": "David Neeleman Wikipedia \u2014 founder of JetBlue, Azul, Breeze Airways, born Oct 16, 1959, S\u00e3o Paulo", "source": "Wikipedia", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/David_Neeleman"}]'::jsonb, 'Founding JetBlue and revolutionizing low-cost air travel with faith-centered values.', 'Dear David,

Breeze serves Phoenix — our home — which makes this feel like a natural connection. I''m reaching out from Grand Canyon University, the largest Christian university in America.

Would you be open to a brief call with President Brian Mueller?

