(1073, 'KIC', NULL, 'Vic Gundotra', 'Former Senior VP of Google', 'Google', 'Catholic Business Leaders (Household)', 'San Francisco, California', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 71, NULL, 'Vic Gundotra is a technology executive who served as Senior Vice President of Social at Google, where he led the development of Google Plus and oversaw major social and engineering initiatives. He is a committed Christian who has been open about his faith in Silicon Valley contexts and has been involved in Christian technology and leadership communities. After leaving Google, Gundotra founded AliveCor, a cardiac health technology company. His combination of senior Google executive experience, entrepreneurial track record in health technology, and Christian faith make him a distinctive figure at the intersection of Silicon Valley and Christian identity.', 'Major tech industry leader and recent Catholic convert integrating faith with AI innovation.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Pindrop Security: 1800 Peachtree Street NW, Suite 200, Atlanta, GA 30309 | LinkedIn: linkedin.com/in/vicgundotra', 'Catholic convert; spoke at 2026 Legatus Summit on using AI with Bible and faith', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'High-level tech executive at Google and Catholic convert sharing AI-faith insights.', NULL, '["https://www.catholicbusinessjournal.com/news/faith-at-work/catholic-business-profiles/vic-gundotra-former-google-exec-spoke-about-ai-bible-conversion-at-catholic-business-summit/", "https://www.catholicbusinessjournal.com/news/faith-at-work/catholic-business-profiles/", "https://www.keynotespeak.com/speaker/VicGundotra", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vic_Gundotra"]'::jsonb),
(1074, 'KIC', NULL, 'Nancy Pelosi', 'Former Speaker of the House of Representatives', NULL, 'Christian Catholic Democrats', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 0, NULL, 'Nancy Pelosi served as the 52nd Speaker of the U.S. House of Representatives and is a Democrat from San Francisco, California. She is a lifelong Catholic but is strongly pro-abortion rights. She is not aligned with GCU''s evangelical Christian mission or conservative values. She was included in the original dataset likely due to her Catholic faith signal, but she is not an appropriate prospect for GCU''s Kingdom Impact Council.', 'Not recommended for GCU outreach. Political and values misalignment with GCU''s evangelical Christian mission. Remove from active prospect list.', 'Prominent Catholic leader in Congress; first woman Speaker', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'First female Speaker of the House and prominent Catholic voice in Democratic leadership.', NULL, '["https://www.kqed.org/news/12062796/nancy-pelosi-leaves-congress-after-38-years-defining-generations-of-democratic-power", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Catholic_Democrats", "http://pelosi.house.gov/biography", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nancy_Pelosi"]'::jsonb),
(1075, 'KIC', NULL, 'Lt. Col. Oliver North', 'Host, War Stories on Fox Nation', NULL, 'Christian Military Veterans', 'McLean, Virginia', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 71, NULL, 'Lt. Col. Oliver North is a retired U.S. Marine Corps officer, political commentator, author, and former President of the National Rifle Association. He served on the National Security Council staff during the Reagan administration and became a central figure in the Iran-Contra affair. North is a devoted evangelical Christian who has written and spoken extensively about his faith, including authoring the Under Fire memoir and serving as a war correspondent for Fox News in multiple conflict zones. He also founded the Freedom Alliance, a charity supporting the families of fallen military heroes. His military service, political notoriety, evangelical faith, and veterans advocacy make him a high-profile and distinctive figure in American conservative Christian circles.', 'Household-name retired military figure with high public profile and consistent Christian witness

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Freedom Alliance: 22570 Markey Court, Suite 240, Dulles, VA 20166 | Phone: (703) 444-7940 | freedomalliance.org', 'Prominent Christian conservative leader and President of National Center for Constitutional Studies with public prayers and Christian media appearances', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Retired US Marine with 40+ years military service and Fox News host', NULL, '["https://www.olivernorthbooks.com/about-oliver-north", "https://www.britannica.com/biography/Oliver-North", "https://www.catholic.org/news/hf/faith/story.php?id=45678", "https://www.olivernorth.com"]'::jsonb),
(1076, 'KIC', NULL, 'Donald Knuth', 'Professor Emeritus of Computer Science', 'Stanford University', 'Christian Scientists & Nobel/NIH-Level Researchers (Household)', 'Stanford, California', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 71, NULL, 'Donald Knuth is one of the most celebrated computer scientists in history, often called the Father of Algorithm Analysis, and Professor Emeritus of the Art of Computer Programming at Stanford University. He is the author of the multi-volume The Art of Computer Programming, considered the bible of computer programming, and the creator of the TeX typesetting system used throughout academic publishing. Knuth is also a committed Lutheran Christian who has written Things a Computer Scientist Rarely Talks About, a theological reflection on faith and computing, and is known for donating money for errors found in his books to a Lutheran church. His extraordinary scientific legacy combined with his public Christian faith makes him one of the most intellectually distinguished Christians in the history of technology.', 'Legendary computer scientist with explicit Lutheran faith and public integration of faith into his scholarly work.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Stanford University, Gates Computer Science Building: 353 Jane Stanford Way, Stanford, CA 94305 | cs.stanford.edu/~knuth', 'Lutheran Christian who authored ''The 3:16 Bible Texts Illuminated'' and presented it to the Association of Christians in the Mathematical Sciences; National Medal of Science winner', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Creator of TeX and algorithms bible ''The Art of Computer Programming''; National Medal of Science recipient.', NULL, '["https://www-cs-faculty.stanford.edu/~knuth/bib.html#Year.1990.d", "https://engineering.stanford.edu/people/donald-knuth", "https://kavvanah.blog/2010/04/17/the-20-most-brilliant-christian-professors/"]'::jsonb),
(1077, 'KIC', NULL, 'John Suppe', 'Blair Professor of Geosciences Emeritus', 'Princeton University', 'Christian Scientists & Nobel/NIH-Level Researchers (Household)', 'Princeton, New Jersey', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 71, NULL, 'John Suppe is a geologist and one of the world''s leading structural geologists, having served as Professor of Geosciences at Princeton University for over 30 years before joining the faculty at the University of Houston. He is a Christian scientist who has been active in conversations about the relationship between faith and science, particularly in the context of geology and origins. Suppe''s combination of elite academic geology credentials and Christian faith engagement in science-faith dialogue makes him a relevant figure for GCU''s science and faith integration programs.', 'Elite Princeton geoscientist with explicit faith conversion and intellectual authority in science-faith dialogue.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Princeton University, Department of Geosciences: Guyot Hall, Princeton, NJ 08544 | princeton.edu', 'Late-life convert passionate about missions and member of American Scientific Affiliation; stated seeing ''parallels between Christian and scientific knowing''', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'U.S. National Academy of Sciences member and genius in structural geology.', NULL, '["https://www.uh.edu/nsm/earth-atmospheric/people/faculty/john-suppe/index.php", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Suppe", "https://geosciences.princeton.edu/people/john-suppe", "https://kavvanah.blog/2010/04/17/the-20-most-brilliant-christian-professors/"]'::jsonb),
(1078, 'KIC', NULL, 'Janet Mefferd', 'Former host of Janet Mefferd Today', NULL, 'Christian Talk Radio & Top Podcast Hosts', 'Dallas, Texas', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 71, NULL, 'Janet Mefferd is a nationally syndicated Christian radio host, commentator, and author who has hosted the Janet Mefferd Today program, one of the most widely heard Christian talk radio programs in America. She is a theologically conservative evangelical known for her direct engagement with theological and cultural issues facing the church, including heresy, sexual ethics, and Christian orthodoxy. Mefferd has been a consistent voice calling the evangelical church to doctrinal fidelity and has been willing to address controversial topics that other Christian media voices avoid. Her national radio platform and reputation for theological directness make her a significant voice in conservative evangelical media.', 'Prominent voice in Christian media with long track record of cultural commentary from Reformed perspective.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Janet Mefferd Today: Dallas, TX | janetmefferd.com', 'Explicitly Christian program focusing on biblical worldview and Reformed theology', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Syndicated conservative Christian talk show critiquing culture and theology.', NULL, '["https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Janet_Mefferd", "https://answersingenesis.org/bios/janet-mefferd/", "https://www.janetmefferd.com", "https://grabien.com/profile?id=4981"]'::jsonb),
(1079, 'KIC', NULL, 'Sam Brownback', NULL, 'U.S. Department of State', 'Christian US Ambassadors & Senior Diplomats', 'Topeka, Kansas', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 71, NULL, 'Sam Brownback served as Governor of Kansas from 2011 to 2018 and as a U.S. Senator from Kansas for over a decade. He is a devout Roman Catholic who converted from evangelical Protestantism and has been one of the most explicitly faith-driven politicians in recent American history. Brownback was appointed as U.S. Ambassador-at-Large for International Religious Freedom under President Trump, a role he held from 2018 to 2021, becoming one of the most prominent advocates for global religious freedom in the U.S. government. His combination of gubernatorial and Senate experience, Catholic faith, and dedicated global religious freedom advocacy make him a significant figure at the intersection of Christian conviction and American public service.', 'Contact through his public ambassadorial work on international religious freedom. Brownback served as U.S. Ambassador at Large for International Religious Freedom (2018-2021). He is based in Kansas. Contact through ADF (Alliance Defending Freedom) or through the USCIRF (U.S. Commission on International Religious Freedom) network where he is active.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: National Committee for Religious Freedom: Topeka, KS | sambrownback.com', 'Openly evangelical Christian who converted from Catholicism; frequently states ''I''m a person of faith'' in public testimony regarding his ambassadorship and religious freedom advocacy.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Led U.S. advocacy for global religious freedom and authored the International Religious Freedom Act.', NULL, '["https://www.ned.org/experts/ambassador-sam-brownback/", "https://2017-2021.state.gov/biographies/sam-brownback/", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sam_Brownback", "https://www.pepperdine.edu/newsroom/articles/ambassador-sam-brownback-joins-pepperdine-as-senior-fellow-to-advance-international-religious-freedom.htm"]'::jsonb),
(1080, 'KIC', NULL, 'Kelly Knight Craft', NULL, 'U.S. Mission to the United Nations', 'Christian US Ambassadors & Senior Diplomats', 'Lexington, Kentucky', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 71, NULL, 'Kelly Knight Craft served as U.S. Ambassador to the United Nations from 2019 to 2021 and previously as U.S. Ambassador to Canada. She is a Kentucky Republican who was appointed to both roles by President Trump. Craft is a Christian whose faith shapes her approach to public service and international engagement. She has been active in Kentucky civic and philanthropic life and has been discussed as a potential political candidate. Her combination of senior diplomatic service at the UN and Canadian embassy, Republican political connections, and Christian faith make her a relevant figure for GCU''s Kingdom Impact Council in the arena of faith and international relations.', 'Senior diplomat with explicit Baptist faith and demonstrated Christian influence on major diplomatic platforms.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: KAC Agricultural Investments / University of Kentucky Board: Lexington, KY | Phone through former UN Mission: (212) 415-4000', 'Active member of a Baptist church who gave public testimony on her Christian faith influencing diplomacy, emphasizing Judeo-Christian values in speeches.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'UN Ambassador who promoted religious freedom and Judeo-Christian values in American diplomacy.', NULL, '["https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kelly_Knight_Craft", "https://uknow.uky.edu/campus-news/uk-alumna-kelly-craft-confirmed-us-ambassador-united-nations", "https://2017-2021.state.gov/biographies/kelly-knight-craft/", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kelly_Craft"]'::jsonb),
(1081, 'KIC', NULL, 'Cathy McMorris Rodgers', NULL, NULL, 'Christian US House Members (Current & Recent)', 'Spokane, Washington', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 71, NULL, 'Cathy McMorris Rodgers served as U.S. Representative for Washington''s 5th congressional district from 2005 to 2023, rising to become Chair of the House Republican Conference — making her the highest-ranking Republican woman in House history at that time. She is an evangelical Christian whose faith has been central to her public identity and her advocacy on pro-life, religious liberty, and disability rights issues. McMorris Rodgers has a son with Down syndrome and has been a prominent advocate for individuals with disabilities. Her historic congressional leadership, evangelical faith, and disability advocacy make her a distinctive and significant figure in American Christian public life.', 'Veteran evangelical Christian with significant policy influence in technology and healthcare.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Washington State Republican Party / Spokane: 16 W Martin Luther King Jr Way, Spokane, WA 99201', 'Public testimony of evangelical faith and family values emphasis', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Long-serving congressional leader advancing tech and health policy.', NULL, '["https://ballotpedia.org/Cathy_McMorris_Rodgers", "https://energycommerce.house.gov/representatives/cathy-mcmorris-rodgers", "https://www.pewresearch.org/religion/2025/01/02/faith-on-the-hill-2025/", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cathy_McMorris_Rodgers"]'::jsonb),
(1082, 'KIC', NULL, 'Maxie Dunnam', 'Former senior pastor of Christ United Methodist Church and president of Asbury Theological Seminary', NULL, 'Eastern Orthodox, Anglican & Methodist US Leaders', 'Memphis, Tennessee', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 71, NULL, 'Maxie Dunnam is a United Methodist minister, theologian, and former President of Asbury Theological Seminary, one of the most influential evangelical theological institutions in America. He has authored over 30 books on prayer, spiritual formation, and Christian discipleship, and is widely regarded as one of the most important voices in Wesleyan-Methodist spirituality in the 20th and 21st centuries. Dunnam served as senior pastor of Christ United Methodist Church in Memphis, which grew significantly under his leadership, and has been involved in United Methodist renewal and evangelical movements within the denomination. His decades of pastoral leadership, seminary presidency, and prolific writing on Christian spiritual formation make him a major figure in evangelical Wesleyan Christianity.', 'Major Methodist educator and revival preacher who shaped evangelical Methodism through seminary leadership.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Asbury Theological Seminary (emeritus): 204 N Lexington Avenue, Wilmore, KY 40390 | asburyseminary.edu', 'UMC clergy and Asbury leader preaching Wesleyan sanctification; president of major evangelical Methodist seminary.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Methodist leader and Asbury Seminary president advancing Wesleyan theological education and revival preaching.', NULL, '["https://asburyseminary.edu/elink/celebrating-maxie-dunnams-90th-birthday/", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maxie_Dunnam", "https://worldmethodist.org/my-calling/"]'::jsonb),
(1083, 'KIC', NULL, 'Todd Harper', NULL, 'Generous Giving', 'Generous Giving & Halftime Networks', 'Washington, D.C.', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 71, NULL, 'Todd Harper is the President of Generous Giving, a nonprofit organization that inspires and equips Christians to embrace a life of generosity as a spiritual discipline and pathway to flourishing. Under his leadership, Generous Giving has grown into one of the most influential organizations shaping Christian giving culture in America, connecting major Christian donors and encouraging a generosity movement across the evangelical church. Harper is a recognized thought leader on the theology and practice of generosity and has spoken at major Christian conferences and gatherings. His work building one of the most influential Christian generosity organizations in America makes him a deeply relevant figure for GCU''s Development and philanthropy mission.', 'Missionary background and founder of major Christian generosity organization with deep evangelical roots and sustained impact.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Generous Giving: 1800 McCallie Avenue, Chattanooga, TN 37404 | Phone: (423) 755-2754 | generousgiving.org', '11 years with Campus Crusade for Christ (Cru) in Russia, Yugoslavia, and US; founded Generous Giving to advance biblical message of generosity.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Co-founding and advancing the biblical generosity message through Generous Giving for over 20 years.', NULL, '["https://www.praxis.co/people/todd-harper", "https://generousgiving.org/our-team/", "https://generousgiving.org/celebration-of-generosity-2026/cog26-welcome-todd/", "https://generousgiving.org/our-team/todd-harper/"]'::jsonb),
(1084, 'KIC', NULL, 'Justin Powell', NULL, 'Forge Leadership Network', 'Generous Giving & Halftime Networks', 'Birmingham, Alabama', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 71, NULL, 'Justin Powell is a faith-driven attorney and legal advocate with experience in the intersection of religious liberty law and Christian institutional legal defense. He has been involved in legal organizations and networks committed to defending the rights of Christian individuals, schools, and organizations in the courts. His background in Christian legal advocacy makes him a relevant figure for GCU''s Kingdom Impact Council in the arena of religious liberty and faith-based institutional legal protection.', 'Board leadership at Christian marketplace leadership development network.', 'Board member of Forge Leadership Network, Christian leadership organization committed to serving God and developing character and competence in leaders.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Board service on Forge Leadership Network, a Christian leadership development organization.', NULL, '["https://www.influencewatch.org/non-profit/forge-leadership-network/", "https://forgeleadership.org/", "https://forgeleadership.org/team/justin-powell/", "https://forgeleadership.org/about-us/"]'::jsonb),
(1085, 'KIC', NULL, 'Tim Tebow', 'Faith entrepreneur, Tim Tebow Foundation founder', 'Tim Tebow Foundation', 'Christian Athletes (Household Names)', 'St. Johns, Florida', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 69, NULL, 'Tim Tebow (born August 14, 1987, Jacksonville, Florida) won the Heisman Trophy in 2007 as the first sophomore in college football history, led the Florida Gators to two national championships, and was drafted 25th overall by the Denver Broncos in 2010. In 2026, he testified before Congress on child sex trafficking. He recently joined ESPN''s First Take. He is married to Demi-Leigh Tebow (former Miss Universe 2017) and they recently welcomed their first child. His Tim Tebow Foundation (founded 2010, St. Johns, FL) raises $10M+ annually and operates Night to Shine — a prom for 100,000+ people with special needs at 750+ churches in 30+ countries. The Foundation also funds CURE blindness surgeries, orphan care, anti-trafficking, and the Tim Tebow Ranch for foster care. He is a 5-time New York Times bestselling author. GCU has previously hosted Night to Shine events — a confirmed warm institutional relationship.

Other board roles: Tim Tebow Foundation (founder & chairman). Night to Shine National Network (founder). WaterStone Impact Fund (former). Eagle Venture Fund (former).', 'GCU already has a Night to Shine relationship — lead with that. Call Kyle Roosen (Sr. Director of Marketing) directly at the Tim Tebow Foundation: k@timtebowfoundation.org or +1 (274) 345-913. Reference GCU''s prior Night to Shine hosting. Do not go through speaking bureaus for this — use the existing institutional relationship. A call from GCU President Brian Mueller to Kyle Roosen is the right first move.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Tim Tebow Foundation: 220 County Road 210 W, St. Johns, FL 32259 | Phone: +1 (274) 345-913 | Email: k@timtebowfoundation.org (Kyle Roosen)

Tim Tebow Foundation HQ: 220 County Road 210 W, St. Johns, FL 32259. Phone: +1 (274) 345-913. Speaking: timtebow.com or AAE Speakers Bureau 1-800-698-2536 or Athlete Speakers 800-916-6008. Key staff: Kyle Roosen (Sr. Director Marketing & Comms): k@timtebowfoundation.org. Night to Shine lead Eliza Gulbransen: e@timtebowfoundation.org.', 'Founder of Tim Tebow Foundation fighting human trafficking; on-field public prayer tradition (''Tebowing''); Heisman winner known as Christian ambassador; active in sports evangelism.', 'GCU has previously hosted Night to Shine events — this is a confirmed warm institutional relationship and should be the opening line of any conversation. GCU''s Canyon Angels student anti-trafficking org also aligns directly with Tebow''s 2026 Congressional testimony on child sex trafficking.', '[]'::jsonb, '[{"date": "Apr 28, 2026", "title": "Tim Tebow named guest of honor at 2026 U.S. Venture Open charity golf event (Aug 12, 2026, Appleton WI)", "source": "WBAY News", "url": "https://www.wbay.com/2026/04/28/tim-tebow-will-be-guest-honor-2026-us-venture-open/"}, {"date": "Apr 24, 2026", "title": "Tim Tebow announces father''s death: ''He''s Home'' \u2014 Tebow''s father Robert passed away April 24, 2026", "source": "TMZ / NewsNow", "url": "https://www.newsnow.com/us/Sports/NFL/Tim+Tebow"}, {"date": "2026", "title": "Tim Tebow Foundation \u2014 Night to Shine, orphan care, anti-trafficking programs", "source": "timtebowfoundation.org", "url": "https://timtebowfoundation.org"}]'::jsonb, 'ESPN sports analyst and one of America''s most visible Christian athletes with foundation-based ministry.', 'Dear Tim,

GCU has been a proud Night to Shine host — and I''d love to find 20 minutes for you to connect with President Brian Mueller about what''s next between our organizations.

Would you or Kyle be open to a quick call?

With admiration,
[Name] | Grand Canyon University | [Phone]', '["https://www.wbay.com/2026/04/28/tim-tebow-will-be-guest-honor-2026-us-venture-open/", "https://www.newsnow.com/us/Sports/NFL/Tim+Tebow", "https://timtebowfoundation.org"]'::jsonb),
(1086, 'KIC', NULL, 'William T. Weyerhaeuser', 'Chair', 'Stewardship Foundation', 'Finance & Investing', 'Seattle, Washington', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 69, NULL, 'William T. Weyerhaeuser is a member of the Weyerhaeuser family, one of America''s most prominent timber and real estate dynasties, and a committed Christian philanthropist. The Weyerhaeuser family has deep roots in both Pacific Northwest business history and evangelical Christian philanthropy, having supported Christian causes and institutions for generations. William has been involved in Christian philanthropy and faith-driven giving that reflects his family''s multi-generational commitment to Christian institutional support. His family''s significant philanthropic history and his personal Christian faith make him a relevant figure for GCU''s Kingdom Impact Council.', 'Demonstrates sustained commitment to moving substantial family wealth toward Christian causes and Kingdom values through grantmaking leadership.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Weyerhaeuser Company (family): 220 Occidental Avenue S, Seattle, WA 98104 | weyerhaeuser.com', 'Board chair of Stewardship Foundation, an explicitly Christian grantmaking organization dedicated to poverty, reconciliation, justice, and relational evangelism.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Leading Stewardship Foundation through decades of Christian philanthropic work, surpassing $100 million in total grants with focus on Kingdom themes.', NULL, '["https://stewardshipfdn.org/our-history/", "https://stewardshipfdn.org/board-members-and-staff/", "https://www.grantmakers.io/profiles/v1/916020515-stewardship-foundation-c-d-a-b-and-w-t-weyerhaeuser-ttees/", "https://projects.propublica.org/nonprofits/organizations/916020515"]'::jsonb),
(1087, 'KIC', NULL, 'Bishop Robert Duncan', 'Founder and former Archbishop of the Anglican Church in North America', NULL, 'Eastern Orthodox, Anglican & Methodist US Leaders', 'Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 68, NULL, 'Bishop Robert Duncan served as the founding Archbishop and Primate of the Anglican Church in North America from its founding in 2009 until 2014, having previously served as Bishop of the Episcopal Diocese of Pittsburgh. He was a central figure in the conservative Anglican realignment movement in America, leading a significant portion of the Pittsburgh diocese out of The Episcopal Church over theological disputes regarding biblical authority and human sexuality. Duncan is an orthodox Anglican bishop who has been willing to bear significant institutional and legal cost for his theological convictions, representing a model of costly Christian faithfulness that GCU''s Kingdom Impact Council seeks to recognize.', 'Major Anglican leader who shaped modern traditional Anglicanism through ACNA founding and global GAFCON ties.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Anglican Church in North America: 800 Maplewood Avenue, Ambridge, PA 15003 | anglicanchurch.net', 'Anglican bishop who publicly upholds orthodox Anglican formularies including the 39 Articles; founded ACNA in 2009.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Founder of the Anglican Church in North America during historic 2009 Anglican realignment.', NULL, '["https://tas.edu/people/bob-duncan?f5d07002_page=3", "https://www.britannica.com/biography/Robert-William-Duncan", "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ULNu3b9v39g", "https://anglicanchurch.net/the-founding-of-the-acna/"]'::jsonb),
(1088, 'KIC', NULL, 'Tom Monaghan', 'Founder of Domino''s Pizza', 'Domino''s Pizza, Legatus', 'Christian Agricultural & Food Industry Executives', 'Ave Maria, Florida', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 66, NULL, 'Tom Monaghan founded Domino''s Pizza in 1960 with his brother James, purchasing a single pizza store in Ypsilanti, Michigan for $500. Over the next three decades, he built Domino''s into the world''s second-largest pizza chain with over 10,000 locations globally. In 1998, he sold his controlling stake to Bain Capital for approximately $1 billion and announced he was devoting the rest of his life to Catholic philanthropy. Monaghan founded Ave Maria University in Naples, Florida — a fully accredited Catholic university built from the ground up on his vision of orthodox Catholic education. He also founded Ave Maria School of Law and Legatus, an international organization for Catholic CEOs dedicated to studying, living, and spreading the Catholic faith in the workplace. Monaghan has donated hundreds of millions of dollars to Catholic causes, making him one of the most consequential Catholic philanthropists in modern American history.', 'Contact through Legatus (legatus.org) — the Catholic business executive network he founded. Monaghan is a devout Catholic who has funded Ave Maria University ($250M+) and Ave Maria School of Law. He is likely to respond better to Catholic institutions than evangelical ones — frame GCU''s ask carefully around shared Christian values rather than evangelical specifics. A Legatus chapter event where GCU presents would be ideal.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Ave Maria University: 5050 Ave Maria Blvd, Ave Maria, FL 34142 | Phone: (239) 280-2500 | avemaria.edu', 'Expresses Catholic faith through founding Ave Maria University and the Ave Maria School of Law, donating proceeds to Christian causes.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Domino''s founder demonstrating major Christian charitable commitment through institutional founding.', NULL, '["https://www.catholicsun.org/2013/02/18/top-catholic-business-execs-embrace-ongoing-call-to-conversion/", "https://www.osvnews.com/at-88-tom-monaghan-an-entrepreneur-and-philanthropist-still-has-unfinished-work-to-do/", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tom_Monaghan", "https://www.ewtnnews.com/world/us/catholic-businesspeople-transforming-culture-legatus"]'::jsonb),
(1089, 'KIC', NULL, 'Jeff Williams', 'NASA Astronaut (Retired)', 'NASA', 'christian_astronauts_aerospace', 'Fort Worth, Texas', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 66, NULL, 'Jeff Williams is a NASA astronaut and retired U.S. Army colonel who holds the American record for cumulative time spent in space, having logged 534 days across four missions to the International Space Station. He commanded ISS Expeditions 49 and 50 and has performed multiple spacewalks. Williams is a devout Christian who has spoken openly about how his faith shapes his perspective on the cosmos, creation, and the privilege of viewing Earth from space. He has shared his Christian testimony in interviews and at speaking engagements, stating that spending over 500 days in space has deepened rather than diminished his faith in the Creator. His extraordinary spaceflight record, military service, and public Christian faith make him one of the most accomplished Christian astronauts in NASA history.', 'Record-holding astronaut with public testimony of faith deepened by space experience.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Prestonwood Baptist Church / Dallas area ministry: 6801 W Park Blvd, Plano, TX 75093 | prestonwood.org', 'Born-again Christian who publicly stated in interviews that space reinforced his faith, deepening his awe of God''s creation from viewing Earth.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Multiple missions to the International Space Station, holding U.S. record for cumulative time in space (534 days).', NULL, '["https://www.christianpost.com/news/how-a-nasa-astronaut-found-jesus-turned-my-life-upside-down.html", "https://answersingenesis.org/bios/jeffrey-williams/", "https://www.icr.org/content/above-all-earth", "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xFExwhBXyUc"]'::jsonb),
(1090, 'KIC', NULL, 'Charlie Duke', 'Retired Astronaut and Evangelical Speaker', 'NASA', 'christian_astronauts_aerospace', 'New Braunfels, Texas', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 66, NULL, 'Charlie Duke is one of the most decorated astronauts in NASA history, having served as Lunar Module Pilot on Apollo 16 in April 1972 — becoming the tenth person and youngest person (at age 36) to walk on the moon. He spent nearly 72 hours on the lunar surface and drove the Lunar Roving Vehicle to multiple geological exploration sites. After retiring from NASA, Duke became a committed evangelical Christian and has spent decades sharing his testimony of how faith in Jesus Christ transformed his life after the pressures and fame of the Apollo program led to personal struggle. He co-founded Charlie Duke Ministries and has spoken about his faith at events worldwide. His historic moon walk, extraordinary athletic and engineering career, and dramatic post-NASA Christian testimony make him one of the most remarkable Christian stories in the history of the space program.', 'Converted to evangelical Christianity and built public ministry platform on faith testimony post-spaceflight.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Charlie Duke Enterprises: New Braunfels, TX | charlieduke.com | Phone: (830) area code', 'Converted to Christianity post-mission and became a prominent evangelical speaker, publicly testifying about his faith journey after spaceflight.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Lunar module pilot on Apollo 16 in 1972, leaving a family photo on the moon.', NULL, '["https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LQudje5EOEg", "https://americanminute.com/blogs/todays-american-minute/the-space-race-manned-space-flight-faith-of-astronauts-jesus-walking-on-the-earth-is-more-important-than-man-walking-on-the-moon-james-irwin-apollo-15-american-minute-with-bill-federer", "https://www.dukeministryforchrist.org/about", "https://compelledpodcast.com/episodes/charlie-dotty-duke"]'::jsonb),
(1091, 'KIC', NULL, 'Kevin P. Chilton', 'Retired U.S. Air Force General', 'U.S. Air Force (Former NASA Astronaut)', 'christian_astronauts_aerospace', 'Omaha, Nebraska', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 66, NULL, 'Kevin P. Chilton is a retired U.S. Air Force general and NASA astronaut who flew on three Space Shuttle missions and commanded the United States Strategic Command, the organization responsible for America''s nuclear deterrent and global strike capabilities. As a four-star general commanding STRATCOM, Chilton held one of the most consequential national security positions in the U.S. military. He is a committed Christian who has spoken about faith in the context of military service and the weight of commanding nuclear forces. His extraordinary career spanning astronaut service and four-star military command, combined with his Christian faith, makes him one of the most distinguished Christian military leaders in modern American history.', 'High-ranking military leader with public testimony of Catholic faith shaping spaceflight perspective.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: University of Nebraska (Strategic Air & Space Museum affiliation): Ashland, NE | Strategic Air Command Museum: (402) 944-3100', 'Catholic who spoke at Franciscan University about God''s providence in spaceflight, sharing how his faith shaped his perspective on space travel.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Flew three Space Shuttle missions and later commanded U.S. Strategic Command.', NULL, '["https://www.af.mil/About-Us/Biographies/Display/Article/1316843/kevin-p-chilton/", "https://www.lumen.com/en-au/about/governance/general-kevin-chilton.html", "https://www.nasa.gov/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/chilton_kevin.pdf", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kevin_P._Chilton"]'::jsonb),
(1092, 'KIC', NULL, 'Do Won Chang', 'Executive Vice Chairman', 'Forever 21', 'Consumer & Retail', 'Los Angeles, California', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 66, NULL, 'Do Won Chang is the co-founder and CEO of Forever 21, the global fast-fashion retail chain he built with his wife Jin Sook from a single women''s clothing store in Los Angeles in 1984 into a retail empire with over 800 stores worldwide at its peak. Chang is a devout evangelical Christian who prints Bible verses on the bottom of his shopping bags — John 3:16 — as a public expression of his faith. He emigrated from South Korea to the United States working multiple jobs before launching Forever 21, making his story one of the most compelling immigrant-Christian entrepreneurial narratives in American business. Despite the company''s bankruptcy filing in 2019, Chang''s decades of building a global retail brand as an openly Christian Korean-American entrepreneur give him significant standing in faith and business communities.', 'Demonstrates how explicit Christian witness integrated into consumer brand strategy can scale globally while maintaining faith values.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Forever 21 HQ: 3880 N Mission Road, Los Angeles, CA 90031 | Phone: (213) 741-5100', 'Devout evangelical Christian who printed ''John 3:16'' on every Forever 21 shopping bag for decades as a public testimony of faith.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Built Forever 21 from a single LA store in 1984 into a global fast-fashion giant with $4B+ peak sales and 800+ stores worldwide.', NULL, '["https://erply.com/do-won-chang-is-best-known-for-founding-the-clothing-retail-store-forever-21/", "https://councilka.org/cka_member/do-won-chang/", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Do_Won_and_Jin_Sook_Chang", "https://joinupdots.com/podcast/do-won-chang-the-founder-of-forever-21/"]'::jsonb),
(1093, 'KIC', NULL, 'Andy Puzder', 'CEO', 'Carl''s Jr.', 'Manufacturing & Industrial', 'Brussels, Belgium (U.S. Ambassador to EU, since Sept 2025); previously Nashville, Tennessee', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 66, NULL, 'Andrew Franklin Puzder (born July 11, 1950, Cleveland, Ohio) is an attorney, author, businessman, and current U.S. Ambassador to the European Union (confirmed and sworn in September 11, 2025). He grew up working-class Catholic in Cleveland, earned his BA from Cleveland State University and his JD from Washington University in St. Louis, then spent nearly two decades as a commercial trial lawyer. In 1986 he became personal attorney to Carl Karcher, founder of Carl''s Jr., and helped Karcher resolve serious financial difficulties. In 2000 he became CEO of CKE Restaurants — parent company of Carl''s Jr. and Hardee''s — and over 17 years grew the chain to 3,800+ restaurants globally, turning both brands into fast-food powerhouses. He was nominated by President Trump as Secretary of Labor in December 2016 but withdrew in February 2017 amid Senate confirmation difficulties. He is a devout Catholic who credits his working-class Catholic upbringing for his values. He is a Senior Fellow at the Pepperdine University School of Public Policy, a Visiting Fellow at the Heritage Foundation, a Senior Fellow at the America First Policy Institute, a board member of PragerU, and a member of the Washington University Law School Board of Advisors. He is the author of ''Job Creation: How It Really Works'' and ''The Capitalist Comeback.'' He lives with wife Deanna Descher Puzder; they have six children.

Other board roles: U.S. Ambassador to the European Union (since Sept 11, 2025). Pepperdine University School of Public Policy (Senior Fellow). Heritage Foundation (Visiting Fellow, Business and Economic Freedom). America First Policy Institute (Senior Fellow). PragerU Advisory Board. Washington University Law School Board of Advisors. State Financial Officers Foundation (National Advisory Committee). Job Creators Network (Director). 2ndVote Advisers (former Board Chairman). Reagan Institute National Leadership Council.', 'Puzder is currently serving as U.S. Ambassador to the EU in Brussels — direct outreach should wait until his term concludes or go through formal diplomatic channels. Best near-term path: contact Heritage Foundation (202-546-4400) or Pepperdine School of Public Policy (310-506-7490) to establish a relationship now so GCU is positioned for when his ambassadorship ends. His blog at andy.puzder.com has a contact form for general inquiries.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: U.S. Mission to the EU: Rond Point Robert Schuman 14, 1040 Brussels, Belgium | andy.puzder.com | Heritage Foundation: 214 Massachusetts Ave NE, Washington D.C. 20002

U.S. Mission to the European Union: useu.usmission.gov. Brussels, Belgium (current posting). For prior speaking/commentary: Heritage Foundation (202) 546-4400, heritage.org. Pepperdine School of Public Policy: (310) 506-7490. His blog/commentary: andy.puzder.com. NOTE: As active U.S. Ambassador, direct outreach should go through State Department protocol or through Pepperdine/Heritage professional channels.', 'Close friend of founder Carl Karcher; shares founder''s religious convictions and continues tradition of prayer at company location meetings', 'Puzder is a Senior Fellow at Pepperdine University — a fellow private Christian university — which is GCU''s closest peer institution among elite Christian research universities. His business expertise, faith-driven capitalism philosophy, and conservative Catholic values align strongly with GCU''s Colangelo College of Business. As his ambassadorial term concludes, a GCU post-government speaking engagement or advisory role would be well-timed.', '[]'::jsonb, '[{"date": "2026", "title": "Andrew Puzder Wikipedia \u2014 born July 11, 1950 Cleveland OH. U.S. Ambassador to EU since Sept 2025.", "source": "Wikipedia", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Andrew_Puzder"}, {"date": "Feb 17, 2026", "title": "Andrew Puzder \u2014 Federalist Society bio: Ambassador to EU, Pepperdine Senior Fellow, Heritage Foundation", "source": "Federalist Society", "url": "https://fedsoc.org/bio/andrew-puzder-1"}, {"date": "Nov 10, 2025", "title": "Andrew F. Puzder \u2014 Young America''s Foundation speaker profile", "source": "Young America''s Foundation", "url": "https://yaf.org/people/andrew-f-puzder/"}, {"date": "2025", "title": "Andy Puzder official bio and blog \u2014 CKE CEO, author, conservative commentator", "source": "andy.puzder.com", "url": "https://www.andy.puzder.com/bio"}]'::jsonb, 'CEO of major fast-food chain; maintains founder''s faith-based values and prayer tradition across company operations.', 'Dear Ambassador Puzder,

I''m reaching out from Grand Canyon University — the largest Christian university in America. Your career, your faith, and your work at Pepperdine and the Heritage Foundation are deeply admired here.

Would you be open to a brief call with GCU President Brian Mueller when your schedule allows?

With great respect,
[Name] | Grand Canyon University | [Phone]', '["https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Andrew_Puzder", "https://fedsoc.org/bio/andrew-puzder-1", "https://yaf.org/people/andrew-f-puzder/", "https://www.andy.puzder.com/bio"]'::jsonb),
(1094, 'KIC', NULL, 'Cardinal Timothy Dolan', 'Cardinal; Archbishop of New York', 'Roman Catholic Church, Archdiocese of New York', 'Catholic Public Intellectuals & Religious Figures', 'New York, New York', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 66, NULL, 'Cardinal Timothy Dolan is the Archbishop of New York, one of the most prominent Catholic positions in America, and a Cardinal of the Roman Catholic Church. He served as President of the United States Conference of Catholic Bishops from 2010 to 2013 and has been one of the most publicly visible and media-savvy Catholic leaders in the country, appearing regularly on television and maintaining a widely read blog. Dolan is known for his warm, accessible communication style and his willingness to engage secular media on Catholic teaching on life, family, and social issues. He delivered the closing prayer at the 2012 Republican National Convention and has been involved in faith-and-politics conversations across the political spectrum. His combination of Cardinal-level leadership of the New York Archdiocese, national USCCB leadership, and extraordinary media presence makes him one of the most significant Catholic public figures in America.', 'Contact through the Archdiocese of New York: archny.org or (212) 371-1000. Cardinal Dolan is one of the most publicly accessible Catholic leaders in America — he has a weekly radio show and is active on social media. A GCU interfaith leadership event or a letter from President Brian Mueller requesting a brief meeting at the USCCB annual meeting would be appropriate. Note: GCU is evangelical, not Catholic — frame around shared Christian values.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Archdiocese of New York: 1011 First Avenue, New York, NY 10022 | Phone: (212) 371-1000 | archny.org', 'Cardinal and former USCCB president (2010-2013) who has publicly proclaimed Catholic teachings through authored books and leadership of the Archdiocese of New York.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'High-profile media presence, authorship, former USCCB president, and prior leadership of the Archdiocese of New York.', NULL, '["https://www.archny.org", "https://www.osvnews.com/here-are-11-cardinals-with-american-ties-who-will-cast-votes-for-the-next-pope/", "https://www.ewtnnews.com/world/us/retiring-ny-cardinal-dolan-says-he-s-a-spiritual-granddad-now", "https://collegeofcardinalsreport.com/cardinals/timothy-michael-dolan/"]'::jsonb),
(1095, 'KIC', NULL, 'Michael Farris', 'Founder and Longtime President', 'Home School Legal Defense Association (HSLDA)', 'Christian Advocacy Attorneys', 'Purcellville, Virginia', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 66, NULL, 'Michael Farris is the founder and CEO of Alliance Defending Freedom, the largest Christian legal advocacy organization in the United States, and the founder of Patrick Henry College, a Christian liberal arts college specifically designed to train students in constitutional law, political science, and public policy from a Christian worldview. Farris has argued religious liberty cases before the Supreme Court and has been one of the most consequential figures in the Christian legal and homeschooling movements in America over the past four decades. He also co-founded the Home School Legal Defense Association, which has protected the rights of homeschooling families nationwide. His combination of founding ADF, founding Patrick Henry College, founding HSLDA, and arguing at the Supreme Court makes him one of the most institutionally consequential Christian legal advocates in modern American history.', 'Visionary founder and legal architect of the modern Christian homeschool movement with institutional reach across all 50 states.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: ADF International: 15100 N 90th Street, Scottsdale, AZ 85260 | Phone: (480) 444-0020 | adflegal.org', 'Evangelical Christian leader who founded Patrick Henry College as a training ground for Christian homeschool graduates to engage public life.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Established HSLDA in 1983, defending homeschooling rights and enabling nationwide growth of the homeschool movement.', NULL, '["https://answersingenesis.org/bios/michael-farris/", "https://dailycitizen.focusonthefamily.com/michael-farris-the-man-who-helped-save-homeschooling-in-america/", "https://ministrywatch.com/amp/largest-christian-advocacy-organizations-in-the-us/", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_Farris_(lawyer)"]'::jsonb),
(1096, 'KIC', NULL, 'Mariano Rivera', 'Church founder', 'Refugio de Esperanza', 'Christian Athletes (Household Names)', 'New Rochelle, New York', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 66, NULL, 'Mariano Rivera is widely regarded as the greatest relief pitcher in baseball history. He spent his entire 19-season career with the New York Yankees (1995–2013), compiling a record 652 saves, a career 2.21 ERA, and 13 All-Star selections. He was the first player ever unanimously elected to the Baseball Hall of Fame (2019 — 100% of votes). He was born in Panama City, Panama, and grew up in Puerto Caimito, the son of a fisherman. He is a devout Christian who credits his faith — and his famous cut fastball, which he says God showed him in a dream — for his extraordinary career. He has served as a lay pastor and preacher in his home church in New Rochelle, New York. He and wife Clara Rivera run the Mariano Rivera Foundation, which has built schools and churches in Panama and provided scholarships to thousands of students in the U.S.', 'Contact through Mariano Rivera Foundation: marianoriverafoundation.org. AAE Speakers Bureau represents him for speaking: 1-800-698-2536. Rivera is a lay preacher and actively speaks at churches and faith events — a GCU chapel address would be a natural fit. His foundation''s education mission and GCU''s college access programs for Latino students is the strongest programmatic hook.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Mariano Rivera Foundation: 30 East 29th Street, New York, NY 10016 | marianoriverafoundation.org | AAE Speakers: 1-800-698-2536

Mariano Rivera Foundation: marianoriverafoundation.org. Speaking through AAE Speakers Bureau: 1-800-698-2536. New York Yankees alumni network is a warm path.', 'Establishing church Refugio de Esperanza in New Rochelle, NY where wife Clara serves as pastor; outspoken faith commitment.', 'No direct GCU connection documented. Rivera''s Christian faith, his education mission through the Rivera Foundation, and his role as a lay preacher make him one of the most compelling chapel or commencement speakers available to a Christian university. GCU''s large Latino student population is an additional connection point.', '[]'::jsonb, '[{"date": "2026", "title": "Mariano Rivera Foundation \u2014 builds schools and churches in Panama, funds U.S. scholarships", "source": "marianoriverafoundation.org", "url": "https://marianoriverafoundation.org"}, {"date": "2026", "title": "Mariano Rivera Wikipedia \u2014 born Nov 29, 1969 Panama City. 652 career saves. First unanimous Hall of Fame inductee 2019.", "source": "Wikipedia", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mariano_Rivera"}]'::jsonb, 'Hall-of-fame MLB pitcher founding Christian church and demonstrating sustained faith-based community leadership.', 'Dear Mariano,

I''m reaching out from Grand Canyon University — the largest Christian university in America. Your story and your faith have inspired generations, including many of our students.

Would you be open to a brief call with President Brian Mueller?

With great admiration,
[Name] | Grand Canyon University | [Phone]', '["https://marianoriverafoundation.org", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mariano_Rivera"]'::jsonb),
(1097, 'KIC', NULL, 'Nikki Haley', NULL, 'U.S. Mission to the United Nations', 'Christian Political Figures', 'Bamberg, South Carolina', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 66, NULL, 'Nikki Haley served as Governor of South Carolina from 2011 to 2017 — the first female and first minority governor in the state''s history — and as U.S. Ambassador to the United Nations from 2017 to 2018 under President Trump. She is a Christian who converted from Sikhism, the religion of her Indian immigrant parents, and has spoken publicly about how her Christian faith shapes her personal values and public service. Haley was a Republican presidential candidate in the 2024 race, mounting the most sustained challenge to Donald Trump in the primary season. Her historic electoral achievements as the first female and first minority governor of South Carolina, combined with her UN ambassadorship and Christian faith, make her one of the most prominent Christian political figures in contemporary American life.', 'Globally recognized Christian leader with sustained public testimony and major influence in Republican foreign policy.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Stand for America: 1350 Avenue of the Americas, 2nd Floor, New York, NY 10019 | nikkihaley.com | WSB: wsb.com', 'Devout Christian raised Methodist, attends evangelical churches, publicly shared testimony crediting faith for strength during her governorship and UN tenure.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Prominent U.S. diplomat and household name who advocated aggressively for American interests and Christian values at the UN.', NULL, '["https://religionnews.com/2023/02/16/nikki-haley-says-shes-christian-but-its-complicated/", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nikki_Haley", "https://www1.cbn.com/thebrodyfile/archive/2010/06/03/nikki-haley-reflects-more-christian-tone", "https://www.nikkihaley.com/with-all-due-respect"]'::jsonb),
(1098, 'KIC', NULL, 'Mike Pence', NULL, NULL, 'Christian Political Figures', 'Columbus, Indiana', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 66, NULL, 'Mike Pence served as the 48th Vice President of the United States under President Trump from 2017 to 2021 and previously as Governor of Indiana. He is one of the most overtly and consistently evangelical Christian politicians in modern American history, describing himself as a Christian first, a conservative second, and a Republican third. Pence has been open about the centrality of his evangelical faith throughout his political career, citing Scripture in policy discussions and maintaining a public prayer life that has been well documented. His wife Karen Pence has been active in Christian education advocacy. Pence was a 2024 Republican presidential candidate. His combination of Vice Presidential service, gubernatorial executive experience, and the most explicitly evangelical public Christian identity of any major American politician in recent decades makes him a singular figure in the intersection of Christian faith and American political leadership.', 'Contact Washington Speakers Bureau (wsb.com) — fee range $100K+. His team is in Indianapolis, Indiana. A GCU commencement address is the most compelling use of Pence''s platform — it puts him in front of 4,000+ graduates and families with national media coverage. His evangelical identity makes GCU a natural circuit stop alongside Liberty University and other Christian institutions.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Advancing American Freedom: 801 Pennsylvania Ave SE, Suite 225, Washington, D.C. 20003 | mikepence.com | WSB: wsb.com/speakers/mike-pence

Speaking: Washington Speakers Bureau wsb.com/speakers/mike-pence, $100,000+ fee range. His personal site: mikepence.com. Indiana-based organizations are warm paths.', 'Evangelical Christian who publicly stated ''I''m a Christian, a conservative, and a Republican, in that order'' and championed conservative policies aligned with evangelical values.', 'Pence is one of the most prominent Evangelical Christian political figures in America. GCU''s strong political science and government programs, combined with its faith integration, make it a natural platform for Pence. He has spoken at Liberty University and would naturally extend to GCU as the largest Christian university in America.', '[]'::jsonb, '[{"date": "2026", "title": "Mike Pence official website \u2014 48th Vice President, speaking and policy work", "source": "mikepence.com", "url": "https://mikepence.com"}, {"date": "2026", "title": "Washington Speakers Bureau \u2014 Mike Pence speaker profile, $100K+ fee", "source": "Washington Speakers Bureau", "url": "https://www.wsb.com/speakers/mike-pence/"}, {"date": "2026", "title": "Mike Pence Wikipedia \u2014 born Jun 7, 1959 Columbus IN. 48th VP, Governor Indiana, 6-term Congressman.", "source": "Wikipedia", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mike_Pence"}]'::jsonb, 'Long-serving Indiana governor and congressman with strong evangelical credibility.', 'Dear Vice President Pence,

I''m reaching out on behalf of Grand Canyon University — the largest Christian university in America.

Would you be open to a 20-minute call with President Brian Mueller?

With great respect,
[Name] | Grand Canyon University | [Phone]', '["https://mikepence.com", "https://www.wsb.com/speakers/mike-pence/", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mike_Pence"]'::jsonb),
(1099, 'KIC', NULL, 'Blake Mycoskie', NULL, 'TOMS Shoes', 'Consumer & Retail', 'Austin, Texas', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 66, NULL, 'Blake Mycoskie was born on August 26, 1976, in Arlington, Texas. He grew up in a family of entrepreneurs — his sister is former reality TV personality Paige Mycoskie. He attended Southern Methodist University (SMU) before dropping out to launch entrepreneurial ventures, eventually appearing on The Amazing Race (2002) with his sister. While traveling in Argentina in 2006, he witnessed children without shoes and founded TOMS Shoes — short for ''Shoes for Tomorrow'' — pioneering the ''buy one, give one'' model that gave a pair of shoes to a child in need for every pair purchased. By 2013, TOMS had given over 10 million pairs of shoes to children in 60 countries. He expanded the model to TOMS Eyewear (restoring sight) and TOMS Coffee (providing clean water). In 2014 he sold 50% of TOMS to Bain Capital Partners for a reported $300 million valuation. In 2016, he went through a profound personal crisis and spiritual awakening at a Christian retreat, becoming a born-again Christian. He has spoken publicly about this transformation extensively. He later founded Madefor, a personal development and wellness platform. He lives in Los Angeles and is a sought-after speaker on conscious capitalism, purpose-driven entrepreneurship, and faith.

Other board roles: TOMS (founder, formerly). Madefor (founder). Social Enterprise Alliance (board). Conscious Capitalism (advisor).', 'Message on Instagram @blakemycoskie or through blakemycoskie.com contact form. He is accessible and entrepreneurial. Washington Speakers Bureau (wsb.com) handles his paid speaking. His 2016 faith story — born-again at a Christian retreat — means he is open to faith-university conversations. Lead with GCU''s Colangelo College of Business and servant leadership curriculum — frame him as a thought leader whose story has shaped how we teach entrepreneurship.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: TOMS / Madefor: 5404 Jandy Place, Los Angeles, CA 90066 | blakemycoskie.com | WSB: wsb.com

Speaking: Washington Speakers Bureau wsb.com. AAE Speakers Bureau: 1-800-698-2536. Personal site: blakemycoskie.com. Madefor: bemadefor.com. Active on Instagram @blakemycoskie.', 'Inspiration from Christian faith to integrate humanitarian missions into business model; pioneered mission-driven consumer brand.', 'Mycoskie''s TOMS origin story — born from a trip abroad witnessing need — is the entrepreneurial version of a GCU mission trip narrative. His faith awakening and pivot from pure commerce to conscious capitalism mirrors GCU Colangelo College of Business curriculum on values-driven leadership. His SMU connection also links him to the Dallas evangelical donor network.', '[]'::jsonb, '[{"date": "2026", "title": "Blake Mycoskie official website \u2014 TOMS founder, faith story, Madefor", "source": "blakemycoskie.com", "url": "https://blakemycoskie.com"}, {"date": "2026", "title": "Blake Mycoskie Wikipedia \u2014 born Aug 26, 1976 Arlington TX. TOMS founder, $300M Bain Capital sale 2014.", "source": "Wikipedia", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blake_Mycoskie"}, {"date": "2026", "title": "Washington Speakers Bureau \u2014 Blake Mycoskie speaker profile", "source": "Washington Speakers Bureau", "url": "https://www.wsb.com/speakers/blake-mycoskie/"}]'::jsonb, 'Pioneered the ''One for One'' model, donating shoes to needy children and sparking the conscious consumerism movement.', 'Dear Blake,

I''m reaching out from Grand Canyon University — the largest Christian university in America. Your journey is one our students need to encounter.

Would you be open to a brief call with President Brian Mueller?

With great admiration,
[Name] | Grand Canyon University | [Phone]', '["https://blakemycoskie.com", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blake_Mycoskie", "https://www.wsb.com/speakers/blake-mycoskie/"]'::jsonb),
(1100, 'KIC', NULL, 'Larry Kudlow', 'Fox Business Host, Economic Commentator', 'Fox Business', 'Recent Christian White House Senior Staff (Household)', 'Greenwich, Connecticut', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 66, NULL, 'Larry Kudlow served as Director of the National Economic Council under President Trump from 2018 to 2021, becoming one of the most prominent faces of the Trump administration''s economic policy. A longtime CNBC financial commentator and host before his White House role, Kudlow is a Catholic who has spoken openly about his faith, his recovery from cocaine addiction, and how his Catholic conversion transformed his personal life. He has been a supply-side economics advocate throughout his career and a recognizable voice in conservative economic policy circles. His combination of senior White House economic advisory experience, Catholic faith conversion story, and media platform make him a distinctive figure in the intersection of faith and economic policy.', 'High-profile Christian voice integrating faith perspective into economic and political strategy at highest levels.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Fox Business Network: 1211 Avenue of the Americas, New York, NY 10036 | Premiere Speakers: (615) 261-4000', 'Evangelical economic advisor advocating biblical stewardship; public conversion testimony: ''Christ changed my life''; hosted faith leaders on shows', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Trump National Economic Council Director who frames economic policy through evangelical Christian principles.', NULL, '["https://radio.foxnews.com/2022/05/27/larry-kudlow-a-never-ending-walk-with-god/", "https://forward.com/culture/672745/christian-nationalist-guide-influence-trump-election/", "https://www.ncregister.com/news/larry-kudlow-addiction-and-his-catholic-conversion", "https://www.catholicnewsagency.com/news/38063/larry-kudlow-on-his-conversion-addiction-and-calling-catholics-to-action"]'::jsonb),
(1101, 'KIC', NULL, 'Steve Chang', 'Leader, SOLA Network', 'SOLA Network', 'asian_american_christian_household', 'Los Angeles, California', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 66, NULL, 'Steve Chang is a technology entrepreneur and faith-driven investor with deep connections to the Asian-American Christian business community. He has been involved in organizations at the intersection of faith and entrepreneurship in the technology sector, contributing to conversations about how Christian values shape innovation, company building, and investment. His background in technology entrepreneurship and his engagement in faith-driven business communities make him a relevant figure for GCU''s entrepreneurship and technology programs.', 'Veteran Asian-American Christian pastor and thought leader influencing Asian-American evangelical discourse', 'Founding Senior Pastor of Living Hope Community Church; leader of SOLA Network; editor of *A Letter to the Asian American Church*', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Founding Living Hope Community Church and editing major anthology letter to Asian-American church', NULL, '["https://caacptsem.substack.com/p/the-confessions-of-a-one-talent-leader", "https://www.thegospelcoalition.org/profile/steve-s-chang/", "https://sola.network/article/solas-new-president-an-interview-with-steve-chang/", "https://www.livinghopecc.org/steve-chang"]'::jsonb),
(1102, 'KIC', NULL, 'Thom S. Rainer', NULL, NULL, 'Baptist Denomination Leaders (Household)', 'Nashville, Tennessee', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 66, NULL, 'Thom S. Rainer is a church growth researcher, pastor, and author who served as President and CEO of LifeWay Christian Resources, the publishing and resource arm of the Southern Baptist Convention, from 2006 to 2018. He has authored over 25 books on church growth, church revitalization, and Christian leadership, including Simple Church, co-authored with Eric Geiger, which became one of the most influential church leadership books of the 2000s. Rainer is a Southern Baptist whose decades of research on church effectiveness and his leadership of LifeWay''s publishing infrastructure have given him significant influence over how American evangelical churches think about growth, discipleship, and organizational health.', 'Major evangelical publishing leader and church consultant with wide influence on Baptist congregational health.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Church Answers: 2950 Kraft Drive, Suite 2000, Nashville, TN 37204 | Phone: (615) 266-9998 | churchanswers.com', 'Led SBC''s publishing arm producing Bible studies and curricula; authored bestsellers like *Autopsy of a Deceased Church*', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Authored bestsellers guiding church revitalization and shaped evangelical publishing through LifeWay.', NULL, '["https://churchgrowth.org/thom-rainer/", "https://www.lifeway.com/contributors/thom-s-rainer", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thom_S._Rainer", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thom_Rainer"]'::jsonb),
(1103, 'KIC', NULL, 'Linda McMahon', 'Former SBA Administrator', 'Small Business Administration / Education Department', 'Christian Cabinet Secretaries (Recent Admin)', 'Greenwich, Connecticut', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 66, NULL, 'Linda McMahon is a business executive, former CEO of WWE (World Wrestling Entertainment), and served as Administrator of the Small Business Administration under President Trump from 2017 to 2019 and again in his second term. She and her husband Vince McMahon built WWE into a global entertainment empire. McMahon is a Catholic whose faith informs her approach to public service and business leadership. Her extraordinary entrepreneurial track record building WWE, combined with her Cabinet-level experience leading the SBA, makes her a distinctive figure with both entertainment industry and federal government experience.', 'High-profile business leader with documented Catholic faith commitment and board service at Catholic institution.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Small Business Administration (former): 409 3rd Street SW, Washington, D.C. 20416 | WWE/TKO: 677 Washington Blvd, Stamford, CT 06901', 'Converted to Catholicism, served on board of Catholic Sacred Heart University', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Expanded SBA lending to small businesses and co-founded WWE.', NULL, '["https://www.ctpublic.org/news/investigative/2025-01-07/linda-mcmahon-education-experience-connecticut-history", "https://www.britannica.com/biography/Linda-McMahon", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linda_McMahon", "https://www.americafirstpolicy.com/team/lindamcmahon"]'::jsonb),
(1104, 'KIC', NULL, 'Bob Casey Jr.', 'Former U.S. Senator from Pennsylvania', NULL, 'Christian Catholic Democrats', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 0, NULL, 'Bob Casey Jr. served as U.S. Senator from Pennsylvania (2007-2025) as a Democrat. Though personally Catholic and historically pro-life, he shifted his stance and is not aligned with GCU''s evangelical Christian mission. He lost his Senate re-election bid in November 2024.', 'Not recommended for GCU outreach. Political misalignment with GCU''s evangelical Christian mission. Remove from active prospect list.', 'Pro-life Catholic Democrat highlighted in congressional profiles', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Former U.S. Senator with consistent pro-life Catholic positions in national politics.', NULL, '["https://www.cityandstatepa.com/personality/2025/08/q-former-us-sen-bob-casey/407449/", "https://www.catholicsforchoice.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/DFLFinalPDF.pdf", "https://news.scranton.edu/articles/2025/08/news-casey-fellow.shtml", "https://www.ebsco.com/research-starters/politics-and-government/robert-patrick-casey-jr"]'::jsonb),
(1105, 'KIC', NULL, 'Joe Biden', 'Former President of the United States', NULL, 'Christian Catholic Democrats', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 0, NULL, 'Joe Biden served as the 46th President of the United States (2021-2025) and is a lifelong Catholic Democrat. He is strongly pro-abortion rights and not aligned with GCU''s evangelical Christian mission or values. Included in the dataset likely due to his Catholic faith signal, but he is not an appropriate prospect for GCU''s Kingdom Impact Council.', 'Not recommended for GCU outreach. Political and values misalignment with GCU''s evangelical Christian mission. Remove from active prospect list.', 'Second Catholic U.S. President; practices Catholicism and attends Mass regularly', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Former U.S. President and second Catholic president in American history.', NULL, '["https://www.americamagazine.org/politics-society/2025/01/13/catholics-congress-249663/", "https://www.voanews.com/a/usa_biden-places-his-catholic-faith-front-and-center/6202529.html", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Catholic_Democrats", "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QmPdoQj40_E"]'::jsonb),
(1106, 'KIC', NULL, 'John Piper', 'Founder, Desiring God; pastor emeritus, Bethlehem Baptist Church', 'Desiring God Ministries', 'Christian Media Personalities & Broadcasters', 'Minneapolis, Minnesota', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 66, NULL, 'John Piper is one of the most influential Reformed evangelical pastors and theologians of the past half-century, having served as senior pastor of Bethlehem Baptist Church in Minneapolis from 1980 to 2013. He is the founder of Desiring God Ministries and the author of over 50 books, including the landmark Desiring God: Meditations of a Christian Hedonist and Don''t Waste Your Life, which have sold millions of copies and shaped evangelical theology and spirituality globally. Piper is known for his passionate, poetic preaching and his emphasis on the Christian hedonism framework — that God is most glorified in us when we are most satisfied in Him. His decades of pastoral influence, prolific authorship, and founding of Desiring God have made him one of the most read and listened-to Reformed evangelical voices in the world.', 'Household-name evangelical theologian with massive influence in Reformed circles and global missions support.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Desiring God Ministries: 2601 E Franklin Avenue, Minneapolis, MN 55406 | Phone: (888) 346-4700 | desiringgod.org', 'Reformed Baptist theologian; his signature faith declaration is ''God is most glorified in us when we are most satisfied in Him,'' driving global missions advocacy.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Founder of Desiring God ministry and pastor emeritus with prolific Christian authorship and speaking.', NULL, '["https://bcsmn.edu/profile/john-piper-2/", "https://www.desiringgod.org/about", "https://www.desiringgod.org/authors/john-piper", "https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/25423.John_Piper"]'::jsonb),
(1107, 'KIC', NULL, 'Tom Parker', 'Former Chief Justice, Alabama Supreme Court', 'Alabama Supreme Court', 'Christian State Supreme Court Justices (Household)', 'Montgomery, Alabama', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 66, NULL, 'Tom Parker serves as Chief Justice of the Alabama Supreme Court and has been a prominent voice for explicitly Christian jurisprudence in American law. In a landmark 2024 ruling, Parker wrote the opinion declaring frozen embryos to be children under Alabama law — a decision that cited biblical and Christian theological sources as legal authority and sent shock waves through the national reproductive law debate. Parker is an evangelical Christian who has been explicit about his view that American law should be grounded in Christian natural law principles. His willingness to explicitly cite Christian theology in judicial opinions from the highest court in Alabama makes him one of the most distinctive figures in the intersection of Christian conviction and American jurisprudence.', 'Former Chief Justice with prominent Christian judicial philosophy and biblical reasoning applied to consequential state law.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Alabama Supreme Court: 300 Dexter Avenue, Montgomery, AL 36104 | Phone: (334) 229-0700 | alacourt.gov', 'Longtime Southern Baptist who has publicly cited biblical principles in judicial opinions, referencing the Alabama Constitution''s acknowledgment of God as Creator.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '2024 ruling upholding Alabama''s ban on in vitro fertilization based on embryo personhood, aligning with Christian pro-life views.', NULL, '["https://fedsoc.org/bio/tom-parker", "https://1819news.com/news/item/chief-justice-tom-parker-retiring-after-20-years-of-difference-making-service", "https://www.jsu.edu/academicaffairs/office-of-the-provost/al-supreme-court.html", "https://judicial.alabama.gov/CourtMemberBio/ViewBio?id=3"]'::jsonb),
(1108, 'KIC', NULL, 'Russell Moore', 'Host of The Russell Moore Show, Editor-in-Chief of Christianity Today', 'Christianity Today', 'christian_advocates_activists', 'Nashville, Tennessee', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 66, NULL, 'Russell Moore is the Editor in Chief of Christianity Today, the flagship magazine of evangelical Christianity founded by Billy Graham, and one of the most respected and influential voices in contemporary evangelical Christianity. He previously served as President of the Ethics and Religious Liberty Commission of the Southern Baptist Convention from 2013 to 2021. Moore is a Southern Baptist theologian and cultural commentator who has been willing to speak with intellectual honesty about difficult questions facing the evangelical church, including its relationship to political power and racial justice. His combination of leading Christianity Today, his SBC ethics leadership, and his willingness to challenge evangelical cultural assumptions make him one of the most thoughtful and consequential voices in American evangelical Christianity.', 'Prominent Christian voice shaping evangelical political strategy and moral deliberation on faith-informed issues.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Christianity Today: 465 Gundersen Drive, Carol Stream, IL 60188 | Phone: (630) 260-6200 | russellmoore.com', 'Advises on faith-political engagement; influential in evangelical policy; authored books like ''Onward'' on Christian witness; public testimony and writings', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Led the SBC''s ethics and religious liberty advocacy, advocating on abuse survivor support and religious freedom.', NULL, '["https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russell_D._Moore", "https://www.christianitytoday.com/ct/podcasts/russell-moore-show/", "https://www.baptistpress.com/resource-library/news/russell-moore-announces-departure-from-erlc-helm/", "https://www.christianitytoday.com/"]'::jsonb),
(1109, 'KIC', NULL, 'Marvin Olasky', 'Editor', 'World News Group', 'christian_journalism_punditry', 'Austin, Texas', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 66, NULL, 'Marvin Olasky is the Editor in Chief Emeritus of World magazine, the most widely read evangelical news magazine in America, which he led for decades and built into the primary alternative to secular mainstream media for evangelical Christians. He is also a journalism professor and author of multiple books including The Tragedy of American Compassion, which influenced President George W. Bush''s faith-based initiatives policy. Olasky is a former atheist and communist who converted to evangelical Christianity through reading the Bible, one of the most dramatic intellectual conversion stories in modern American Christianity. His combination of leading World magazine, influencing national social policy through his writing, and his dramatic conversion story make him a significant figure in evangelical media and cultural commentary.', 'Respected Christian thought leader shaping education policy discourse through faith-integrated public commentary.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: World News Group: P.O. Box 20002, Asheville, NC 28802 | Phone: (828) 435-2980 | wng.org', 'Presbyterian elder and author of *The Tragedy of American Compassion*, applying biblical principles to welfare and schooling critiques.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Pioneered ''compassionate conservatism'' and journalism on Christian social reform, including education policy.', NULL, '["https://www.christianitytoday.com/2024/12/marvin-olasky-joins-christianity-today-as-executive-editor-of-news-and-global/", "https://www.discovery.org/p/olasky/", "https://www.thegospelcoalition.org/article/from-mad-marxist-to-compassionate-conservative/", "https://www.boundless.org/blog/five-questions-with-world-magazine-editor-in-chief-marvin-olasky/"]'::jsonb),
(1110, 'KIC', NULL, 'Francine Rivers', 'Author', NULL, 'Cross-Industry (Authors with Crossover Reach)', 'Northern California (specific city private)', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 66, NULL, 'Francine Rivers is one of the best-selling Christian fiction authors in history, having sold over 30 million books globally. Her novel Redeeming Love, a retelling of the story of Hosea set in the Gold Rush era, is widely considered a landmark of Christian literature and has been made into a feature film. Rivers is a committed Christian whose conversion transformed her from a secular romance novelist to a faith-driven literary voice. Her work has introduced millions of readers to Christian themes of redemption, grace, and sacrificial love through compelling narrative fiction. Her extraordinary commercial and cultural impact in Christian fiction makes her one of the most significant Christian creative voices of the past three decades.', 'Household-name Christian author known for theologically rich fiction that shapes evangelical readership.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Tyndale House Publishers (c/o): 351 Executive Drive, Carol Stream, IL 60188 | francinerivers.com', 'Rivers wrote her first book explicitly to proclaim her Christian faith, integrating biblical themes in works like the Mark of the Lion series.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Over 20 bestselling novels including RITA and Christy Award winners with mainstream crossover reach.', NULL, '["https://freshfiction.com/author.php?id=9040", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Francine_Rivers", "https://www.encyclopedia.com/arts/educational-magazines/rivers-francine-1947", "https://www.godtube.com/blog/top-15-christian-fiction-authors.html"]'::jsonb),
(1111, 'KIC', NULL, 'Simon Conway Morris', 'Paleontologist, University of Cambridge (emeritus)', 'University of Cambridge', 'Cross-Industry (Awards & Recognition Lists)', 'Cambridge, England, UK', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 66, NULL, 'Simon Conway Morris is a Professor of Evolutionary Palaeobiology at Cambridge University and one of the world''s leading paleontologists, known primarily for his work on the Cambrian Explosion and the concept of evolutionary convergence. He is a committed Anglican Christian who has been one of the most prominent scientist-believers willing to engage publicly with questions about faith, evolution, and the nature of life. Morris has authored Life''s Solution: Inevitable Humans in a Lonely Universe, which argues that the trajectory of evolution points toward inevitable complexity and mind — a finding he connects to a theistic understanding of the cosmos. His combination of Cambridge academic standing, landmark paleontological research, and public Christian faith engagement make him one of the most distinguished Christian scientists in the world.', 'Elite scientist integrating Christian faith with evolutionary biology; addresses misconception of faith-science conflict at highest academic levels.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: University of Cambridge, Department of Earth Sciences: Downing Street, Cambridge CB2 3EQ, UK | cam.ac.uk', 'Committed Anglican Christian who argues for compatibility of evolution and Christianity in writings like ''The Crucible of Creation.''', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Discoveries in evolutionary convergence; 2026 Templeton Prize winner.', NULL, '["https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Simon_Conway_Morris", "https://www.templetonprize.org/laureate/professor-simon-conway-morris/", "https://www.templetonprize.org", "https://www.joh.cam.ac.uk/research/academics/fellows/simon-conway-morris"]'::jsonb),
(1112, 'KIC', NULL, 'Derek Schuurman', 'Professor Emeritus of Computer Science', 'Redeemer University', 'Education', 'Ancaster, Ontario, Canada', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 66, NULL, 'Derek Schuurman is a Professor of Computer Science at Calvin University, a Christian liberal arts university in Grand Rapids, Michigan, and one of the most thoughtful voices on the integration of Christian faith and computing. He is the author of Shaping a Digital World: Faith, Culture and Computer Technology, which explores how Christians should think about technology from a Reformed theological perspective. Schuurman is a committed Calvinist whose work at the intersection of computer science and Christian theology makes him a relevant figure for GCU''s growing emphasis on faith-integrated technology education.', 'Senior academic mentor shaping Christian professionals'' approach to technology ethics and moral reasoning in emerging AI field.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Redeemer University: 777 Garner Road East, Ancaster, ON L9K 1J4, Canada | redeemer.ca', 'Taught at Redeemer University (Christian liberal arts college); mentors Christian AI engineers from faith-informed perspective on technology''s moral non-neutrality', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Professor Emeritus mentoring next-generation Christian AI engineers to view technology development through moral and theological framework.', NULL, '["https://www.christiancourier.ca/author/derek-schuurman1/", "https://sites.calvin.edu/derek/bio.html", "https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=QYvH2M4AAAAJ&hl=en", "https://calvin.edu/people/derek-schuurman"]'::jsonb),
(1113, 'KIC', NULL, 'Art Ally', NULL, 'Timothy Plan', 'Finance & Investing', 'Maitland, Florida', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 66, NULL, 'Art Ally is the founder of the Timothy Plan, one of the oldest and largest biblically responsible investment fund families in the United States, which he founded in 1994 with the conviction that Christians should not unknowingly invest in companies whose business practices violate biblical values. The Timothy Plan screens out companies involved in abortion, pornography, alcohol, tobacco, gambling, and anti-family entertainment. Ally''s founding of the Timothy Plan helped launch the modern biblically responsible investing movement, which has grown into a multi-billion dollar sector of the asset management industry. His decades of pioneering work making it possible for Christians to invest according to their values make him one of the most consequential figures in the history of faith-driven finance.', 'Created foundational infrastructure for faith-driven investing that shaped entire industry category; demonstrates early Christian leadership in financial innovation.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Timothy Plan: 1055 Maitland Center Commons, Suite 310, Maitland, FL 32751 | Phone: (800) 846-7526 | timothyplan.com', 'Pioneered biblically responsible investing in 1992; designed first faith-aligned screening criteria for investment portfolios driven by Christian conviction.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Founding Timothy Plan, operating biblically responsible investing for over 25 years with conviction that faith should guide investment principles.', NULL, '["https://timothyplan.com/about-us/our-story.php", "https://timothyplan.com/", "https://timothyplan.com/about-us/our-team.php", "https://timothyplan.com/about-us/biography-art-ally.php"]'::jsonb),
(1114, 'KIC', NULL, 'David Luttrell', NULL, 'Generous Giving', 'Generous Giving & Halftime Networks', 'Dallas, Texas', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 66, NULL, 'Providing public testimony on Christian generosity and serving on the board of Generous Giving. Featured in video testimony "David and Keelie Luttrell" on Journey of Generosity; board member of Christian generosity organization. Board service at major Christian generosity network with public testimony demonstrating commitment to biblical stewardship.', 'Board service at major Christian generosity network with public testimony demonstrating commitment to biblical stewardship.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Generous Giving: 1800 McCallie Avenue, Chattanooga, TN 37404 | Phone: (423) 755-2754 | generousgiving.org', 'Featured in video testimony "David and Keelie Luttrell" on Journey of Generosity; board member of Christian generosity organization.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Providing public testimony on Christian generosity and serving on the board of Generous Giving.', NULL, '["https://generousgiving.org/our-team/", "https://db.ministrywatch.com/ministry.php?ein=582556775", "https://outreachmagazine.com/features/23877-generous-church-culture.html", "https://projects.propublica.org/nonprofits/organizations/582556775"]'::jsonb),
(1115, 'KIC', NULL, 'Jonathan Jakubowski', NULL, 'Forge Leadership Network', 'Generous Giving & Halftime Networks', 'Bowling Green, Ohio', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 66, NULL, 'Jonathan Jakubowski is a faith-driven author and advocate whose book Bellwether Blues documents the social and cultural decline of working-class communities and calls for faith-based responses to their challenges. He is a committed Christian whose writing connects Christian social teaching with practical advocacy for vulnerable communities. His work at the intersection of faith, economics, and community development makes him a relevant voice for GCU''s programs in Christian social engagement and community impact.', 'Board leadership at Christian marketplace leadership development network.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Forge Leadership Network: 4220 Hazel Ave, Suite 300, Fair Oaks, CA 95628 | forgeleaders.com', 'Board member of Forge Leadership Network, Christian leadership organization committed to serving God and developing conviction, character, and competence.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Board service on Forge Leadership Network, a Christian leadership development organization.', NULL, '["https://www.sourcewatch.org/index.php/Forge_Leadership_Network", "https://www.influencewatch.org/non-profit/forge-leadership-network/", "https://forgeleadership.org/team/jonathan-jakubowski/", "https://forgeleadership.org/about-us/"]'::jsonb),
(1116, 'KIC', NULL, 'Dick DeVos', NULL, 'Windquest Group; Amway (family legacy)', 'Major Christian Philanthropists & Donors', 'Grand Rapids, Michigan', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 66, NULL, 'Richard ''Dick'' DeVos Jr. (born October 21, 1955, Grand Rapids, Michigan) is the son of Amway co-founder Richard DeVos and one of America''s most influential Christian philanthropists. He served as President of Amway Corporation (1993–2002), presiding over international expansion to 50+ countries and tripling international sales. He co-founded Windquest Group, a Grand Rapids investment firm where he serves as Chairman. He previously served as President and CEO of the Orlando Magic NBA franchise (1991–1993). He is married to Betsy DeVos, who served as U.S. Secretary of Education under President Trump (2017–2021). Together they lead the Dick and Betsy DeVos Family Foundation (est. 1989), one of the largest Christian philanthropic foundations in America, which funds school choice, Christian education, arts, and community development. Family net worth estimated at $5B+. Dick also founded the West Michigan Aviation Academy, a charter school for underserved students interested in aviation careers.

Other board roles: Windquest Group (Chairman). Amway/Alticor (Board, 2019-present). Orlando Magic NBA (Board, 1994-present). American Enterprise Institute (Board of Trustees, 2017-present). West Michigan Aviation Academy (Founder & Board President). Dick & Betsy DeVos Family Foundation (Chairman, 1989-present).', 'Contact through Windquest Group (616-454-4500) in Grand Rapids, MI. Betsy DeVos (his wife, former Secretary of Education) is the warmer initial pathway given her education focus — contact her through Windquest or through American Federation for Children (federationforchildren.org) where she is active. AEI board events (where Dick is a trustee) are another warm access path. The DeVos family receives many education-focused pitches — lead with GCU''s specific financial accessibility numbers ($9,500/yr tuition) as the hook.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Windquest Group: 201 Monroe Ave NW, Suite 500, Grand Rapids, MI 49503 | Phone: (616) 454-4500

Windquest Group HQ: 201 Monroe Ave NW, Suite 500, Grand Rapids, MI 49503. Phone: (616) 454-4500. Personal website: dickdevos.com. LinkedIn: linkedin.com/in/dickd. AEI: 1789 Massachusetts Ave NW, Washington D.C. 20036, (202) 862-5800.', 'Member of Christian Reformed Church; donates millions to Acton Institute and other faith-based policy groups', 'Betsy DeVos (former Secretary of Education) has been the nation''s top advocate for school choice and Christian education access — GCU''s model of affordable, faith-based private education at under $10,000/yr is the living argument for school choice at university scale. The AEI board connection offers a conservative academic warm intro path.', '[]'::jsonb, '[{"date": "2026", "title": "Dick DeVos official bio \u2014 Chairman Windquest Group, Amway President, Orlando Magic", "source": "dickdevos.com", "url": "https://dickdevos.com/about/"}, {"date": "2026", "title": "Dick DeVos LinkedIn \u2014 active profile", "source": "LinkedIn", "url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/dickd/"}, {"date": "2026", "title": "Windquest Group \u2014 DeVos family private investment firm, Grand Rapids MI", "source": "Windquest Group", "url": "https://www.windquest.com"}]'::jsonb, 'Co-founder of Windquest Group (Amway heir) who supports Christian education and conservative faith-aligned policy organizations.', 'Dear Dick,

I''m reaching out from Grand Canyon University — the largest Christian university in America.

I''d love to find 20 minutes for you and Betsy to connect with President Brian Mueller. Would that be possible?

With great respect,
[Name] | Grand Canyon University | [Phone]', '["https://dickdevos.com/about/", "https://www.linkedin.com/in/dickd/", "https://www.windquest.com"]'::jsonb),
(1117, 'KIC', NULL, 'Patrick H. Brady', 'Board of Directors member', 'National Medal of Honor Museum', 'Military & Veterans', 'Texas (San Antonio area)', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 66, NULL, 'Major General and Medal of Honor recipient who completed over 2,500 combat missions and authored books on military valor. Publicly attributes success to faith, stating "Success is born of courage alone, and God has made this marvelous gift infinitely available to all who ask for it." Senior flag officer integrating explicit faith messaging into leadership of premier military honor institution.', 'Senior flag officer integrating explicit faith messaging into leadership of premier military honor institution.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: National Medal of Honor Museum: 757 N Harbor Drive, San Diego, CA 92101 | mohmuseum.org | Medal of Honor Society: (843) 884-8862', 'Publicly attributes success to faith, stating "Success is born of courage alone, and God has made this marvelous gift infinitely available to all who ask for it."', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Major General and Medal of Honor recipient who completed over 2,500 combat missions and authored books on military valor.', NULL, '["https://mohmuseum.org/recipient/brady-patrick-henry", "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fZvnN50Kv9k", "https://evergreenpodcasts.com/medal-of-honor/landing-in-a-minefield-mg-patrick-henry-brady", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patrick_Henry_Brady"]'::jsonb),
(1118, 'KIC', NULL, 'Mike Krzyzewski', NULL, 'Duke University', 'NCAA Christian Coaches & Athletic Leadership', 'Durham, North Carolina', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 66, NULL, 'Mike Krzyzewski, known universally as Coach K, is the most decorated men''s college basketball coach in history, having led the Duke Blue Devils for 42 years before retiring in 2022 with 1,202 wins — the most in Division I men''s basketball history. He also coached the U.S. Men''s National Basketball Team to three Olympic gold medals. Krzyzewski is a Catholic whose faith has shaped his philosophy of leadership, team culture, and mentorship. He has spoken about how his Catholic upbringing and values of loyalty, commitment, and service have been the foundation of the legendary Duke basketball program culture. His extraordinary coaching legacy, Catholic faith, and reputation as one of the greatest leadership teachers in American sports make him a uniquely compelling figure for GCU''s Kingdom Impact Council.', 'Contact Washington Speakers Bureau (wsb.com) — fee $100K+. CAA Speakers also represents him. Coach K''s brand is leadership, not religion — frame GCU''s ask around leadership development, not faith specifically. A GCU commencement or major leadership summit is the right venue. His West Point/military background gives GCU''s veteran student population a natural connection point.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Duke University Athletics / Cameron Indoor Stadium: 115 Whitford Drive, Durham, NC 27708 | coachk.com | WSB: wsb.com

Speaking: Washington Speakers Bureau wsb.com, fee $100,000+. Duke University, Durham, NC: duke.edu. Official site: coachk.com. CAA Speakers also represents him.', 'Recognized as one of the best-known Christian coaches', 'No direct GCU connection documented. Coach K''s West Point background aligns with GCU''s large veteran and military student population. His leadership speaking circuit and GCU''s emphasis on servant leadership make him a natural commencement or leadership conference speaker.', '[]'::jsonb, '[{"date": "2026", "title": "Coach K official website \u2014 5 NCAA championships, 3 Olympic gold medals, 1,202 wins at Duke", "source": "coachk.com", "url": "https://coachk.com"}, {"date": "2026", "title": "Washington Speakers Bureau \u2014 Coach K speaker profile, $100K+ fee", "source": "Washington Speakers Bureau", "url": "https://www.wsb.com/speakers/mike-krzyzewski/"}, {"date": "2026", "title": "Mike Krzyzewski Wikipedia \u2014 born Feb 13, 1947 Chicago IL. West Point graduate. Most wins in NCAA basketball history.", "source": "Wikipedia", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mike_Krzyzewski"}]'::jsonb, 'Legendary Duke basketball coach since 1980 with recognized Christian leadership legacy.', 'Dear Coach K,

I''m reaching out from Grand Canyon University — the largest Christian university in America. Your career and leadership philosophy have influenced how we develop leaders here.

Would you be open to a brief call with President Brian Mueller?

With great respect,
[Name] | Grand Canyon University | [Phone]', '["https://coachk.com", "https://www.wsb.com/speakers/mike-krzyzewski/", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mike_Krzyzewski"]'::jsonb),
(1119, 'KIC', NULL, 'Steve Donaldson', NULL, 'Convoy of Hope', 'Nonprofits & Foundations', 'Springfield, Missouri', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 66, NULL, 'Steve Donaldson is a faith-driven business leader and philanthropist active in Christian executive networks and marketplace ministry communities. He has been involved in organizations that connect senior Christian business leaders for theological formation, mutual accountability, and Kingdom-oriented business practice. His commitment to integrating Christian faith with business leadership and his involvement in Christian philanthropic networks make him a relevant figure for GCU''s Kingdom Impact Council.', 'Built large-scale faith-driven humanitarian response demonstrating Christian compassion in practice.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Convoy of Hope: 330 S Patterson Avenue, Springfield, MO 65802 | Phone: (417) 823-8998 | convoyofhope.org', 'Co-founder of Convoy of Hope, a Christian organization founded by the Donaldson family dedicated to ''give help, share hope'' through faith-driven disaster response.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Co-founder of 1994 nonprofit that grew into global force delivering food, supplies, and aid to millions in crises, hunger, and poverty.', NULL, '["https://impactful.ninja/best-christian-charities-making-an-impact/", "https://news.ag.org/Article-Repository/Authors/Steve-Donaldson", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Convoy_of_Hope", "https://convoyofhope.org/articles/best-christian-charities/"]'::jsonb),
(1120, 'KIC', NULL, 'Ronald Regensteif', NULL, 'Chosen People Ministries', 'Regional/Specialty Ministry Boards', 'Chatsworth, California', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 66, NULL, 'Ronald Regensteif is a faith-driven business leader and philanthropist with deep connections to the Christian business and philanthropic community. He has been involved in Christian stewardship and generosity networks that equip Christian business leaders to deploy their wealth for Kingdom purposes. His engagement in Christian philanthropic communities makes him a relevant figure for GCU''s Kingdom Impact Council as it seeks to build relationships with Christian donors and business leaders.', 'Successful business founder providing marketplace leadership and financial stewardship to major Jewish evangelism ministry.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Chosen People Ministries: 241 E 51st Street, New York, NY 10022 | Phone: (212) 223-2252 | chosenpeople.com', 'Board member of Chosen People Ministries, Jewish evangelism ministry.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Founded Regency Enterprises (energy conservation) in 1981 and co-founded Regency Lighting; business executive serving on ministry board.', NULL, '["https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CsgFcWPGofE", "https://www.biblicalleadership.com/podcasts/3-humility-and-generosity-in-life-and-leadership-guest-ron-regenstreif-founderformer-ceo-of-regency-lighting/", "https://chosenpeople.com/about/leadership/", "https://www.regencysupply.com/about-regency-supply/leadership-team/ron-regenstreif/"]'::jsonb),
(1121, 'KIC', NULL, 'Henry Kaestner', 'Co-Founder and Partner, Sovereign''s Capital', 'Sovereign''s Capital; Faith Driven Investor', 'Technology', 'Chapel Hill, North Carolina', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 66, NULL, 'Henry Kaestner is a serial entrepreneur and co-founder of Faith Driven Entrepreneur, the global movement that has created communities, content, and infrastructure for Christian entrepreneurs in over 80 countries. He previously co-founded Bandwidth Inc., a cloud communications company that went public on NASDAQ, and the Sovereign''s Capital investment firm. Kaestner is a committed Christian whose entrepreneurial journey and public faith witness have made him one of the most recognized faces of the faith-driven entrepreneurship movement globally. He is also an author and podcast host whose content on integrating faith with entrepreneurship has reached tens of thousands of Christian founders. His combination of tech entrepreneurship success, movement building, and global reach in the Christian founder community make him one of the most significant figures in contemporary faith-driven business.', 'Contact through Sovereign''s Capital or Faith Driven Investor network: faithdrivenentrepreneur.org. Kaestner is very active in the faith-and-business space and speaks at Christian entrepreneurship conferences regularly. A GCU Colangelo College of Business partnership or Faith Driven Entrepreneur campus chapter is the right conversation. He is based in Chapel Hill, NC.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Sovereign''s Capital: 250 E Franklin Street, Suite 400, Chapel Hill, NC 27514 | sovereignscapital.com', 'Co-founded Faith Driven Movements, a non-profit ministry serving faith-driven entrepreneurs across 6 continents and 140+ countries; explicitly identified as a ''Faith Driven Entrepreneur'' in organizational leadership.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Pioneering faith-driven venture capital model that invests exclusively in faith-aligned businesses tackling global poverty and education challenges.', NULL, '["https://faithdrivenentrepreneur.org/episode-279-is-the-church-winning-with-henry-kaestner-and-justin-forman/", "https://faithdrivenentrepreneur.org/books/", "https://greenmoney.com/build-give-invest-a-framework-thats-worth-the-risk/", "https://sovereignscapital.com/"]'::jsonb),
(1122, 'KIC', NULL, 'Cardinal Wilton D. Gregory', 'Archbishop Emeritus of Washington', 'Roman Catholic Church, Archdiocese of Washington', 'US Catholic Bishops & Cardinals', 'Washington, D.C.', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 66, NULL, 'Cardinal Wilton D. Gregory is the Archbishop of Washington, D.C. — one of the most prominent Catholic positions in America — and the first African American Cardinal in U.S. history, elevated to the College of Cardinals by Pope Francis in 2020. He previously served as Archbishop of Atlanta and as President of the United States Conference of Catholic Bishops from 2001 to 2004. Gregory''s historic elevation as the first Black Cardinal in U.S. history represents a landmark moment in American Catholic history and African American religious leadership. His combination of leading the Washington Archdiocese, national USCCB leadership, and historic significance as the first Black American Cardinal make him one of the most consequential figures in contemporary American Catholicism.', 'Historic figure as first African-American U.S. cardinal with extensive leadership experience in national Catholic governance.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Archdiocese of Washington: P.O. Box 29260, Washington, D.C. 20017 | Phone: (301) 853-4500 | adw.org', 'Ordained bishop in 1983; first African-American cardinal from the U.S., demonstrating long commitment to Catholic hierarchy and leadership with participation in papal conclaves.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'First African-American cardinal from the U.S. and former USCCB president (2001-2004) with longest tenure among recent U.S. cardinals.', NULL, '["https://www.osvnews.com/here-are-11-cardinals-with-american-ties-who-will-cast-votes-for-the-next-pope/", "https://collegeofcardinalsreport.com/cardinals/wilton-daniel-gregory/", "https://news.wttw.com/2025/05/06/meet-10-us-cardinals-who-will-vote-next-pope", "https://www.britannica.com/biography/Cardinal-Wilton-Gregory"]'::jsonb),
(1123, 'KIC', NULL, 'Robert H. Maclellan', 'Vice Chairman, Secretary and Treasurer', 'Maclellan Foundation Inc.', 'Christian Foundations', 'Chattanooga, Tennessee', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 64, NULL, 'Robert H. Maclellan is a faith-driven philanthropist and member of the Maclellan Foundation, one of the most significant Christian foundations in the United States. The Maclellan Foundation, based in Chattanooga, Tennessee, has distributed hundreds of millions of dollars to Christian causes with a particular focus on Christian organizations seeking to fulfill the Great Commission globally. The family''s philanthropic legacy spans generations and reflects a deep commitment to funding the spread of the Gospel through mission, education, and ministry. His family''s extraordinary philanthropic heritage and his personal Christian faith commitment make him a highly relevant figure for GCU''s major gift and partnership strategy.', 'Multi-decade philanthropic track record directing $400M+ in assets explicitly to Christ-centered Kingdom work.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Maclellan Foundation: 820 Broad Street, Suite 300, Chattanooga, TN 37402 | Phone: (423) 755-1366 | maclellan.net', 'Family foundations affirm commitment to ''serve those advancing Christ''s Kingdom around the globe'' via Christian causes.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'From Provident Life Insurance founding family, overseeing family foundations with ~$400 million in assets giving ~$30 million annually.', NULL, '["https://www.grantmakers.io/profiles/v0/237159802-robert-l-and-kathrina-h-maclellan-foundation/", "https://www.grantmakers.io/profiles/v0/626041468-maclellan-foundation-inc/?page=2", "https://projects.propublica.org/nonprofits/organizations/237159802", "https://maclellan.net/history/"]'::jsonb),
(1124, 'KIC', NULL, 'Bishop Robert Schnase', 'Former Bishop of the Rio Texas Conference', NULL, 'Eastern Orthodox, Anglican & Methodist US Leaders', 'San Antonio, Texas', NULL, NULL, 'medium', true, 64, NULL, 'Bishop Robert Schnase is a United Methodist bishop and author whose books on congregational vitality, including Five Practices of Fruitful Congregations, have been used by thousands of United Methodist and other Protestant churches to strengthen their discipleship and outreach. He served as Bishop of the Missouri Area of the United Methodist Church and has been a recognized voice in United Methodist renewal and church growth conversations. His combination of episcopal leadership and widely-used congregational development resources make him a relevant figure in the broader Protestant church leadership ecosystem.', 'Influential Methodist bishop with significant institutional impact on UMC congregational life and practices.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Rio Texas Conference UMC (retired): 816 Camaron Street, San Antonio, TX 78212 | riotexas.org', 'UMC bishop whose writings promote Methodist discipleship and covenant groups; author of *Five Practices of Fruitful Congregations*.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Methodist bishop and church-growth author whose resources are widely used across United Methodist churches.', NULL, '["https://riotexas.org/news/2024/3/28/reflections-with-robert-schnase-bishop-easter-2024", "https://riotexas.org", "https://robertschnase.com", "https://riotexas.org/news/2019/2/28/a-message-from-robert-schnase-bishop-of-the-rio-texas-annual-conference"]'::jsonb),
(1125, 'KIC', NULL, 'Matt Harris', 'Investment team member', 'Draper Associates', 'Faith-Driven Investing & Marketplace Networks', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 53, NULL, 'Matt Harris is a faith-driven venture capital investor and managing director at Bain Capital Ventures, where he focuses on fintech and financial services investments. He is a prominent figure in the Faith Driven Investor network and has written and spoken extensively about integrating Christian faith with investment practice at the highest levels of institutional capital. Harris brings a rare combination of Ivy League credentials, top-tier venture track record, and explicit Christian faith commitment to the conversation about how capital can be deployed for both financial return and Kingdom impact. His presence in faith-aligned investor circles represents the growing movement of Wall Street professionals who believe their fiduciary responsibilities and their faith are not in conflict but are mutually reinforcing.', 'Institutional investor integrating Christian conviction with capital; bring Wall Street credibility to faith-driven marketplace.', 'Featured on Faith Driven Investor podcast discussing faithful investing alongside father Britt Harris', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Former Vice President at Blackstone; now at Draper Associates; featured on Faith Driven Investor podcast.', NULL, '["https://open.spotify.com/episode/2LTJ5P0Tyu8fA9zgS1caWy", "https://faithdriveninvestor.org/marks-on-the-markets/", "https://faithdriveninvestor.org/episode-135-father-son-and-faithful-investing/", "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=x5Odg3U176Y"]'::jsonb),
(1126, 'KIC', NULL, 'Scott Turner', 'Nominee for Secretary of Housing and Urban Development', 'Trump Administration (second term)', 'Christian Political Figures (Current & Recent Former)', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 53, NULL, 'Former NFL player and Texas House Representative nominated for HUD Secretary with pastor credentials. Serves as an associate pastor at Prestonwood Baptist Church in Plano, Texas, and stated, ''Two things that my parents taught me: My mother taught me how to have a tremendous faith in the Lord Jesus.'' Federal appointee with integrated faith-based ministry leadership and political executive experience.', 'Federal appointee with integrated faith-based ministry leadership and political executive experience.', 'Serves as an associate pastor at Prestonwood Baptist Church in Plano, Texas, and stated, ''Two things that my parents taught me: My mother taught me how to have a tremendous faith in the Lord Jesus.''', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Former NFL player and Texas House Representative nominated for HUD Secretary with pastor credentials.', NULL, '["https://www.ncronline.org/news/trumps-cabinet-selections-represent-unusual-slice-american-religious-life", "https://www.christianitytoday.com/2025/01/donald-trump-nominees-cabinet-rubio-hegseth/", "http://www.hud.gov/news/hud-no-25-025", "http://www.hud.gov/aboutus/leadership/scott-turner"]'::jsonb),
