(1138, 'KIC', NULL, 'Sean Duffy', 'Secretary of Transportation', 'U.S. Department of Transportation', 'Christian Cabinet Secretaries (Recent Admin)', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 47, NULL, 'Sean Duffy is a Republican politician, television personality, and Fox Business host who served as a U.S. Representative for Wisconsin''s 7th congressional district from 2011 to 2019. He is a devout Catholic and father of nine children with his wife Rachel Campos-Duffy, also a prominent conservative media figure. Duffy was named Secretary of Transportation by President Trump in his second term. He is known for his public Catholic faith, his vocal pro-life advocacy, and his integration of faith into his public service. His large family, Catholic identity, and high-profile media presence make him a recognizable figure at the intersection of faith, family values, and conservative public policy.', 'Catholic leader with publicly demonstrated family values rooted in faith commitment.', 'Practicing Catholic who cited family values in resigning from House', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Former Wisconsin congressman and Fox host with large family advocating for family-centered values.', NULL, '["https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sean_Duffy", "https://www.deseret.com/faith/2024/11/17/jd-vance-religion-marco-rubio-religion/", "https://abcnews.com/GMA/News/transportation-secretary-sean-duffy-defends-new-road-trip/story?id=132840754", "https://www.transportation.gov/office-of-secretary"]'::jsonb),
