(1165, 'KIC', NULL, 'Chandler Moore', 'Worship Leader', 'Maverick City Music', 'Christian Musicians & Worship Leaders', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 46, NULL, 'Chandler Moore is a worship leader, singer-songwriter, and recording artist known for his landmark work with Maverick City Music, the Atlanta-based collective that has transformed contemporary Christian worship. He co-wrote and performed Jireh, one of the most streamed worship songs of the 2020s, which reached No. 1 on multiple Christian music charts and introduced millions of listeners to a more intimate, gospel-inflected worship style. Moore is an ordained minister who brings pastoral depth to his music, and his work with Maverick City has been widely credited with bridging racial and denominational divides within the American church. His continued work with Maverick City places him among the most influential voices in contemporary Christian music, with particular impact on younger generations of worshipers.', 'Worship leader whose raw authenticity and church leadership shape contemporary worship.', 'Leads at Champion Church, shares raw faith expressions in music.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Worship leader with innovative gospel worship anthems.', NULL, '["https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=joSy_pITYSo"]'::jsonb),
(1166, 'KIC', NULL, 'Bob Castellini', 'Principal owner, Cincinnati Reds (MLB)', 'Cincinnati Reds', 'Christian Pro Sports Team Owners & GMs', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 46, NULL, 'Bob Castellini is the principal owner and chairman of the Cincinnati Reds Major League Baseball franchise, having led a group that purchased the team in 2006. He is a devout Catholic and prominent Cincinnati civic leader whose faith shapes his approach to team ownership and community investment. Castellini also serves as chairman of Castellini Company, one of the largest fresh produce distributors in the United States, a business his family has operated for generations. His combination of professional sports ownership, multi-generational family business leadership, and documented Catholic faith makes him a relevant figure for GCU''s Kingdom Impact Council, particularly as it relates to the intersection of Christian values and professional sports franchise stewardship.', 'Major MLB owner with demonstrated Catholic faith integrated into business operations and charitable giving.', 'Devout Catholic who supports Christian charities and has spoken at faith-based events about God''s role in his business.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Stabilized Reds ownership and led major ballpark developments transforming Cincinnati baseball.', NULL, '["https://www.sportsspeakers360.com/blog/christian-athletes"]'::jsonb),
