(1179, 'KIC', NULL, 'Timothy Dalrymple', 'President', 'John Templeton Foundation', 'Nonprofits & Foundations', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 46, NULL, 'Led multi-year transformation of Christianity Today that reenvisioned the historic evangelical media property and expanded its global reach. Appointed president of John Templeton Foundation in July 2025; previously led Christianity Today, the historic evangelical media property, as CEO. Bridges evangelical leadership and major philanthropic foundation work supporting religion and science intersection.', 'Bridges evangelical leadership and major philanthropic foundation work supporting religion and science intersection.', 'Appointed president of John Templeton Foundation in July 2025; previously led Christianity Today, the historic evangelical media property, as CEO.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Led multi-year transformation of Christianity Today that reenvisioned the historic evangelical media property and expanded its global reach.', NULL, '["https://www.templeton.org/team-member/timothy-dalrymple", "https://ministrywatch.com/tim-dalrymple-leaves-christianity-today/", "https://www.templeton.org/news/john-templeton-foundation-appoints-timothy-dalrymple-as-president", "https://www.templeton.org/about/our-team"]'::jsonb),
(1180, 'KIC', NULL, 'Joe Gibbs', 'Retired NFL coach, NASCAR team owner', 'Joe Gibbs Racing', 'Christian Athletes (Household Names)', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 45, NULL, 'Three Super Bowl wins as Redskins coach and building a top NASCAR team with multiple championships. Devout evangelical Christian who hosts Bible studies for his team and authored "Game Plan for Life"; openly credits Jesus for his success. Iconic household-name former Super Bowl coach and active NASCAR owner with overt evangelical faith embedded in team culture and authored Christian leadership.', 'Iconic household-name former Super Bowl coach and active NASCAR owner with overt evangelical faith embedded in team culture and authored Christian leadership.', 'Devout evangelical Christian who hosts Bible studies for his team and authored "Game Plan for Life"; openly credits Jesus for his success.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Three Super Bowl wins as Redskins coach and building a top NASCAR team with multiple championships.', NULL, '["https://www.gameplanforlife.com/about-coach-gibbs", "https://www.billygraham.ca/stories/joe-gibbs-journey-with-god/", "https://www.beliefnet.com/celebrity-faith-database/g/joe-gibbs.aspx", "https://www.sportsspeakers360.com/blog/christian-athletes"]'::jsonb),
(1181, 'KIC', NULL, 'Daniel P. Amos', 'Former CEO (1990-2023)', 'Aflac Incorporated', 'Cross-Industry (Fortune 500 Christian Executives)', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 45, NULL, 'Joe Gibbs is one of the most accomplished coaches in NFL history, having led the Washington Redskins to three Super Bowl championships across four Super Bowl appearances with three different starting quarterbacks — a feat unmatched in NFL history. He was inducted into the Pro Football Hall of Fame in 1996. After his first retirement from coaching, Gibbs founded Joe Gibbs Racing, which became one of the most successful NASCAR teams ever, winning multiple championships. Gibbs is a devout evangelical Christian who has spoken openly about his faith throughout his career, hosting Bible studies for his football players and NASCAR team, and authoring Game Plan for Life, a book on Christian principles of living. He founded the Youth For Tomorrow ministry in Virginia, which provides residential care and counseling for at-risk youth. His extraordinary athletic achievement across two major sports, combined with his consistent evangelical Christian witness and meaningful ministry work, make him one of the most distinguished Christian sports figures in American history.', 'Retired long-serving CEO with decades of faith-driven leadership in Fortune 500; publicly integrated Scripture into corporate principles.', 'United Methodist whose company principles in ''The Aflac Way'' are derived from Scripture, as described by his son Paul S. Amos II in an interview with Duke Divinity School''s Faith and Leadership program.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'CEO of Aflac since 1990, building it into a major supplemental insurance provider with industrial-scale operations.', NULL, '["https://www.businessroundtable.org/members/dan-amos", "https://faithandleadership.com/paul-s-amos-not-who-we-are", "https://www.georgiahistory.com/bio/daniel-p-amos/", "https://news.ambest.com/newscontent.aspx"]'::jsonb),
(1182, 'KIC', NULL, 'Tony Dungy', 'Former co-owner and executive, Indianapolis Colts (NFL)', 'Indianapolis Colts', 'Christian Athletes (Household Names)', 'Tampa, Florida', NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 45, NULL, 'Hall of Fame coaching career including a Super Bowl win with the Indianapolis Colts; nationally recognized Christian author and speaker. Prominent Christian author and speaker ("Quiet Strength"); frequently testifies about Jesus shaping his leadership; active in Bible studies and NFL chaplaincy work. Iconic household-name former coach and owner with deep evangelical faith publicly woven into mentoring, authorship, and sports leadership.', 'Iconic household-name former coach and owner with deep evangelical faith publicly woven into mentoring, authorship, and sports leadership.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Athletes in Action / Speaking: Indianapolis, IN | Washington Speakers Bureau: wsb.com | Twitter: @TonyDungy', 'Prominent Christian author and speaker ("Quiet Strength"); frequently testifies about Jesus shaping his leadership; active in Bible studies and NFL chaplaincy work.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Hall of Fame coaching career including a Super Bowl win with the Indianapolis Colts; nationally recognized Christian author and speaker.', NULL, '["https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tony_Dungy", "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hOJD-pJewaM", "https://www.ewtnnews.com/world/us/who-is-tony-dungy-the-nfl-hall-of-fame-coach-speaking-at-the-march-for-life", "https://bleacherreport.com/articles/962060-the-25-most-religious-athletes"]'::jsonb),
(1183, 'KIC', NULL, 'Drew Brees', 'Retired NFL quarterback', NULL, 'Christian Athletes (Household Names)', 'New Orleans, Louisiana', NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 45, NULL, 'Tony Dungy is one of the most celebrated coaches in NFL history, serving as head coach of the Tampa Bay Buccaneers and Indianapolis Colts over a 13-year career. He became the first Black head coach to win a Super Bowl when he led the Colts to victory in Super Bowl XLI in 2007. Dungy is among the most outspoken Christian figures in professional sports, authoring multiple bestselling books including Quiet Strength, which chronicles how his faith sustained him through personal tragedy and professional success. He is a vocal pro-life advocate, a prison ministry supporter, and a mentor to dozens of NFL players and coaches. After retiring from coaching, Dungy became an NBC Sports analyst and continued to use his platform to speak openly about his Christian faith, making him one of the most enduring examples of faith-integrated leadership in American sports.', 'Contact AAE Speakers Bureau (1-800-698-2536) or through Brees Dream Foundation (breesdreamfoundation.org). Brees is now a media personality (NBC Sports) — his team is accessible through standard booking channels. A GCU chapel or commencement address is the right venue. His New Orleans/Louisiana roots make Arizona a less natural geography — a strong event concept is essential.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Brees Dream Foundation: 6301 Perkins Road, Baton Rouge, LA 70808 | breesdreamfoundation.org | AAE Speakers: 1-800-698-2536

Brees Dream Foundation: breesdreamfoundation.org. Speaking through AAE Speakers Bureau: 1-800-698-2536 or aaespeakers.com. NBC Sports / NFL Network for media inquiries.', 'Listed among high-profile retired outspoken Christians using platform for Jesus; prominent in Christian athlete circles.', 'No direct GCU connection documented. Brees'' faith, athletic excellence, and philanthropic work in education and community development align strongly with GCU''s mission. A GCU chapel or commencement speech would be highly compelling for GCU''s large sports-connected student body.', '[]'::jsonb, '[{"date": "2026", "title": "Brees Dream Foundation \u2014 $50M+ committed to education and recreation in New Orleans, San Diego, West Lafayette", "source": "breesdreamfoundation.org", "url": "https://breesdreamfoundation.org"}, {"date": "2026", "title": "Drew Brees Wikipedia \u2014 born Jan 15, 1979 Dallas TX. NFL career passing yards record 80,358. Super Bowl XLIV champion.", "source": "Wikipedia", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drew_Brees"}]'::jsonb, 'Super Bowl-winning NFL quarterback and hall-of-fame player with public Christian faith witness.', 'Dear Drew,

I''m reaching out from Grand Canyon University — the largest Christian university in America. What you''ve built on and off the field resonates deeply here.

Would you be open to a brief call with President Brian Mueller?

With great admiration,
[Name] | Grand Canyon University | [Phone]', '["https://breesdreamfoundation.org", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drew_Brees"]'::jsonb),
