(1240, 'KIC', NULL, 'Richard Zhang', 'Engineer at Google DeepMind', 'Google DeepMind', 'Christian Tech Leaders', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 42, NULL, 'Started Global Christians in AI collective with 250 subscribers and initiated Bible studies at Google to integrate Christian perspective into AI research. Founded the Global Christians in AI collective with 250 subscribers to support faith in ethical AI and started Bible studies at Google. Young tech leader building grassroots Christian networks at major AI companies, shaping faith-informed AI ethics from inside the industry.', 'Young tech leader building grassroots Christian networks at major AI companies, shaping faith-informed AI ethics from inside the industry.', 'Founded the Global Christians in AI collective with 250 subscribers to support faith in ethical AI and started Bible studies at Google.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Started Global Christians in AI collective with 250 subscribers and initiated Bible studies at Google to integrate Christian perspective into AI research.', NULL, '["https://chaiglobal.ai/about", "https://aiandfaith.org/member/richard-zhang/", "https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=mE11hO8AAAAJ&hl=en", "https://qiuyiz.github.io"]'::jsonb),
(1241, 'KIC', NULL, 'Doug McMillon', 'CEO, Walmart', 'Walmart (Fortune 1)', 'Fortune 500 Christian CEOs', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 42, NULL, 'Doug McMillon has served as President and CEO of Walmart since 2014, leading the world''s largest company by revenue with over 2.3 million employees and $650 billion in annual sales. McMillon grew up in Arkansas and started his Walmart career unloading trucks as a teenager, eventually rising to the top job through a career spanning three decades. He is a Christian whose faith informs his leadership philosophy and his emphasis on servant leadership, a concept he has cited publicly in discussing how he approaches managing the world''s largest private employer. McMillon has pushed Walmart toward significant investments in workforce development, sustainability, and community impact — priorities shaped in part by values rooted in his faith background.', 'Household-name Fortune 1 CEO whose Christian faith informs values-driven leadership at scale.', 'Known for Christian faith through public affiliations and alignment with values-driven leadership.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Leading Walmart since 2014, expanding e-commerce and global reach as CEO of the world''s largest retailer.', NULL, '["https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=L92hTBPD4-E", "https://chiefexecutive.net/bring-religious-values-work/", "https://faithdrivenentrepreneur.org/live-with-the-end-in-mind-doug-mcmillon-ceo-of-walmart/", "https://treeleafpartners.com/2024/05/29/christian-ceos-leaders/"]'::jsonb),
(1242, 'KIC', NULL, 'Clayton Kershaw', 'MLB pitcher', 'Kershaw''s Challenge', 'Christian Athletes (Household Names)', 'Dallas, Texas', NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 42, NULL, 'Clayton Kershaw is widely considered the greatest pitcher of his generation, spending his entire MLB career with the Los Angeles Dodgers (2008–2024). He is an 8-time All-Star, 3-time NL Cy Young Award winner (2011, 2013, 2014), 2014 NL MVP, and World Series champion (2020). He attended Highland Park High School in Dallas, Texas. He and wife Ellen Kershaw are devout Christians who co-founded Kershaw''s Challenge, a charitable foundation dedicated to serving orphans in Zambia, Rwanda, Los Angeles, and the Dominican Republic. The foundation has raised over $50 million. Kershaw has spoken widely about his Christian faith and how it defines his identity beyond baseball. He graduated from Highland Park High School in Dallas, Texas, where he was classmates with Matthew Stafford.', 'Contact Kershaw''s Challenge directly: kershawschallenge@kershawschallenge.com or kershawschallenge.com. AAE Speakers Bureau (1-800-698-2536) or Athlete Speakers (800-916-6008) handle speaking. Kershaw is based in Dallas, Texas — his evangelical Dallas roots are a natural GCU connection. Lead with Kershaw''s Challenge + GCU nursing/healthcare students serving children internationally.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Kershaw''s Challenge: P.O. Box 250249, Plano, TX 75025 | Email: kershawschallenge@kershawschallenge.com | AAE Speakers: 1-800-698-2536

Kershaw''s Challenge: kershawschallenge.com. Contact: kershawschallenge@kershawschallenge.com. Speaking through AAE Speakers Bureau or Athlete Speakers: 800-916-6008.', 'Speaks at Calvary Chapel about Christian charity and missions in Africa; co-founded Kershaw''s Challenge with wife Ellen focused on charitable/mission work.', 'No direct GCU connection documented. Kershaw''s faith, Dallas roots, and orphan care mission through Kershaw''s Challenge align with GCU''s ministry ethos. GCU''s large student body of sports fans plus its faith integration make Kershaw a natural chapel or commencement speaker.', '[]'::jsonb, '[{"date": "2026", "title": "Kershaw''s Challenge \u2014 $50M+ raised for orphans in Zambia, Rwanda, Dominican Republic, and Los Angeles", "source": "kershawschallenge.com", "url": "https://kershawschallenge.com"}, {"date": "2026", "title": "Clayton Kershaw Wikipedia \u2014 born Mar 19, 1988 Dallas TX. 3\u00d7 Cy Young, NL MVP 2014, World Series champion 2020.", "source": "Wikipedia", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clayton_Kershaw"}]'::jsonb, 'Hall-of-fame MLB pitcher with sustained Christian mission work and charitable platform.', 'Dear Clayton,

I''m reaching out from Grand Canyon University — the largest Christian university in America. You and Ellen''s work through Kershaw''s Challenge is deeply admired here.

Would you be open to a brief call with President Brian Mueller?

With great admiration,
[Name] | Grand Canyon University | [Phone]', '["https://kershawschallenge.com", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clayton_Kershaw"]'::jsonb),
(1243, 'KIC', NULL, 'Patrick Lencioni', 'Founder of The Table Group; Author and speaker', 'The Table Group (founder)', 'Christian Business / Leadership Thought-Leaders', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 42, NULL, 'Patrick Lencioni is a business consultant, speaker, and author of some of the most widely read business books of the past two decades, including The Five Dysfunctions of a Team and The Advantage, which have collectively sold millions of copies and are standard reading in MBA programs globally. Lencioni is a devout Catholic who is open about how his faith shapes his approach to organizational health, vulnerability, and the purpose of work. He founded The Table Group, a consulting firm focused on organizational health, and speaks regularly to both secular and Christian business audiences. His position as a mainstream business thought leader whose work is explicitly grounded in Catholic Christian values makes him a powerful bridge between the corporate world and the faith community.', 'Household-name business consultant whose faith-centered approach to organizational health has shaped corporate culture across industries.', 'Openly Catholic, integrates Christian principles throughout business leadership books and consulting with tech firms.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Bestselling author of leadership books like ''The Five Dysfunctions of a Team'' widely used by tech executives including Intel.', NULL, '["https://fortune.com/2014/11/11/7-ceos-with-notably-devout-religious-beliefs/", "https://www.tablegroup.com/pat/", "https://premierespeakers.com/speakers/patrick-lencioni"]'::jsonb),
(1244, 'KIC', NULL, 'Rachel Cruze', 'Co-Host and Personal Finance Expert, Ramsey Solutions', 'Ramsey Solutions', 'Christian Business / Leadership Thought-Leaders', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 42, NULL, 'Personal finance expert and author of *Know Yourself, Know Your Money* co-hosting on Ramsey Solutions team. Integrates biblical principles in teachings, noting ''God''s Word is the ultimate authority on money'' in her content. Influential Christian financial educator whose faith-centered approach to money shapes young leaders'' stewardship practices.', 'Influential Christian financial educator whose faith-centered approach to money shapes young leaders'' stewardship practices.', 'Integrates biblical principles in teachings, noting ''God''s Word is the ultimate authority on money'' in her content.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Personal finance expert and author of *Know Yourself, Know Your Money* co-hosting on Ramsey Solutions team.', NULL, '["https://johnolearyinspires.com/podcast/archive/live-inspired-podcast-s8-ep-83-rachel-cruze-ramsey-personality-financial/", "https://themayanah.com/about-us/", "https://music.amazon.com/podcasts/1ffe57ad-873d-455e-81f2-1b0850c0d198/the-rachel-cruze-show", "https://www.youtube.com/rachelcruze"]'::jsonb),
(1245, 'KIC', NULL, 'Craig Hill', 'Chairman', 'Hume Lake Christian Camps', 'Christian Camps, Retreats & Conference Center Boards', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 42, NULL, 'Craig Hill is the founder of Family Foundations International, a ministry that conducts seminars on biblical family principles in over 60 countries, reaching hundreds of thousands of people annually. He is a bestselling author whose books including The Ancient Paths and Marriage: Cover or Control have been translated into dozens of languages. Hill''s work focuses on healing family and generational patterns through the application of biblical truth, and his seminars are known for producing dramatic personal and relational transformation. His global reach, pastoral depth, and focus on the foundational role of family in building healthy societies makes him directly relevant to GCU''s mission, which similarly values faith-formation at the family and community level.', 'Senior governance role at established Christian camping ministry with significant market reach.', 'Chairman of the Board of Directors at Hume Lake Christian Camps', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Board leadership at major Christian camp organization serving youth and families.', NULL, '["https://fuller.edu/adjunct/craig-hill/", "https://faithdrivenentrepreneur.org/craig-hill/", "https://hume.org/about-hume/", "https://craighill.org/about/"]'::jsonb),
(1246, 'KIC', NULL, 'Ree Drummond', 'Food Network star and blogger', 'Pioneer Woman Media', 'Christian Culinary, Wellness & Lifestyle (Household)', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 42, NULL, 'Ree Drummond is the creator of The Pioneer Woman, a lifestyle brand encompassing a food and lifestyle blog, multiple New York Times bestselling cookbooks, a long-running Food Network television series, a magazine, and a retail store in Pawhuska, Oklahoma. Drummond is a Christian who weaves her faith, family values, and rural Oklahoma life naturally into her brand and public persona, making her one of the most widely followed Christian lifestyle influencers in America. Her Food Network show has been one of the network''s most popular programs for over a decade, and her blog was at one point the most-read food blog in the world. Her ability to build a massive mainstream media platform while maintaining an authentic Christian family identity makes her a compelling example of faith-integrated brand building at scale.', 'Household name with unparalleled reach in culinary and lifestyle space, authentically integrating Christian worldview.', 'Writes openly about evangelical Christian faith, including church involvement and devotionals on her blog', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Building a massively popular blog and TV empire inspiring home cooking for millions with faith-centered values.', NULL, '["https://www.movieguide.org/news-articles/pioneer-woman-loves-serving-her-churchs-childrens-ministry.html", "https://www.wideopencountry.com/ree-drummond-faith/", "https://thepioneerwoman.com/", "https://www.thepioneerwoman.com/ree-drummond-life/a61139874/ree-drummond-childrens-time-church-stories/"]'::jsonb),
(1247, 'KIC', NULL, 'Bill High', 'CEO, The Signatry', 'The Signatry', 'Christian Finance & Investment Leaders', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 42, NULL, 'Bill High serves as CEO of the National Christian Foundation, one of the largest Christian philanthropic organizations in the United States, which has facilitated over $15 billion in charitable giving since its founding. NCF provides donor-advised funds, gift planning, and generosity coaching to Christian donors, enabling individuals and families to give more strategically to Kingdom causes. High is also an author and speaker on generational legacy, biblical stewardship, and family philanthropy. His position at the helm of a $15 billion Christian giving infrastructure makes him one of the most influential figures in Christian philanthropic circles, with deep relationships across major Christian donors, foundations, and ministry organizations nationwide.', 'Prominent Christian finance leader directing major organization focused on strategic kingdom-aligned giving.', 'Directs organization dedicated to Christian charitable giving and stewardship, leading faith-based philanthropic advising', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Leader in faith-based philanthropic advising and stewardship.', NULL, '["https://thesignatry.com/our-story/", "https://ministrywatch.com/amp/the-signatry-helps-connect-doers-and-donors/", "https://www.wealthbuilders.org/10-iconic-christians-in-business/", "https://www.finishlinepledge.com/episode103/"]'::jsonb),
(1248, 'KIC', NULL, 'Bear Grylls', 'Chief Scout', 'The Scouts', 'Christian Humanitarian & Mission Celebrities', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 42, NULL, 'Bear Grylls is one of the world''s most recognizable adventurers and survival experts, best known as the host of Man vs. Wild on Discovery Channel and subsequent survival series that have aired in over 200 countries. He is a former British Special Air Service soldier who survived a freefall parachuting accident that broke his back in three places, after which he made a full recovery and went on to climb Mount Everest. Grylls is an outspoken Christian who has written extensively about how his faith sustains him through extreme physical and emotional challenges, authoring Soul Fuel, a daily devotional, and speaking regularly about the centrality of Jesus in his life. He served as Chief Scout of the United Kingdom''s Scout Association. His combination of global household-name status, extreme achievement, and genuine public Christian witness makes him one of the most effective ambassadors for the message that faith and courage are inseparable.', 'Household-name media personality leveraging massive audience for evangelical youth and missions advocacy.', 'Evangelical Christian stating, ''My faith is my backbone... Jesus is everything to me.''', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Adventure TV personality promoting outdoor missions and youth discipleship through media influence.', NULL, '["https://www.beargrylls.com", "https://www.premierchristianity.com/interviews/bear-grylls-sharing-the-story-of-jesus-is-the-proudest-thing-ive-ever-done/19621.article", "https://www.liberty.edu/news/2025/10/15/tv-host-bear-grylls-tells-tale-of-true-adventure-through-faith/", "https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/bear-grylls-russell-brand-chief-scout-baptism-b2563151.html"]'::jsonb),
(1249, 'KIC', NULL, 'Josiah Queen', 'Singer-Songwriter', 'Provident Label Group', 'Christian Musicians & Worship Leaders', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 42, NULL, 'Josiah Queen is a worship leader, songwriter, and artist known for his work in the contemporary Christian worship space, with associations with Maverick City Music and other prominent worship collectives that have reshaped evangelical and charismatic worship culture in the 2020s. Queen represents the generation of young Black worship artists who have brought gospel sensibility, authenticity, and depth to the broader Christian worship movement, attracting both Black church and multiethnic audiences. His music and ministry presence make him a relevant voice for GCU''s student population, particularly in connecting faith with contemporary cultural expression.', 'Rising household-name artist with viral reach and commitment to church ministry.', 'Preaches at churches, shares testimony of leaving baseball for ministry.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Young viral worship hits like ''The Prodigal.''', NULL, '["https://www.josiahqueen.com", "https://music.youtube.com/@josiahqueenmusic", "https://open.spotify.com/artist/7yAymwuYh9RcpX84GSNIq2"]'::jsonb),
(1250, 'KIC', NULL, 'Naomi Raine', 'Singer', 'Maverick City Music', 'Christian Musicians & Worship Leaders', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 42, NULL, 'Naomi Raine is a Grammy Award-nominated worship leader and singer-songwriter best known for her landmark work with Maverick City Music, the Atlanta-based collective that has become one of the most influential forces in contemporary Christian music. She co-wrote and performed on multiple songs from Maverick City''s Grammy-winning projects, and her voice and songwriting have helped define the collective''s distinctive blend of gospel, R&B, and contemporary Christian influences. Raine is an ordained minister whose musical gifts and pastoral heart make her one of the most compelling worship voices of her generation, with particular influence in multiethnic and younger church communities.', 'Rising household-name artist shaping contemporary worship and reaching diverse audiences.', 'Performs at multicultural churches, testifies to God''s provision.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Genre-blending worship with Maverick City Music like ''Jireh.''', NULL, '["https://www.christianitytoday.com/2025/10/naomi-raine-maverick-city-music-jesus-over-everything/", "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sQwUD__WMD0", "https://www.naomirainemusic.com/bio"]'::jsonb),
(1251, 'KIC', NULL, 'Frank Chen', 'Partner at Faith Driven Entrepreneur', 'Faith Driven Entrepreneur', 'Christian Tech Leaders', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 42, NULL, 'Frank Chen is a Silicon Valley technology executive with deep connections to the faith-driven technology community. He has served in senior roles at Andreessen Horowitz, one of the world''s most influential venture capital firms, where he focused on AI and enterprise technology. Chen is a Christian who is active in the intersection of faith and technology, participating in networks and conversations about how Christian values should shape the development and deployment of artificial intelligence and emerging technologies. His combination of top-tier venture capital experience, AI expertise, and Christian faith makes him a distinctive figure as GCU develops its own AI and technology programs.', 'Tech investor shaping Christian founder ecosystem through direct capital and mentorship at major faith-tech organization.', 'Co-leads organization explicitly supporting Christian entrepreneurs in tech and investing in faith-aligned ventures.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Invests in faith-aligned tech ventures and bridges Christian entrepreneurship with Silicon Valley innovation.', NULL, '["https://faithdrivenvestor.org/podcast-episode-5-the-investor-as-a-servant-leader-with-frank-chen-of-andreessen-horowitz/", "https://www.riotimesonline.com/silicon-valleys-christian-revival-techs-new-power-players-seek-meaning-and-morals/", "https://faithdriveninvestor.org/bios/frank-chen/", "https://faithdrivenentrepreneur.org/frank-chen/"]'::jsonb),
(1252, 'KIC', NULL, 'Chris Pratt', 'Major Hollywood actor', NULL, 'christian_creators_arts', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 42, NULL, 'Chris Pratt is one of Hollywood''s most bankable stars, known for his leading roles in the Guardians of the Galaxy franchise, Jurassic World, and The Tomorrow War. He is among the most openly Christian actors in mainstream Hollywood, attending Zoe Church in Los Angeles and speaking candidly about his faith in interviews, awards speeches, and on social media. Pratt used his MTV Generation Award acceptance speech to deliver an explicit Christian message to mainstream audiences, encouraging viewers to pray, read Scripture, and seek God. His willingness to openly profess his faith in environments generally hostile to evangelical Christianity, combined with his A-list box office status, makes him one of the most impactful Christian voices in contemporary popular culture.', 'Major cultural figure leveraging enormous mainstream platform to advance Christian testimony.', 'Well-known Christian celebrity who routinely speaks about Jesus at public events; told MTV audience ''God is real. God loves you''', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Mainstream A-list actor using Hollywood platform for consistent public Christian witness', NULL, '["https://www.mariashriversundaypaper.com/chris-pratt-faith/", "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7nyEtP8ocZA", "https://cbn.com/news/entertainment/chris-pratt-shares-moment-he-turned-jesus-and-chose-never-look-back-its-where-my", "https://www.pureflix.com/insider/18-christian-celebrities-who-are-changing-show-business"]'::jsonb),
(1253, 'KIC', NULL, 'Christian Pulisic', 'Professional soccer player', 'AC Milan / U.S. men''s national team', 'Elite & Olympic Athletes', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 42, NULL, 'Christian Pulisic is one of America''s most accomplished soccer players, serving as captain of the U.S. Men''s National Team and playing professionally for AC Milan in Serie A after stints at Chelsea FC and Borussia Dortmund. He is a vocal Christian who credits his faith for grounding him through the pressures of professional soccer at the highest levels, speaking in interviews about the peace he finds in his relationship with Jesus. Pulisic has become the face of American soccer''s growing international prominence, and his combination of elite athletic achievement, national team captaincy, and public Christian witness makes him one of the most prominent young Christian athletes in American sports.', 'Elite current athlete with global platform using soccer prominence to publicly share faith.', 'Listed among prominent Christ-following athletes using his platform to share faith publicly.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Captain of the USMNT and key figure in MLS-to-Europe success at AC Milan.', NULL, '["https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Christian_Pulisic", "https://www.acmilan.com/en/teams/men-first-team/players/christian-pulisic/statistics", "https://sportsspectrum.com/sport/2026/01/01/13-christ-following-athletes-to-watch-in-2026/", "https://www.espn.com/soccer/player/_/id/225607/christian-pulisic"]'::jsonb),
(1254, 'KIC', NULL, 'Britt Harris', 'President, CEO, and CIO', 'UTIMCO', 'Faith-Driven Investing & Marketplace Networks', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 42, NULL, 'President, CEO, and CIO of UTIMCO; featured on Faith Driven Investor podcast. Featured as faith-driven investor on Faith Driven Investor podcast discussing faithful investing Large endowment leader practicing faith-aligned investing; big-title executive integrating Christian conviction with capital stewardship.', 'Large endowment leader practicing faith-aligned investing; big-title executive integrating Christian conviction with capital stewardship.', 'Featured as faith-driven investor on Faith Driven Investor podcast discussing faithful investing', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'President, CEO, and CIO of UTIMCO; featured on Faith Driven Investor podcast.', NULL, '["https://mays.tamu.edu/directory/britt-harris/", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thomas_Britton_Harris_IV", "https://faithdriveninvestor.org/episode-135-father-son-and-faithful-investing/", "https://www.oewadvisors.com/founder"]'::jsonb),
(1255, 'KIC', NULL, 'Gary Brown', 'Board Chair', 'Mercy Ships', 'Missions & Relief Org Boards (Beyond Top-3)', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 42, NULL, 'Gary Brown is a faith-driven business leader and philanthropist active in the Christian executive and marketplace ministry community. He has been involved in organizations and networks that bring together Christian business leaders for mutual accountability, theological formation, and Kingdom-oriented business practice. His philanthropic giving and network relationships within the Christian business world make him a relevant figure for GCU''s Kingdom Impact Council as it seeks to build connections across the ecosystem of marketplace Christianity.', 'Leadership role in prominent Christian relief organization with global reach', 'Serves as board chair of Mercy Ships, a Christian organization providing free medical services globally', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Board chair of Mercy Ships, a major Christian healthcare relief organization', NULL, '["https://www.mercyships.org/about-us/", "https://www.mercyships.org/board-of-directors/", "https://www.mercyships.org/gary-brown-elected-chairman-of-mercy-ships-international-board-of-directors/", "https://oru.edu/about-oru/governance/board-of-trustees/gary-brown.php"]'::jsonb),
(1256, 'KIC', NULL, 'Dame Ann Gloag', 'Lifetime Director', 'Mercy Ships', 'Missions & Relief Org Boards (Beyond Top-3)', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 42, NULL, 'Dame Ann Gloag is a Scottish businesswoman and philanthropist who co-founded Stagecoach Group, one of the United Kingdom''s largest public transportation companies, alongside her brother Brian Souter. She built significant personal wealth through Stagecoach''s growth into a multi-billion dollar transport empire spanning buses, trains, and coaches across the UK and internationally. Gloag is a committed Christian whose faith drives her extraordinary philanthropic work, including founding Freedom from Fistula, a charity providing life-changing surgery to women in developing nations. She has been recognized with a damehood for charitable work spanning healthcare, education, and anti-trafficking initiatives in Africa. Her combination of business success, international philanthropy, and explicit Christian motivation makes her one of the most compelling examples of faith-driven capitalism in the global arena.', 'Long-term governance leader of Christian relief organization with global impact', 'Serves as Lifetime Director of Mercy Ships, a Christian organization providing free medical and surgical services globally', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Lifetime director of Mercy Ships, major Christian relief organization', NULL, '["https://www.mercyships.org/board-of-directors/", "https://www.reframe.co.uk/dame-ann-heron-gloag", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ann_Gloag"]'::jsonb),
(1257, 'KIC', NULL, 'Mike DeWine', 'Governor of Ohio', 'State of Ohio', 'Recent Christian Governors (US States)', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 42, NULL, 'Mike DeWine has served as Governor of Ohio since 2019 and previously served as Ohio Attorney General and U.S. Senator. He is a Roman Catholic whose faith has visibly shaped his governance approach, including his pro-life legislative priorities and his emphasis on compassion-centered policy responses to the opioid crisis, mental health, and child welfare. DeWine is known for a governing style that reflects Catholic social teaching — emphasizing concern for vulnerable populations and common-ground solutions. His long record of public service rooted in Catholic values and his tenure as governor of one of America''s most politically significant states make him a relevant figure for GCU''s interest in faith-informed civic leadership.', 'Current governor with sustained Catholic faith practice integrated into governance and public Christian witness.', 'Lifelong Catholic who attends Mass regularly and supports Catholic charities', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Ohio governor respected for pro-life stance and Catholic faith guiding public policy on life and community support.', NULL, '["https://www.catholicnewsagency.com/news/ohio-gov-dewine-catholic-faith", "https://www.nga.org/governor/mike-dewine/", "https://governor.ohio.gov", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mike_DeWine"]'::jsonb),
(1258, 'KIC', NULL, 'Garry Tan', 'CEO at Y Combinator', 'Y Combinator', 'Technology', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 42, NULL, 'Garry Tan is the President and CEO of Y Combinator, the most influential startup accelerator in the world, having funded companies including Airbnb, Dropbox, Stripe, Reddit, and thousands of others collectively worth trillions of dollars. He is a Christian who has spoken about faith, purpose, and meaning in his personal journey through the technology industry, and he is associated with the growing community of Christians in Silicon Valley who are thinking seriously about how faith shapes technology entrepreneurship. His position at the center of the global startup ecosystem, combined with his Christian faith and influence over the next generation of technology founders, makes him a highly significant figure for GCU''s entrepreneurship and technology programs.', 'Household-name tech leader whose public Christian faith shapes entrepreneurial ecosystem influencing thousands of founders.', 'Speaks publicly about Christian beliefs, contributing to the trend of tech elites openly embracing faith.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Leads the premier startup accelerator that launched Airbnb and Stripe, fostering innovation across Silicon Valley.', NULL, '["https://www.forbes.com/profile/garry-tan/", "https://www.riotimesonline.com/silicon-valleys-christian-revival-techs-new-power-players-seek-meaning-and-morals/", "https://x.com/garrytan", "https://www.telegraph.co.uk/business/2025/09/04/silicon-valley-finds-religion-as-techies-turn-right/"]'::jsonb),
