(1559, 'KIC', NULL, 'Doug Kiesewetter', 'Chairman', 'WaterStone (Christian Community Foundation Inc)', 'Regional Christian Foundations & Donor Networks', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 40, NULL, 'Leading one of the nation''s largest Christian community foundations serving as a conduit for Kingdom-focused charitable giving. Chairman of WaterStone, a major Christian donor-advised fund and community foundation with stated vision ''Every Christian a faith-filled intentional giver.'' Big-title, low-profile foundation chair with deep influence over major Christian philanthropic flows.', 'Big-title, low-profile foundation chair with deep influence over major Christian philanthropic flows.', 'Chairman of WaterStone, a major Christian donor-advised fund and community foundation with stated vision ''Every Christian a faith-filled intentional giver.''', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Leading one of the nation''s largest Christian community foundations serving as a conduit for Kingdom-focused charitable giving.', NULL, '["https://waterstone.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Waterstone-Q4-Winter-2024.pdf", "https://projects.propublica.org/nonprofits/organizations/841430063", "https://db.ministrywatch.com/ministry.php?ein=751750059", "https://waterstone.org/about/"]'::jsonb),
(1560, 'KIC', NULL, 'Kurt Warner', 'NFL MVP and Founder of First Things First Foundation', NULL, 'Christian Athletes (Household Names)', 'Scottsdale, Arizona', NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 40, NULL, 'Kurt Warner is one of the most celebrated and improbable success stories in NFL history. After going undrafted and spending time stocking grocery store shelves, Warner won two NFL MVP awards and led the St. Louis Rams to a Super Bowl championship in 2000 in what became known as The Greatest Show on Turf. He famously concluded every post-game interview and his Super Bowl MVP speech by thanking Jesus Christ as his Lord and Savior — a practice so consistent and public that it became a defining element of his identity. Warner is also a public believer in faith healing and co-founded the First Things First Foundation, which serves underprivileged youth and families through faith-based programs. He was inducted into the Pro Football Hall of Fame in 2017. Warner''s story is one of the most powerful testimonies of faith, perseverance, and unlikely grace in American sports history.', 'Household-name quarterback with deep evangelical convictions and sustained public faith testimony.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Kurt Warner Foundation: 14419 N 91st Avenue, Peoria, AZ 85381 | kurtwarner.org | AAE Speakers: 1-800-698-2536', 'Devout evangelical who famously thanked Jesus as Lord and Savior after winning Super Bowl MVP; public faith healing beliefs.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Super Bowl-winning NFL quarterback known for explicit Christian faith expression and public witness.', NULL, '["https://treasurehouse.org/board-members-brenda-and-kurt-warner/", "https://www.kurtwarner.org", "https://www.christianitytoday.com/2009/01/kurtwarner/", "https://www.bigspeak.com/well-known-christian-keynote-speakers/"]'::jsonb),
(1561, 'KIC', NULL, 'Mark Meadows', NULL, NULL, 'Recent Christian White House Senior Staff (Household)', 'Highlands, North Carolina', NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 40, NULL, 'White House Chief of Staff and Freedom Caucus chair defending Trump through impeachments. Evangelical who led Bible studies in Congress and cited Scripture in political advocacy. Chief-of-staff-rank evangelical with documented Bible study leadership in Congress.', 'Chief-of-staff-rank evangelical with documented Bible study leadership in Congress.', 'Evangelical who led Bible studies in Congress and cited Scripture in political advocacy.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'White House Chief of Staff and Freedom Caucus chair defending Trump through impeachments.', NULL, '["https://www.cpi.org/staff/mark-meadows/", "https://www.christiancentury.org/news/new-book-mark-meadows-confirms-trump-bible-photo-op-was-ivanka-s-idea", "https://cbn.com/news/politics/freedom-caucus-leader-rep-mark-meadows-god-gets-credit", "https://religionnews.com/2021/12/10/in-new-book-mark-meadows-confirms-trump-bible-photo-op-was-ivankas-idea/"]'::jsonb),
(1562, 'KIC', NULL, 'John Tyson', 'Chairman, Tyson Foods', 'Tyson Foods (Fortune 100)', 'Manufacturing & Industrial', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 40, NULL, 'Founded one of the world''s largest food production companies; pioneered faith integration in corporate culture through chaplaincy program. Deep roots in United Methodist Church; established Chaplain Program with 100+ chaplains dedicated to serving Christ and helping employees; company values explicitly state ''strive to honor God'' and ''be a faith-friendly company'' Active chairman of Fortune 500 agricultural/food processing company with explicit Methodist faith commitment and faith-integrated employee ministry.', 'Active chairman of Fortune 500 agricultural/food processing company with explicit Methodist faith commitment and faith-integrated employee ministry.', 'Deep roots in United Methodist Church; established Chaplain Program with 100+ chaplains dedicated to serving Christ and helping employees; company values explicitly state ''strive to honor God'' and ''be a faith-friendly company''', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Founded one of the world''s largest food production companies; pioneered faith integration in corporate culture through chaplaincy program.', NULL, '["https://religiousfreedomandbusiness.org/john-tyson", "https://www.arkansasaghalloffame.org/members/member/tyson-john-w/", "https://faithandwork.princeton.edu/people/john-tyson", "https://gospellightminute.wordpress.com/2012/09/30/john-h-tyson-bold-faith-in-the-workplace-gospel-light-minute-73/"]'::jsonb),
(1563, 'KIC', NULL, 'Harold Hamm', 'Executive Chairman and Co-Founder', 'Continental Resources', 'Christian Energy & Utility Executives (Household)', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 39, NULL, 'Harold Hamm is the executive chairman and co-founder of Continental Resources, one of the largest independent oil producers in the United States. Born the youngest of 13 children to Oklahoma sharecroppers, Hamm worked his way from poverty to build a multi-billion dollar energy empire by pioneering the horizontal drilling and hydraulic fracturing techniques that unlocked the Bakken Shale formation in North Dakota, effectively launching the American shale revolution. He is a strong evangelical Christian who funds church initiatives and has publicly testified to his faith in interviews, describing how his Christian beliefs guided him through acquisition battles and the 2014 oil price crash. Forbes has estimated his net worth at over $15 billion. Hamm''s life story — from sharecropper''s son to energy titan, anchored throughout by evangelical faith — is one of the most compelling American entrepreneurial narratives of the past half-century.', 'Household-name energy magnate with documented evangelical commitment and substantial faith-based philanthropic influence.', 'Known for strong Christian faith, funding church initiatives and publicly testifying to his evangelical beliefs in interviews.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Built Continental Resources into a major independent oil producer, pioneering shale revolution techniques.', NULL, '["https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Harold_Hamm", "https://www.umary.edu/about/news/all-stories/harold-hamm-monsignor-shea-and-dignitaries-christen-hamm-school-engineering", "https://www.umary.edu/about/news/all-stories/harold-hamm-foundation-donates-10m-and-continental-resources-donates-2m", "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bcQyLr4wLhM"]'::jsonb),
(1564, 'KIC', NULL, 'Mike Wirth', 'Chairman and CEO', 'Chevron', 'Christian Energy & Utility Executives (Household)', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 39, NULL, 'Mike Wirth has served as Chairman and CEO of Chevron Corporation since 2018, leading one of the world''s largest integrated energy companies with operations in over 180 countries and annual revenues exceeding $200 billion. Wirth joined Chevron in 1982 and spent 36 years rising through the organization before assuming the top role. He is recognized within Christian leadership circles as a prominent believer in the U.S. energy sector, listed among notable Christian executives in the oil and gas industry. Under his leadership, Chevron has pursued long-term energy strategies balancing conventional production with investment in lower-carbon technologies. His position as the CEO of a Fortune 10 company, combined with his documented Christian faith, makes him one of the most senior Christian executives in American industry.', 'Household-name supermajor CEO identified as prominent Christian energy leader.', 'Recognized in lists of well-known Christian leaders in the US energy sector.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Oversees Chevron''s operations as one of the world''s largest integrated energy companies.', NULL, '["https://influencemap.org/site/data/000/781/Meet_Mike_Wirth,_Chairman_of_the_Board_and_CEO_%E2%80%94_Chevron.com.pdf", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mike_Wirth", "https://milkeninstitute.org/events/global-conference-2026/speakers/mike-wirth"]'::jsonb),
(1565, 'KIC', NULL, 'Vicki Hollub', 'President and CEO', 'Occidental Petroleum', 'Christian Energy & Utility Executives (Household)', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 39, NULL, 'Vicki Hollub has served as President and CEO of Occidental Petroleum since 2016, making her one of the few women to lead a major oil and gas company in the history of the industry. She joined Occidental in 1982 and spent over three decades in operational and engineering roles before becoming CEO. Under her leadership, Occidental completed the landmark $38 billion acquisition of Anadarko Petroleum and has become a global leader in carbon capture technology through its subsidiary 1PointFive. Hollub is recognized among prominent Christian executives in the energy sector. Her pioneering status as a female CEO in one of America''s most male-dominated industries, combined with her technical expertise and Christian faith, makes her a compelling and historically significant profile for GCU''s Kingdom Impact Council.', 'Historic female energy leader recognized as prominent Christian executive in oil & gas sector.', 'Included among notable US Christian utility and energy executives.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Pioneering female CEO in oil & gas, leading Occidental through major acquisitions and carbon capture innovations.', NULL, '["https://www.womenspowergap.org/ceo-profile/occidental-petroleum-vicki-hollub/", "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tj3TMccQ08A", "https://business.rice.edu/person/vicki-hollub", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vicki_Hollub"]'::jsonb),
(1566, 'KIC', NULL, 'Darren Woods', 'Chairman and CEO', 'ExxonMobil', 'Christian Energy & Utility Executives (Household)', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 39, NULL, 'Darren Woods has served as Chairman and CEO of ExxonMobil since 2017, leading one of the world''s largest publicly traded companies with over $400 billion in annual revenues. Woods joined Exxon in 1992 and rose through engineering and business leadership roles before assuming the top position. He publicly identifies as Catholic and has spoken about his faith informing his personal leadership philosophy and his approach to corporate social responsibility. Woods has navigated significant geopolitical complexity — from the Russia exit following the Ukraine invasion to the ongoing energy transition debate — while maintaining ExxonMobil''s position as a global energy powerhouse. His combination of Fortune 10 executive authority and public Catholic faith makes him a distinctive figure in American Christian business leadership.', 'Supermajor CEO with public Catholic faith commitment and demonstrated faith-informed philanthropic vision.', 'Publicly identifies as Catholic, with faith influencing his leadership in energy philanthropy.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Directs ExxonMobil, the supermajor oil giant, emphasizing long-term energy strategies amid global transitions.', NULL, '["https://fortune.com/2026/01/13/exxon-mobil-ceo-darren-woods-trump-venezuela-oil-stood-up-angered/", "https://wikipedia.org/wiki/Darren_Woods", "https://engineering.tamu.edu/news/2025/10/darren-woods-87-shares-his-perspective-and-journey-with-engineering-students.html", "https://corporate.exxonmobil.com/corporate-governance/board-of-directors/darren-woods"]'::jsonb),
(1567, 'KIC', NULL, 'Tim Headington', 'Founder and CEO', 'Headington Companies', 'Christian Energy & Utility Executives (Household)', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 39, NULL, 'Tim Headington is the founder and CEO of Headington Companies, a Dallas-based conglomerate spanning oil exploration, luxury real estate, and luxury hospitality. His oil exploration success in the Permian Basin generated significant personal wealth that he has channeled into Christian ministry support, arts philanthropy, and faith-driven giving throughout Texas. Headington is also a film producer with credits including Martin Scorsese''s Hugo. He is known within Dallas''s Christian and philanthropic communities for his public faith journey and his support of evangelical ministry organizations. His blend of energy wealth, real estate, hospitality, and film — all undergirded by a faith-giving philosophy — makes him a multi-dimensional prospect uniquely positioned across several of GCU''s programmatic interests.', 'Major energy investor with documented public faith witness and substantial Christian ministry support.', 'Strong Christian context, publicly sharing faith journey and supporting ministries.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Successful oil explorer and investor with ventures in exploration, production, and real estate tied to energy wealth.', NULL, '["https://therealdeal.com/people/tim-headington/", "https://www.oklahomahof.com/hof/inductees/headington-timothy-c-2013", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Timothy_Headington"]'::jsonb),
