(1572, 'KIC', NULL, 'Lori Alexander', 'YouTube host and blogger', 'The Transformed Wife', 'Christian YouTube & TikTok Creators (Household)', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 39, NULL, 'Author of The Power of a Transformed Wife influencing homemaking movement with biblical perspective. Runs Christian blog The Transformed Wife teaching Titus 2 submission and traditional biblical roles for wives Established Christian thought leader with significant household influence in faith-based women''s content.', 'Established Christian thought leader with significant household influence in faith-based women''s content.', 'Runs Christian blog The Transformed Wife teaching Titus 2 submission and traditional biblical roles for wives', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Author of The Power of a Transformed Wife influencing homemaking movement with biblical perspective.', NULL, '["https://thetransformedwife.com/about-2/", "https://puritanboard.com/threads/the-transformed-wife.96933/", "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mrHZz8zmnCc", "https://the-end-time.org/2023/06/19/ken-alexanders-messages-to-me-about-his-wife-lori-the-transformed-wife-godlywomanhood/"]'::jsonb),
(1573, 'KIC', NULL, 'David Grizzle', 'Senior Vice President of Corporate Development', 'Continental Airlines', 'Christian Airline & Aviation Executives (Household)', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 37, NULL, 'Built culture of 250+ Bible studies and Alpha course participants at Continental Airlines through open Christian witness. "I have made a major contribution to the work of God at Continental Airlines simply by openly identifying myself as a follower of Jesus. We have 250 people involved in Bible studies and Alpha courses at Continental." Exemplifies integration of explicit Christian faith leadership in major airline operations with measurable spiritual impact.', 'Exemplifies integration of explicit Christian faith leadership in major airline operations with measurable spiritual impact.', '"I have made a major contribution to the work of God at Continental Airlines simply by openly identifying myself as a follower of Jesus. We have 250 people involved in Bible studies and Alpha courses at Continental."', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Built culture of 250+ Bible studies and Alpha course participants at Continental Airlines through open Christian witness.', NULL, '["https://www.dazzlepartners.com/about", "https://www.theologyofwork.org/the-high-calling/conversation-david-grizzle-sr-vp-continental-airlines/", "https://www.gordon.edu/stories/an-aerial-viewpoint-david-grizzle", "https://raa.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/2025-David-Grizzle.pdf"]'::jsonb),
(1574, 'KIC', NULL, 'Chris Hodges', 'Pastor and Author, Church of the Highlands', 'Church of the Highlands', 'Christian Business / Leadership Thought-Leaders', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 37, NULL, 'Chris Hodges is the founding Senior Pastor of Church of the Highlands, which he launched in 2001 with 34 people in an elementary school gymnasium in Birmingham, Alabama. Today Church of the Highlands is one of the largest churches in the United States, with over 65,000 weekly attendees across more than 25 campuses. Hodges is also a co-founder of the Association of Related Churches, which has helped plant over 1,000 churches across North America and internationally. He is a prolific author and conference speaker in the charismatic-evangelical space, with books including Fresh Air and The Daniel Dilemma. He also founded GROW, a curriculum and leadership development resource used by thousands of churches worldwide. His track record of building one of America''s largest church networks from scratch — driven by Spirit-filled leadership and organizational excellence — makes him one of the most important figures in contemporary American Christianity.', 'Household-name megachurch leader whose faith-integrated growth model shapes Christian organizational leadership globally.', 'Founder of Church of the Highlands with Spirit-filled growth conferences and worship emphasis in charismatic space.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Founding major multisite megachurch model in charismatic space with significant regional and national influence.', NULL, '["https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KfUWlQYtT1E", "https://roysreport.com/founding-pastor-chris-hodges-abruptly-steps-down-church-of-the-highlands/", "https://churchofthehighlands.com/about/leadership", "https://churchofthehighlands.com/about"]'::jsonb),
(1575, 'KIC', NULL, 'Daniel Amen', 'Psychiatrist and Founder, Amen Clinics', 'Amen Clinics', 'Christian Doctors & Healthcare Personalities (Household)', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 37, NULL, 'Dr. Daniel Amen is a psychiatrist, neuroscientist, and founder of Amen Clinics, a network of brain imaging centers that has conducted over 250,000 brain SPECT scans — more than any other facility in the world. His pioneering use of brain imaging to diagnose psychiatric conditions challenged the conventional approach to mental health and built a new paradigm for brain-based assessment. Amen has authored over 30 books, including the bestseller Change Your Brain, Change Your Life. He is a devout Christian who collaborated with Pastor Rick Warren and Dr. Mark Hyman to create The Daniel Plan, a faith-based health and wellness program launched at Saddleback Church that reached 15,000 participants in its first year and became a global movement. Amen''s rare combination of clinical credibility, bestselling authorship, and explicit faith integration in healthcare makes him one of the most influential Christian voices in the wellness and mental health space.', 'Household-name psychiatrist whose innovative brain-imaging approach and collaboration with Rick Warren bridged neuroscience and evangelical faith.', 'Public Christian testimony through books like *The Daniel Plan* co-authored with Rick Warren, emphasizing faith-integrated wellness', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Brain SPECT imaging revolutionized mental health diagnostics; authored 30+ books including bestseller ''Change Your Brain, Change Your Life.''', NULL, '["https://cbn.com/news/health/christian-psychiatrist-reveals-how-you-can-be-30-percent-happier-30-days", "https://www.amenclinics.com/blog/spirituality-how-does-it-affect-mental-health/", "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WxzUz-pzRj4", "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rWtt_lkVT0w"]'::jsonb),
(1576, 'KIC', NULL, 'Santiago Mellado', 'President & CEO', 'Compassion International', 'Christian Missions & Relief Org CEOs', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 37, NULL, 'Santiago Mellado serves as President and CEO of Compassion International, one of the world''s largest and most respected Christian child development organizations. Compassion serves over 2 million children in 29 countries through a network of more than 8,500 local church partners, providing education, healthcare, economic support, and spiritual formation through a model that centers the local church as the primary agent of transformation. He has been a vocal advocate in Washington, D.C., joining over 100 other Christian leaders in urging Congress to protect international development funding. Mellado''s executive leadership of a globally recognized Christian relief organization, his pastoral heart, and his advocacy at the intersection of faith and public policy make him a highly credible and connected figure in Christian ministry and philanthropy circles.', 'Proven executive leadership of global Christian missions impact with demonstrated influence on US foreign policy advocacy.', 'Leadership of major Christian relief organization Compassion International', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Heading one of the world''s largest Christian child sponsorship and relief organizations.', NULL, '["https://www.usglc.org/the-budget/100-christian-leaders-tell-congressional-leadership-protect-foreign-assistance/", "https://blog.compassion.com/author/jimmymellado/", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Santiago_Mellado", "https://christianleadershipalliance.org/magazine/pursuing-god-inspired-vision/"]'::jsonb),
(1577, 'KIC', NULL, 'Victor Glover', 'NASA Astronaut', 'NASA', 'christian_astronauts_aerospace', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 37, NULL, 'Victor Glover is a NASA astronaut and U.S. Navy pilot who made history in 2020 as a crew member on SpaceX Crew-1 — the first operational commercial crew mission to the International Space Station — and again as the pilot of NASA''s Artemis II mission, becoming the first Black astronaut to travel to the moon. Glover is a devout Christian who has spoken openly about his faith, with fellow believers publicly describing him as a brother in Christ whose Christian witness has been consistent throughout his NASA career. His military service as a Naval Aviator and test pilot preceded his selection as a NASA astronaut in 2013. His combination of groundbreaking aerospace achievement, military service, and public Christian faith make him one of the most compelling and historically significant profiles in GCU''s prospect universe.', 'Historic first Black astronaut to circumnavigate the moon with public Christian faith.', 'Described as a brother in Christ by fellow Christians, highlighting his public Christian faith during Artemis I mission.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Piloted NASA''s Artemis I Orion spacecraft in 2022, first Black astronaut to journey around the moon.', NULL, '["https://aleteia.org/2026/04/11/how-faith-was-the-real-fuel-of-artemis-iis-victor-glover/", "https://www.youtube.com/shorts/YSMAOfANzUE", "https://christianchronicle.org/faith-in-space/", "https://religionunplugged.com/news/christian-astronaut-pilots-first-moon-mission-in-53-years"]'::jsonb),
(1578, 'KIC', NULL, 'Caeleb Dressel', 'Olympic swimmer', 'USA Swimming', 'Elite & Olympic Athletes', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 37, NULL, 'Caeleb Dressel is widely considered the greatest American swimmer of his generation. He won seven Olympic gold medals, including five in a single Games at the Tokyo 2020 Olympics, and has set multiple individual world records in sprint freestyle and butterfly events. Dressel is an outspoken Christian who draws strength from his faith and speaks openly about his relationship with Jesus in interviews and on social media. After struggling with mental health challenges following the Tokyo Olympics, Dressel took a year away from competition and cited his faith and family as central to his recovery and return to the sport. His elite achievement, genuine faith witness, and transparent vulnerability about mental health make him a deeply compelling figure for the next generation of Christian student athletes.', 'Elite current athlete with consistent public witness of faith commitment across major competitions.', 'Openly shares his Christian faith, drawing strength from it as a dedicated believer.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Seven-time Olympic gold medalist (including five in Tokyo 2020) and multiple world record holder.', NULL, '["https://churchleaders.com/news/402674-caeleb-dressel-happiness-gods-gifts.html", "https://www.crosswalk.com/faith/spiritual-life/10-us-olympic-athletes-who-champion-their-christian-faith.html", "https://hopenation.org/10-christian-athletes-competing-in-the-2024-olympics/", "https://baptiststandard.com/news/world/olympic-gold-medalist-finds-source-of-happiness-in-god-s-gifts/"]'::jsonb),
(1579, 'KIC', NULL, 'John Coleman', 'Managing Partner', 'Sovereign''s Capital', 'Faith-Driven Investing & Marketplace Networks', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 37, NULL, 'John Coleman is Managing Partner at Sovereign''s Capital, a private equity and venture firm that explicitly integrates biblical values into its investment strategy and portfolio management decisions. Sovereign''s Capital invests in businesses across Southeast Asia and the United States with a conviction that faithful stewardship of capital and competitive financial returns are mutually reinforcing. Coleman is also a contributing author to the Harvard Business Review and co-authored Passion and Purpose: Stories from the Best and Brightest Young Business Leaders. He is active in the Faith Driven Investor network and is recognized as a leading voice on the theology and practice of faith-integrated investing. His HBR platform, private equity experience, and explicit integration of Christian theology into capital allocation makes him a distinctive and influential figure in the faith-driven marketplace ecosystem.', 'Leading faith-aligned capital deployment in marketplace; big-title low-profile Christian investor.', 'Leadership of Sovereign''s Capital, a faith-driven investment firm; featured in Faith Driven Investor network', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Managing Partner at Sovereign''s Capital, a faith-driven investment firm.', NULL, '["https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6_aBEHGW9v8", "https://www.heritage.org/staff/john-coleman", "https://www.johnwilliamcoleman.com/meet-john", "https://faithdriveninvestor.org/john-coleman/"]'::jsonb),
(1580, 'KIC', NULL, 'Andy Crouch', 'Partner, Theology & Culture', 'Praxis Labs', 'Praxis & Redemptive Entrepreneur Ecosystem', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 37, NULL, 'Cultural thinker and author shaping theological frameworks for faith-integrated entrepreneurship and cultural engagement. Contributes to Praxis''s mission of "redemptive imagination" explicitly tied to Christian faith perspectives; serves as advisor to Faith Driven Investor Intellectual leader integrating deep Christian theology into marketplace and entrepreneurial contexts.', 'Intellectual leader integrating deep Christian theology into marketplace and entrepreneurial contexts.', 'Contributes to Praxis''s mission of "redemptive imagination" explicitly tied to Christian faith perspectives; serves as advisor to Faith Driven Investor', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Cultural thinker and author shaping theological frameworks for faith-integrated entrepreneurship and cultural engagement.', NULL, '["https://andy-crouch.com", "https://www.praxislabs.org/about", "https://www.nae.org/crouchpodcast/", "https://faithdriveninvestor.org/andy-crouch/"]'::jsonb),
(1581, 'KIC', NULL, 'Julius Kim', 'President, The Gospel Coalition', 'The Gospel Coalition', 'asian_american_christian_household', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 37, NULL, 'Serving as President of The Gospel Coalition, a influential network of evangelical churches and leaders Appointed President of The Gospel Coalition (January 2020); leadership of major evangelical network Prominent Asian-American Christian leader heading major evangelical coalition with significant platform', 'Prominent Asian-American Christian leader heading major evangelical coalition with significant platform', 'Appointed President of The Gospel Coalition (January 2020); leadership of major evangelical network', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Serving as President of The Gospel Coalition, a influential network of evangelical churches and leaders', NULL, '["https://wm.wts.edu/read/rev-julius-j-kim-ph-d-joins-westminster-theological-seminary", "https://www.thegospelcoalition.org/profile/julius-kim/", "https://www.thegospelcoalition.org/press-release/julius-kim-selected-as-president-of-the-gospel-coalition/", "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PPlFrEqILTw"]'::jsonb),
(1582, 'KIC', NULL, 'Kristen Waggoner', 'CEO, President, and General Counsel of Alliance Defending Freedom', 'Alliance Defending Freedom (ADF)', 'Christian Advocacy Attorneys', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 37, NULL, 'Kristen Waggoner serves as CEO, President, and General Counsel of Alliance Defending Freedom, the largest Christian legal advocacy organization in the United States with a team of over 100 attorneys and an annual budget exceeding $100 million. She has argued landmark cases before the U.S. Supreme Court, winning major victories including 303 Creative v. Elenis in 2023, which protected the rights of creative professionals to decline work that violates their faith. Waggoner is an evangelical Christian who publicly credits her faith in Jesus Christ as the foundation for her legal work. Under her leadership, ADF has expanded internationally and continued to win at the highest levels of American jurisprudence on religious liberty, free speech, and the sanctity of life. ADF is headquartered in Scottsdale, Arizona — directly in GCU''s backyard.', 'Leading Christian legal advocate with transformative Supreme Court victories on religious expression and conscience protections.', 'Evangelical Christian who credits ''faith in Jesus Christ'' for victories in defending biblical views on marriage.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Winning landmark Supreme Court cases like Masterpiece Cakeshop v. Colorado and Kennedy v. Bremerton protecting religious expression.', NULL, '["https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kristen_Waggoner", "https://answersingenesis.org/bios/kristen-waggoner/", "https://www.theconservateur.com/interviews-tc/interviewing-kristen-waggoner", "https://adflegal.org/staff/kristen-waggoner"]'::jsonb),
(1583, 'KIC', NULL, 'Stephen Curry', 'NBA guard', 'Golden State Warriors', 'Christian Athletes (Household Names)', 'Atherton, California', NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 37, NULL, 'Stephen Curry is a four-time NBA champion, two-time league MVP, and the player most responsible for transforming modern basketball through his revolutionary three-point shooting. He has led the Golden State Warriors to four championships and was named the first unanimous MVP in league history in 2016. Curry is one of the most consistently and prominently Christian athletes in professional sports, routinely writing Bible verses on his sneakers, conducting post-game prayer and devotionals, and speaking about his faith in press conferences and social media. He attended Davidson College, a Presbyterian liberal arts school, where his faith deepened significantly. The Eat. Learn. Play. Foundation, which Curry co-founded with his wife Ayesha, reflects their commitment to serving underserved communities. His global brand, authentic and sustained Christian witness, and status as arguably the most influential player in the current NBA make him one of the most valuable Christian athlete connections available.', 'Contact Eat. Learn. Play. Foundation: eatlearnplay.org. For speaking/appearances, contact IMG or Octagon (Curry''s representation). This is a very high-profile ask — start with Eat. Learn. Play. Foundation''s partnership team, not Curry directly. Ayesha Curry (his wife) is accessible through her media platforms and is a warm entry point. GCU''s Oakland-area students and education access programs are the hook.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: Eat. Learn. Play. Foundation: 1999 Harrison Street, Suite 1400, Oakland, CA 94612 | eatlearnplay.org

Eat. Learn. Play. Foundation: eatlearnplay.org. Speaking through Washington Speakers Bureau or Premier. IMG/Octagon represents him for appearances. Ayesha Curry is a warm access path through her media and food/education platform.', 'Famous vocal Christian athlete evangelist listed prominently among faith transformers in athletic circles.', 'No direct GCU connection documented. Curry''s Stanford degree, faith, and Eat. Learn. Play. education mission align with GCU''s programs. His endorsement of GCU would be one of the most impactful in college athletics — GCU''s arena events are a strong hook.', '[]'::jsonb, '[{"date": "2026", "title": "Eat. Learn. Play. Foundation \u2014 Stephen & Ayesha Curry''s Oakland education, food, and youth foundation", "source": "eatlearnplay.org", "url": "https://eatlearnplay.org"}, {"date": "2026", "title": "Stephen Curry Wikipedia \u2014 born Mar 14, 1988 Charlotte NC. 4\u00d7 NBA champion, 2\u00d7 MVP, Stanford graduate.", "source": "Wikipedia", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stephen_Curry"}]'::jsonb, 'NBA superstar and perennial All-Star known for vocal public Christian faith and athletic excellence.', 'Dear Stephen,

I''m reaching out from Grand Canyon University — the largest Christian university in America. Your faith and your work through Eat. Learn. Play. are deeply admired here.

Would you be open to a brief call with President Brian Mueller?

With great admiration,
[Name] | Grand Canyon University | [Phone]', '["https://eatlearnplay.org", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stephen_Curry"]'::jsonb),
(1584, 'KIC', NULL, 'Larry the Cable Guy', 'Stand-up comedian', 'Larry the Cable Guy Productions', 'Christian Comedians & Creative Personalities', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 37, NULL, 'Larry the Cable Guy (Daniel Lawrence Whitney) is one of the most commercially successful stand-up comedians in American history, best known for his blue-collar humor, his signature catchphrase Git-R-Done, and his role in the Blue Collar Comedy Tour alongside Jeff Foxworthy, Bill Engvall, and Ron White. The tour''s concert film became one of the best-selling comedy DVDs of all time. He has also voiced Mater in Pixar''s Cars franchise across multiple films and television series, giving him significant reach into family audiences. Beyond his mainstream success, Larry performs regularly at Christian comedy events and family-friendly venues, maintaining a consistent presence in faith-based entertainment contexts. He is a rare crossover figure with household-name recognition in both secular comedy and the Christian entertainment community.', 'Household-name entertainer with major TV and Netflix presence performing regularly in Christian and family-friendly contexts.', 'Stand-up comedian with blue-collar humor performed at Christian events and family venues', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Mainstream stand-up comedian known for ''git-r-done'' catchphrase and clean comedy circuit performances.', NULL, '["https://edbostonministries.com/2017/10/17/larry-the-cable-guy-gives-his-testimony/", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Larry_the_Cable_Guy", "https://www.christiancomedyacts.com/comedians/", "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=g7fnOtO7m98"]'::jsonb),
(1585, 'KIC', NULL, 'Mike Huckabee', 'Fox News host, radio host', 'Fox News', 'Christian Media Personalities & Broadcasters', 'Jerusalem, Israel (U.S. Ambassador)', NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 37, NULL, 'Mike Huckabee is a former Governor of Arkansas, two-time presidential candidate, ordained Southern Baptist minister, longtime Fox News television host, and author of multiple books. In 2025, President Trump appointed him as U.S. Ambassador to Israel, reflecting both his evangelical credentials and his deep commitment to the U.S.-Israel relationship rooted in biblical theology. Huckabee is one of the most prominent evangelical Christian voices in American public life, consistently integrating his pastoral identity into his political commentary, media presence, and authorship. His unique combination of gubernatorial experience, ordained ministry, television reach across millions of households, and presidential campaign name recognition make him one of the most multi-dimensional Christian public figures in America.', 'Major household-name Christian media figure with significant influence across broadcast, radio, and publishing.

Contact: 📍 MAILING ADDRESS: U.S. Embassy Brussels (EU): Rond Point Robert Schuman 14, 1040 Brussels, Belgium | For speaking post-term: huckabee.com

U.S. Embassy Israel (current role): il.usembassy.gov. Speaking/media: huckabee.com. TBN''s Huckabee show: tbn.org. Premiere Speakers Bureau represents him for speaking.', 'Ordained Southern Baptist minister; former pastor', 'Huckabee''s appointment as U.S. Ambassador to Israel is highly relevant to GCU''s Israel studies and Christian Zionism programming. GCU has significant programming around the Holy Land and biblical geography — Huckabee''s role creates a natural partnership opportunity.', '[]'::jsonb, '[{"date": "2026", "title": "U.S. Embassy Israel \u2014 Mike Huckabee''s current role as U.S. Ambassador to Israel (confirmed Jan 2025)", "source": "U.S. Embassy Israel", "url": "https://il.usembassy.gov"}, {"date": "2026", "title": "Mike Huckabee Wikipedia \u2014 born Aug 24, 1955 Hope AR. 44th Governor Arkansas, U.S. Ambassador to Israel 2025-.", "source": "Wikipedia", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mike_Huckabee"}]'::jsonb, 'Ordained Southern Baptist minister hosting Fox News show and radio with Christian testimony.', 'Dear Governor Huckabee,

Congratulations on your appointment as Ambassador to Israel. I''m reaching out from Grand Canyon University — the largest Christian university in America.

Would you be open to a brief call with President Brian Mueller?

With great respect,
[Name] | Grand Canyon University | [Phone]', '["https://il.usembassy.gov", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mike_Huckabee"]'::jsonb),
(1586, 'KIC', NULL, 'Sean Hannity', 'Fox News host, radio host', 'Fox News', 'Christian Media Personalities & Broadcasters', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 37, NULL, 'Sean Hannity is one of the most-watched television personalities in America, hosting the primetime Hannity program on Fox News, which consistently ranks among the top-rated cable news programs in the country with millions of nightly viewers. He also hosts a nationally syndicated radio show reaching tens of millions of listeners weekly. Hannity is a devout Catholic who regularly references his faith in his commentary, having attended St. Pius X Preparatory Seminary briefly and maintained a public Catholic identity throughout his media career. His willingness to discuss faith openly on one of the largest broadcasting platforms in America, combined with his Catholic credibility and massive audience reach, makes him one of the most influential Christian voices in mainstream media.', 'Household-name Christian media figure with massive broadcast audience.', 'Catholic Christian, frequently references faith in commentary', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Fox News primetime host and radio personality with explicit Catholic Christian faith expression.', NULL, '["https://www.fox.com/hub/talent/TAL0000292728/sean-hannity", "https://www.foxnews.com/", "https://www.catholicnewsagency.com/news/45123/sean-hannity-on-his-catholic-faith-and-trump", "https://www.britannica.com/biography/Sean-Hannity"]'::jsonb),
(1587, 'KIC', NULL, 'Gary Chapman', 'Pastor and Counselor, Gary Chapman Ministries', 'Gary Chapman Ministries', 'Christian Psychology & Counseling', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 37, NULL, 'Authored ''The 5 Love Languages,'' a global bestseller with over 20 million copies sold, transforming relationship counseling worldwide. Southern Baptist pastor who frames love languages through a Christian lens in books like ''The 5 Love Languages of Apology'' Household-name author whose globally recognized framework explicitly integrates Christian theology with relational health counsel.', 'Household-name author whose globally recognized framework explicitly integrates Christian theology with relational health counsel.', 'Southern Baptist pastor who frames love languages through a Christian lens in books like ''The 5 Love Languages of Apology''', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Authored ''The 5 Love Languages,'' a global bestseller with over 20 million copies sold, transforming relationship counseling worldwide.', NULL, '["https://5lovelanguages.com/about-gary-chapman/", "https://www.sermonaudio.com/speakers/34090/", "https://cbn.com/person/dr-gary-chapman", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gary_Chapman_(author)"]'::jsonb),
(1588, 'KIC', NULL, 'Brian Mosley', 'President', 'RightNow Media', 'Christian Tech & Digital Ministry', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 37, NULL, 'Brian Mosley serves as President of RightNow Media, widely known as the Netflix of Christian content, which provides on-demand streaming access to thousands of Bible studies, discipleship videos, and Christian leadership resources for individuals, families, and churches. Under his leadership, RightNow Media has grown to serve over 7,000 churches across North America and internationally, making it one of the most widely used digital discipleship platforms in the church ecosystem. Mosley is a church member at Cadence Church in McKinney, Texas, and is recognized as a leading voice at the intersection of digital technology and Christian formation. RightNow Media''s model significantly expanded access to Christian education resources, particularly during the COVID-19 pandemic when in-person church programming was disrupted.', 'Marketplace executive scaling Christian digital discipleship platform serving thousands of churches across North America and globally', 'President of RightNow Media, Christian digital ministry company serving 7,000 churches; lives in McKinney and attends Cadence Church', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Leading RightNow Media''s global expansion to serve 7,000+ churches with premium Christian educational content at scale', NULL, '["https://www.confidein.com/blog/general/christian-tech-companies", "https://www.rightnowmedia.org/us/presidents-story", "https://exponential.org/person/brian-mosley/", "https://www.rightnowmedia.org/team/us"]'::jsonb),
(1589, 'KIC', NULL, 'Andy Mineo', 'Christian hip-hop artist and co-founder of Reach Records', 'Reach Records', 'christian_advocates_activists', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 37, NULL, 'Andy Mineo is one of the most critically acclaimed and commercially successful artists in Christian hip-hop, signed to Reach Records — the label co-founded by Lecrae that has been central to the mainstream breakthrough of the genre. He has released multiple albums that debuted on the Billboard Top 200 and has sold out headline tours across North America. Mineo''s music is known for its theological depth, honest engagement with doubt, mental health, and identity, and its refusal to use faith as a marketing veneer. He is a speaker and ministry leader whose platform extends beyond music into faith conversations and mental health advocacy. His crossover appeal to both Christian and mainstream hip-hop audiences, combined with his genuine faith and artistic credibility, makes him one of the most effective Christian voices in reaching younger demographics.', 'Influential Christian cultural figure reaching younger audiences through music and ministry platform', 'Reach Records artist with explicit faith messaging in hip-hop; speaker with public Christian testimony and sold-out tours.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Christian hip-hop artist known for thoughtful faith-centered lyrics and speaking engagements.', NULL, '["https://rapandhiphop.fandom.com/wiki/Andy_Mineo", "https://rapzilla.com/2025-06-andy-mineo-officially-announces-departure-reach-records/", "https://real.fm/music/artists/andy-mineo", "https://www.andymineo.com/"]'::jsonb),
(1590, 'KIC', NULL, 'Simone Manuel', 'Olympic swimmer', 'USA Swimming', 'Elite & Olympic Athletes', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 37, NULL, 'Simone Manuel is an Olympic gold medalist swimmer and one of the most historically significant athletes in American sports. At the 2016 Rio Olympics, she became the first Black woman ever to win an individual Olympic gold medal in swimming — a barrier-breaking achievement celebrated globally and which opened profound conversations about representation in the sport. Manuel is a Christian who has spoken publicly about turning her life to Jesus Christ and crediting her faith for sustaining her through one of her most difficult professional challenges — a diagnosis of overtraining syndrome in 2021 that threatened her Olympic campaign. Her combination of historic athletic achievement, barrier-breaking significance, and authentic public faith testimony makes her one of the most compelling athlete profiles in GCU''s prospect universe.', 'Olympic champion with public testimony of faith commitment and platform for minority representation.', 'Publicly discussed turning her life to Christ, crediting faith for overcoming challenges.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Olympic gold medalist with two golds in Rio 2016 and first Black woman to win individual swimming gold.', NULL, '["https://www.beliefnet.com/celebrity-faith-database/m/simone-manuel.aspx", "https://www.crosswalk.com/faith/spiritual-life/10-us-olympic-athletes-who-champion-their-christian-faith.html", "https://www.christianexaminer.com/news/simone-manuel-all-glory-to-god-after-winning-historic-gold-medal.html", "https://religionnews.com/2016/08/13/olympic-swimmer-simone-manuel-gives-all-glory-to-god-after-historic-gold/"]'::jsonb),
(1591, 'KIC', NULL, 'Robin John', 'CEO and Founder', 'Eventide Asset Management', 'Faith-Driven Investing & Marketplace Networks', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 37, NULL, 'Robin John is co-founder and CEO of Eventide Asset Management, one of the leading biblically responsible investment firms in the United States, managing multiple mutual funds built on the principle that businesses should create value for all stakeholders — not just shareholders. Under his leadership, Eventide has grown to manage several billion dollars in assets while demonstrating that faith-aligned investing can deliver competitive financial performance. John is a regular contributor to the Faith Driven Investor network and has spoken extensively on the integration of Christian ethics and investment practice. His firm''s flagship fund has received recognition for both its performance and its unique approach to evaluating companies through a biblical lens. Eventide''s model has been influential in shaping the broader movement of biblically responsible investing.', 'Built major faith-aligned asset management firm; marketplace leader with significant capital deployment toward Christian values.', 'Founder and CEO of Eventide, a biblically-responsible investing fund; featured on multiple faith-driven investor platforms', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Founder and CEO of Eventide Asset Management, a biblically-responsible investing platform.', NULL, '["https://www.thegospelcoalition.org/profile/robin-john/", "https://www.faithfi.com/faith-driven-investor/episode-199-the-good-investor-with-robin-john-ceo-founder-of-eventide-asset-management-7880", "https://derbyecenter.tufts.edu/people/robin-john/", "https://faithdriveninvestor.org/the-good-investor-with-robin-john/"]'::jsonb),
(1592, 'KIC', NULL, 'Lynsi Snyder', 'CEO, In-N-Out Burger', 'Carl''s Jr. (CKE Restaurants)', 'Manufacturing & Industrial', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 37, NULL, 'CEO of iconic West Coast fast-food chain; took helm from her father and maintained Christian values and marketing practices through decades of growth. Described as devout Christian who continued Bible verse practice on packaging initiated by her father; public testimony about meeting Jesus after personal struggle with addiction and abuse Woman leader demonstrating faith-centered resilience and commitment to family business values; testimony of spiritual transformation adds authenticity.', 'Woman leader demonstrating faith-centered resilience and commitment to family business values; testimony of spiritual transformation adds authenticity.', 'Described as devout Christian who continued Bible verse practice on packaging initiated by her father; public testimony about meeting Jesus after personal struggle with addiction and abuse', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'CEO of iconic West Coast fast-food chain; took helm from her father and maintained Christian values and marketing practices through decades of growth.', NULL, '["https://www.christianpost.com/news/in-n-out-billionaire-lynsi-snyder-on-spiritual-warfare-desire-to-be-plugged-in-to-gods-plan.html", "https://www.wealthbuilders.org/10-iconic-christians-in-business/", "https://restaurantbusinessonline.com/leadership/employees-favorite-restaurant-ceo-n-outs-lynsi-snyder", "https://www.godtube.com/watch/?v=1FB2JFNU"]'::jsonb),
(1593, 'KIC', NULL, 'Sajan George', 'Managing Partner', 'Praxis Labs', 'Praxis & Redemptive Entrepreneur Ecosystem', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 37, NULL, 'Key operator scaling global venture programs and partnerships within faith-based entrepreneurship ecosystem. Serves in leadership at Praxis, which builds ventures for those "motivated by their faith to address the major issues of our time" Experienced operator translating redemptive entrepreneurship vision into scaled program delivery and portfolio growth.', 'Experienced operator translating redemptive entrepreneurship vision into scaled program delivery and portfolio growth.', 'Serves in leadership at Praxis, which builds ventures for those "motivated by their faith to address the major issues of our time"', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Key operator scaling global venture programs and partnerships within faith-based entrepreneurship ecosystem.', NULL, '["https://www.praxis.co/people/sajan-george", "https://theorg.com/org/praxislabs-org/org-chart/sajan-george", "https://www.praxislabs.org/about", "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Uazm5rfYuhw"]'::jsonb),
(1594, 'KIC', NULL, 'Paul Martin', 'Managing Partner, Media, Brand, and Product', 'Praxis Labs', 'Praxis & Redemptive Entrepreneur Ecosystem', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 37, NULL, 'Driving media strategy and product development for faith-integrated entrepreneurial ecosystem. Part of Praxis team resourcing "culture makers motivated by their faith" within redemptive business movement Strategic leader shaping narrative and messaging infrastructure for redemptive entrepreneurship movement.', 'Strategic leader shaping narrative and messaging infrastructure for redemptive entrepreneurship movement.', 'Part of Praxis team resourcing "culture makers motivated by their faith" within redemptive business movement', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Driving media strategy and product development for faith-integrated entrepreneurial ecosystem.', NULL, '["https://www.praxis.co/mentors", "https://knoxvillevoyager.com/interview/check-out-paul-martins-story/", "https://www.praxis.co/business-accelerator", "https://www.praxislabs.org/about"]'::jsonb),
(1595, 'KIC', NULL, 'Henry McMaster', 'Governor of South Carolina', 'State of South Carolina', 'Recent Christian Governors (US States)', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 37, NULL, 'Paul Martin serves as Managing Partner for Media, Brand, and Product at Praxis Labs, the organization at the center of the redemptive entrepreneurship movement. In this role, he shapes how Praxis communicates its vision of businesses built to serve God and neighbor, develops media products that resource faith-driven founders and investors, and contributes to the intellectual infrastructure of the movement. Martin works alongside co-founders Andy Crouch and Dave Blanchard to make the theology and practice of redemptive entrepreneurship accessible to a growing global community of Christian founders, investors, and organizational leaders. His work at the intersection of brand strategy, media production, and Christian mission reflects the kind of integrated faith-work thinking that GCU''s entrepreneurship and communications programs aspire to cultivate.', 'Current governor with explicit Baptist faith practice and public prayer witness in official state capacity.', 'Public Christian faith commitment and church involvement in South Carolina', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'South Carolina governor recognized for Baptist faith and public prayer leadership in state governance.', NULL, '["https://governor.sc.gov/news/2022-06/gov-henry-mcmaster-holds-ceremonial-bill-signing-sc-religious-freedom-act", "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9sf-bQXi3kE", "https://governor.sc.gov/news/faith", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_current_United_States_governors"]'::jsonb),
(1596, 'KIC', NULL, 'Spencer Cox', 'Governor of Utah', 'State of Utah', 'Recent Christian Governors (US States)', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 37, NULL, 'Utah governor known for "Respectful Disagreement" initiative and mental health advocacy rooted in Mormon faith. Devout member of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints; frequently cites faith in public addresses Current governor with explicit LDS faith integration in public governance and compassion-centered leadership framework.', 'Current governor with explicit LDS faith integration in public governance and compassion-centered leadership framework.', 'Devout member of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints; frequently cites faith in public addresses', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Utah governor known for "Respectful Disagreement" initiative and mental health advocacy rooted in Mormon faith.', NULL, '["https://ffrf.org/news/releases/gov-cox-insults-utahns-with-a-day-of-prayer-and-fasting-for-rain/", "https://governor.utah.gov/press/news-release-gov-cox-declares-a-day-of-prayer-fasting-and-contemplation/", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spencer_Cox", "https://www.youtube.com/shorts/W2-P9euwSPI"]'::jsonb),
(1597, 'KIC', NULL, 'Bill Lee', 'Governor of Tennessee', 'State of Tennessee', 'Recent Christian Governors (US States)', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 37, NULL, 'Bill Lee served as Governor of Tennessee from 2019 to 2023 and is a committed evangelical Christian who made his faith central to his public service. A successful businessman who built Lee Company, a multi-state mechanical and electrical contractor, into a major regional enterprise before entering politics, Lee was open about a personal transformation that deepened his Christian faith after the death of his first wife. As Governor, he signed multiple pieces of legislation reflecting his evangelical convictions and was known for inviting pastors to pray at state events and speaking openly about his faith in public forums. His combination of business background, gubernatorial executive experience, and explicit evangelical faith identity makes him a compelling profile for GCU''s marketplace and civic leadership programming.', 'Current governor with explicit evangelical Christian identity and faith-driven criminal justice policy implementation.', 'Evangelical Christian who homeschools and speaks on biblical forgiveness; credited with faith-based foster care reforms', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Tennessee governor known for evangelical faith and biblical justice approach to criminal justice and foster care.', NULL, '["https://www.focusonthefamily.com/episodes/broadcast/trusting-the-lord-in-the-midst-of-tragedies/", "https://governorsinitiative.org/about", "https://www.tn.gov/governor/news/faith.html", "https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/politics/2018/11/bill-lee-faith/"]'::jsonb),
(1598, 'KIC', NULL, 'Glenn Youngkin', 'Governor of Virginia', 'State of Virginia', 'Recent Christian Governors (US States)', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 37, NULL, 'Virginia governor known for education reforms and faith-driven leadership message delivered at major Christian institution. Shared personal faith journey at Liberty University, affirming Christianity as central to his life Household-name current governor with public Christian faith testimony and education policy alignment with Christian values.', 'Household-name current governor with public Christian faith testimony and education policy alignment with Christian values.', 'Shared personal faith journey at Liberty University, affirming Christianity as central to his life', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Virginia governor known for education reforms and faith-driven leadership message delivered at major Christian institution.', NULL, '["https://www.liberty.edu/news/2022/03/25/virginia-governor-glenn-youngkin-gives-faith-driven-message-at-liberty-university/", "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EDbta9UZA00", "https://cbn.com/news/us/va-gov-youngkin-shares-moment-god-asked-him-take-leap-faith-we-look-lord-help-every-day", "https://juicyecumenism.com/2021/11/02/diana-butler-bass-glenn-youngkin-anglican/"]'::jsonb),
(1599, 'KIC', NULL, 'Scott Bessent', 'Nominee for Secretary of the Treasury', 'U.S. Department of Treasury', 'Recent Christian White House Senior Staff (Household)', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 37, NULL, 'Hedge fund executive bringing unique financial expertise to Treasury leadership. Protestant in French Huguenot tradition; member of historic French Huguenot Church of Charleston founded by relatives. Protestant leader with concrete faith commitment demonstrated through church membership and significant financial support.', 'Protestant leader with concrete faith commitment demonstrated through church membership and significant financial support.', 'Protestant in French Huguenot tradition; member of historic French Huguenot Church of Charleston founded by relatives.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Hedge fund executive bringing unique financial expertise to Treasury leadership.', NULL, '["https://millercenter.org/scott-bessent-2025", "https://www.christianitytoday.com/2025/01/donald-trump-nominees-cabinet-rubio-hegseth/", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scott_Bessent", "https://www.cfr.org/articles/scott-bessent-may-rue-day-he-became-us-treasury-secretary"]'::jsonb),
(1600, 'KIC', NULL, 'Eric Nelson', 'President', 'Athletes in Action', 'Sports', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 37, NULL, 'Eric Nelson serves as President of Athletes in Action, the sports ministry of Cru, which has been reaching athletes with the Gospel since 1951. AIA operates in more than 50 countries, partnering with professional, Olympic, and collegiate athletes to provide chaplaincy services, Bible studies, and evangelism opportunities in the context of sports. Nelson leads an organization with deep institutional roots in the evangelical campus ministry movement, giving GCU direct connectivity to Cru''s broader network of campus missionaries and athlete discipleship resources. AIA has been instrumental in the faith journeys of numerous professional athletes and Olympic competitors who have publicly credited the ministry with introducing them to Jesus Christ. Nelson''s leadership of this global sports ministry organization makes him a key connector between GCU''s athletics programs and the wider ecosystem of Christian sports ministry.', 'Active executive leader of major sports ministry with global reach and sustained Christian witness platform.', 'Serves as president of Athletes in Action, a sports ministry of Cru committed to giving people opportunity to know and experience God''s love.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Leading Athletes in Action, the sports ministry of Cru, reaching athletes with gospel since 1951.', NULL, '["https://athletesinaction.org/about/", "https://www.670kltt.com/2025/05/29/eric-nelson-now-president-of-athletes-in-action-to-help-spread-gospel/", "https://www.cru.org/us/en/about/our-leadership/cru-leadership/eric-nelson.html", "https://athletesinaction.org/about/our-leaders/"]'::jsonb),
(1601, 'KIC', NULL, 'Dave Blanchard', 'Co-founder and CEO of Praxis Labs', 'Praxis Labs', 'Technology', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 37, NULL, 'Dave Blanchard is co-founder and CEO of Praxis Labs, the premier organization in the redemptive entrepreneurship movement, which resources entrepreneurs and investors who want to build businesses as an expression of Christian faith and calling. Praxis operates a venture accelerator for early-stage startups, convenes a network of faith-driven investors, produces content and curriculum on redemptive business practice, and has become the intellectual center of gravity for a generation of Christian founders who believe their businesses should serve as acts of creation, redemption, and renewal. Blanchard is a regular contributor to the Faith Driven Entrepreneur podcast network and is recognized as one of the primary architects of the theological and organizational infrastructure that has given the faith-driven business movement its coherent identity. His work has influenced thousands of Christian entrepreneurs and investors globally.', 'Active leader building infrastructure for faith-integrated business practice; positioned at the nexus of entrepreneurship and Christian community development.', 'Co-founder and CEO of Praxis Labs, which facilitates a network of faith-driven investors and entrepreneurs; regularly engages with Christian entrepreneurs on integration of faith and work', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Leading Praxis Labs and the Faith Driven Entrepreneur/Investor movement''s thought leadership on redemptive entrepreneurship.', NULL, '["https://denver-frederick.com/2017/05/31/dave-blanchard-co-founder-and-president-of-praxis-labs-joins-denver-frederick/", "https://www.praxis.co/", "https://commongoodmag.com/meet-the-people-giving-undivided-attention-to-work-and-faith/", "https://www.praxis.co/people/dave-blanchard"]'::jsonb),
