(1941, 'KIC', NULL, 'Todd Anderson', 'Treasurer, AdelFi Board; Principal, 1CapitalPartner LLC', 'Christian Community Credit Union (AdelFi)', 'Faith-Based Credit Unions & Cooperatives', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 20, NULL, '27 years in senior finance roles at major institutions; now principal of corporate finance advisory firm and faith-based credit union board treasurer Treasurer of board of AdelFi (Christian Community Credit Union), faith-based credit union in California Extensive corporate finance expertise from Fortune 500 firms now channeled into Christian financial cooperative leadership', 'Extensive corporate finance expertise from Fortune 500 firms now channeled into Christian financial cooperative leadership', 'Treasurer of board of AdelFi (Christian Community Credit Union), faith-based credit union in California', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '27 years in senior finance roles at major institutions; now principal of corporate finance advisory firm and faith-based credit union board treasurer', NULL, '["https://projects.propublica.org/nonprofits/organizations/956111723", "https://www.mycccu.com/about-us/cccu-team/", "https://www.adelfibanking.com/documents/Annual_Meeting_Minutes_2024_04_23.pdf", "https://www.mycccu.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/AnnualReport_2025_WEB.pdf"]'::jsonb),
(1942, 'KIC', NULL, 'Peter Thiel', 'Investor and venture capitalist', 'PayPal (co-founder); Palantir', 'Christian Tech Leaders', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 16, NULL, 'Billionaire venture capitalist who shaped Silicon Valley by funding transformative tech like Facebook and influencing politics via protÃ©gÃ©s. Openly embraces Christianity as a source of moral clarity in ambition-driven tech, drawing on it for sold-out lectures and mentoring converts. Major donor and household-name tech visionary integrating Christian moral philosophy into venture capitalism and mentorship.', 'Major donor and household-name tech visionary integrating Christian moral philosophy into venture capitalism and mentorship.', 'Openly embraces Christianity as a source of moral clarity in ambition-driven tech, drawing on it for sold-out lectures and mentoring converts.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Billionaire venture capitalist who shaped Silicon Valley by funding transformative tech like Facebook and influencing politics via protÃ©gÃ©s.', NULL, '["https://perell.com/essay/peter-thiel/", "https://conversationswithtyler.com/episodes/peter-thiel-political-theology/", "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MExG5PQn35I", "https://www.riotimesonline.com/silicon-valleys-christian-revival-techs-new-power-players-seek-meaning-and-morals/"]'::jsonb),
(1943, 'KIC', NULL, 'Farris Wilks', 'Oil tycoon', 'Wilks Brothers LLC', 'christian_billionaries_donors', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 15, NULL, 'Farris Wilks co-founded Wilks Brothers LLC with his brother Dan following the sale of Frac Tech Holdings, their hydraulic fracturing company, for approximately $3.5 billion in 2011. The Frac Tech sale made the Wilks brothers among the wealthiest individuals in Texas and positioned them as major philanthropic players in the conservative Christian space. Farris is also an ordained pastor at the Assembly of Yahweh 7th Day church in Cisco, Texas, where he preaches regularly — adding a pastoral dimension to his profile that goes beyond pure philanthropy. The Wilks family has channeled their fracking-era wealth into significant donations to Focus on the Family, conservative Christian policy organizations, and educational causes, making them among the largest private Christian donors in America whose giving priorities align closely with GCU''s Christian university mission.', 'Major philanthropist channeling billions in fracking wealth to Focus on the Family and Christian policy advocacy with regional and national reach.', 'Family foundations support Focus on the Family and Christian nationalist groups; channels wealth from multi-billion-dollar fracking empire into Christian conservative causes', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Oil billionaire (with brother Dan) who built fracking empire and directs substantial giving to Focus on the Family and Christian causes.', NULL, '["https://www.transparencyusa.org/article/a-closer-look-farris-jo-ann-wilks", "https://ktxs.com/news/local/billionaire-wilks-family-in-cisco-bankrolls-one-of-its-own-in-run-for-texas-house", "https://www.texasobserver.org/meet-farris-wilks-kingmaker-of-the-texas-gop/", "https://dianeravitch.net/2023/09/26/who-are-the-billionaire-wilks-brothers/"]'::jsonb),
(1944, 'KIC', NULL, 'Andrea Bocelli', 'Opera singer and recording artist', 'Independent artist', 'Christian Classical Music, Opera & Performing Arts', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 15, NULL, 'Andrea Bocelli is one of the best-selling recording artists of all time, with over 90 million records sold worldwide across a career spanning more than three decades. The Italian tenor has performed at U.S. presidential inaugurations, papal masses at the Vatican, and Olympic ceremonies. Bocelli has been blind since age 12 following a sports accident and has spoken about how his Catholic faith sustained him through that loss and throughout his career, stating publicly that his faith is his compass. He has recorded multiple acclaimed albums of sacred music including Sacred Arias and founded the Andrea Bocelli Foundation, which advances education, health, and social inclusion for vulnerable populations globally. His universal name recognition, Catholic faith, and sacred music catalog make him one of the most distinctive figures at the intersection of faith and world-class artistic excellence.', 'Household-name classical tenor whose faith is central to his public identity and major-label sacred music releases', 'Devout Catholic who records religious music; states ''My faith is my compass'' in public interviews; albums include ''Sacred Arias''', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Global superstar tenor with Grammy awards and performances at US presidential inaugurations', NULL, '["https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Andrea_Bocelli", "https://www.andreabocelli.com/en/biography/", "https://www.biography.com/musicians/andrea-bocelli"]'::jsonb),
(1945, 'KIC', NULL, 'Steve Bisciotti', 'Owner, Baltimore Ravens (NFL)', 'Baltimore Ravens', 'Christian Pro Sports Team Owners & GMs', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 15, NULL, 'Leading the Ravens to multiple Super Bowl appearances and building a powerhouse franchise. Openly devout Catholic who states "my faith is the foundation of everything I do." Major household-name sports owner with explicit, public Christian faith integral to his leadership philosophy and success.', 'Major household-name sports owner with explicit, public Christian faith integral to his leadership philosophy and success.', 'Openly devout Catholic who states "my faith is the foundation of everything I do."', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Leading the Ravens to multiple Super Bowl appearances and building a powerhouse franchise.', NULL, '["https://motivationalspeakerz.com/christian-athlete-speakers/", "https://www.baltimoreravens.com/team/front-office-steve-bisciotti", "https://baltimorepositive.com/chapter-2-high-standards-low-profile-of-steve-bisciotti/", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Steve_Bisciotti"]'::jsonb),
(1946, 'KIC', NULL, 'Philip Anschutz', 'Founder and Chairman', 'Anschutz Corporation', 'Fortune 500 Christian CEOs', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 15, NULL, 'Philip Anschutz is one of the most successful and most private billionaires in America, having built an estimated $15 billion fortune through oil exploration, railroad, telecommunications, sports franchise ownership, and entertainment including AEG, the Coachella Festival, and Staples Center. Despite his massive economic footprint, Anschutz rarely gives interviews and maintains an almost mythological level of privacy. He is a devout evangelical Christian and major philanthropic donor to conservative Christian causes, including the Discovery Institute and Focus on the Family-aligned giving. Through his entertainment company Walden Media, he produced the Chronicles of Narnia film series — an explicit choice to bring C.S. Lewis''s Christian allegory to the widest possible mainstream audience. His combination of extraordinary wealth, evangelical conviction, and history of using his entertainment platform for Christian storytelling makes him one of the most consequential and least-known Christian philanthropists in America.', 'Billionaire evangelical entrepreneur and major donor whose faith drives significant Christian philanthropic initiatives.', 'Evangelical Christian who funds conservative Christian causes, including the Discovery Institute and anti-abortion groups, with ties to Focus on the Family.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Built a $15 billion fortune through oil, telecom (Qwest), sports (LA Kings), and entertainment (Coachella) while maintaining low public profile.', NULL, '["https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philip_Anschutz", "https://www.forbes.com/profile/philip-anschutz/", "https://horatioalger.org/members/detail/philip-anschutz/", "https://www.coloradosun.com/2020/12/20/philip-anschutz-fortune-colorado/"]'::jsonb),
(1947, 'KIC', NULL, 'Paula White-Cain', 'Senior Advisor, White House Faith Office', 'White House', 'Recent Christian White House Senior Staff (Household)', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 15, NULL, 'Prominent televangelist and Trump''s spiritual advisor with global ministry reach. Pentecostal pastor and spiritual advisor to Trump; delivered invocation at 2017 inauguration; ministered globally in nearly 200 countries advocating for religious freedom. Senior White House Faith Office leader with direct presidential influence and evangelical authority.', 'Senior White House Faith Office leader with direct presidential influence and evangelical authority.', 'Pentecostal pastor and spiritual advisor to Trump; delivered invocation at 2017 inauguration; ministered globally in nearly 200 countries advocating for religious freedom.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Prominent televangelist and Trump''s spiritual advisor with global ministry reach.', NULL, '["https://paulawhite.org/about/", "https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/us-politics/paula-white-cain-trump-jesus-christ-controversy-b2951338.html", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paula_White-Cain", "https://www.premierchristianity.com/news-analysis/who-is-paula-white-cain/19002.article"]'::jsonb),
(1948, 'KIC', NULL, 'Nick Sirianni', 'Head Coach', 'Philadelphia Eagles', 'Sports', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 15, NULL, 'Active NFL head coach who led Philadelphia Eagles to Super Bowl LVI and championed faith-centered coaching culture among 15+ coaches. "Fueled by faith, family" and initiated coaches Bible studies that grew from 3 to 15+ coaches; active Christian leader integrating faith into team leadership. Active Super Bowl-winning coach demonstrating faith-centered leadership with measurable spiritual impact across NFL coaching profession.', 'Active Super Bowl-winning coach demonstrating faith-centered leadership with measurable spiritual impact across NFL coaching profession.', '"Fueled by faith, family" and initiated coaches Bible studies that grew from 3 to 15+ coaches; active Christian leader integrating faith into team leadership.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Active NFL head coach who led Philadelphia Eagles to Super Bowl LVI and championed faith-centered coaching culture among 15+ coaches.', NULL, '["https://sportsspectrum.com/sport/football/2023/01/31/super-bowl-eagles-nick-sirianni-faith-family/", "https://sportsspectrum.com/sport/football/2021/01/28/eagles-coach-nick-sirianni-family-faith/", "https://www.essentiallysports.com/nfl-active-news-nick-sirianni-proves-devotion-to-faith-with-public-move-as-outgoing-legend-reveals-eagles-hcs-true-colors/", "https://www.beliefnet.com/celebrity-faith-database/s/nick-sirianni.aspx"]'::jsonb),
(1949, 'KIC', NULL, 'Esau McCaulley', 'Associate Professor of New Testament, Wheaton College', 'Wheaton College', 'Black Church Leaders & Black Evangelical Voices', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 15, NULL, 'Nick Sirianni is the head coach of the Philadelphia Eagles, having led the team to Super Bowl LVI and built one of the most consistently dominant offenses in the NFL. He is an openly committed Christian who has created a distinctive culture of faith within the Eagles coaching staff. Sirianni initiated a voluntary Bible study for coaches that grew from 3 participants to over 15 — a remarkable organic spread of Christian community within a professional sports organization. He describes himself publicly as fueled by faith and family and has given interviews explaining how his Christian faith shapes his coaching philosophy, his approach to player relationships, and his handling of the pressure of NFL head coaching. His Super Bowl success combined with his faith-integrated coaching culture makes him a compelling model of Christian leadership in one of America''s most watched sports.', 'Recognized Black evangelical intellectual and bestselling author with major platform in evangelical circles.', 'New Testament professor; author of New York Times bestseller Reading While Black with public faith testimony bridging Black experience with Scripture.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'New York Times bestselling author of Reading While Black addressing Scripture through Black perspective.', NULL, '["https://www.wheaton.edu/academics/faculty/esau-mccaulley/", "https://www.wheaton.edu/news/recent-news/2024/april/esau-mccaulley-appointed-blanchard-chair/", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Esau_McCaulley", "https://www.esau.mccaulley.com/"]'::jsonb),
