(1970, 'KIC', NULL, 'Joel C. Rosenberg', 'Founder of The Joshua Fund', 'The Joshua Fund', 'Cross-Industry (Authors with Crossover Reach)', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'low', true, 10, NULL, 'Founder of The Joshua Fund and New York Times bestselling author of prophetic novels with accurate Middle East predictions; advises U.S. leaders on Israel policy. Hailed as a modern prophet in Christian circles, Rosenberg weaves biblical prophecy into thrillers, with 7 non-fiction works on faith and end times. Household-name bestselling author with major influence on Christian thought regarding Israel and Messianic theology.', 'Household-name bestselling author with major influence on Christian thought regarding Israel and Messianic theology.', 'Hailed as a modern prophet in Christian circles, Rosenberg weaves biblical prophecy into thrillers, with 7 non-fiction works on faith and end times.', NULL, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Founder of The Joshua Fund and New York Times bestselling author of prophetic novels with accurate Middle East predictions; advises U.S. leaders on Israel policy.', NULL, '["https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HT_7JnCW-V4", "https://booktrib.com/2021/04/05/joel-c-rosenberg-on-the-reality-behind-the-fictional-thrillers/", "https://joshuafund.com/learn/latest-news/joel-c-rosenberg/", "https://joelrosenberg.com/about-joel/"]'::jsonb),
(1976, 'KIC', NULL, 'Trevor Rees-Jones', 'Founder & Chairman', 'Chief Oil & Gas', 'Christian Energy & Utility Executives', 'Dallas, TX', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 44, NULL, 'Trevor Rees-Jones is the founder and chairman of Chief Oil & Gas, one of the pioneering companies in the Barnett Shale natural gas revolution in North Texas. His early bets on shale technology built a substantial fortune that he has channeled into faith-based philanthropy through the Rees-Jones Foundation. Rees-Jones is known within Texas energy and Christian philanthropic circles as a deeply committed Christian whose giving reflects evangelical values, funding faith-driven organizations and initiatives across the region. He represents the profile of a quiet but consequential Christian businessman whose Kingdom impact far exceeds his public profile.

Other board roles: Rees-Jones Foundation', 'Approach through Texas energy sector relationships or North Texas philanthropy networks. His low-profile nature means a warm introduction is essential.', 'Devout Christian; Rees-Jones Foundation funds evangelical initiatives and faith-based causes across Texas.', 'His model of leveraging energy wealth for Kingdom purposes aligns with GCU''s vision for Christian business philanthropy.', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'Barnett Shale pioneer; founder of Chief Oil & Gas; major Christian philanthropist through Rees-Jones Foundation', 'Dear Mr. Rees-Jones,

Your work in the Barnett Shale and the Kingdom impact you''ve channeled through the Rees-Jones Foundation is a model for what Christian business leadership can look like.

Grand Canyon University is building a council of leaders with that same vision. I''d be honored to share more.

Blessings,
Sam', '[]'::jsonb),
(1991, 'KIC', NULL, 'James W. Keyes', 'Former CEO, 7-Eleven', '7-Eleven / Education Is Freedom', 'Fortune 500 Christian CEOs', 'Dallas, TX', NULL, NULL, 'high', true, 50, NULL, 'James W. Keyes served as President and CEO of 7-Eleven Inc. from 2000 to 2005, transforming operations and expanding the chain''s global footprint across thousands of locations. He subsequently became CEO of Blockbuster Entertainment, where he attempted to pivot the struggling video rental chain into a digital streaming competitor before its eventual bankruptcy. Beyond his corporate career, Keyes is a committed Christian who founded Education Is Freedom, a nonprofit dedicated to expanding access to higher education for disadvantaged youth through scholarships and mentorship. His philanthropic mission bridges Christian values, education access, and marketplace leadership — an alignment of particular relevance to GCU''s mission of providing affordable Christian higher education.

